title: Psalms 1:1
content: 1 Blessed is the man who does not walk in the counsel of the wicked, or set foot on the path of sinners, or sit in the seat of mockers.

title: Psalms 1:2
content: 2 But his delight is in the Law of the LORD, and on His law he meditates day and night.

title: Psalms 1:3
content: 3 He is like a tree planted by streams of water, yielding its fruit in season, whose leaf does not wither, and who prospers in all he does.

title: Psalms 1:4
content: 4 Not so the wicked! For they are like chaff driven off by the wind.

title: Psalms 1:5
content: 5 Therefore the wicked will not stand in the judgment, nor sinners in the assembly of the righteous.

title: Psalms 1:6
content: 6 For the LORD guards the path of the righteous, but the way of the wicked will perish.

title: Psalms 2:1
content: 1 Why do the nations rage and the peoples plot in vain?

title: Psalms 2:2
content: 2 The kings of the earth take their stand and the rulers gather together, against the LORD and against His Anointed One:

title: Psalms 2:3
content: 3 “Let us break Their chains and cast away Their cords.”

title: Psalms 2:4
content: 4 The One enthroned in heaven laughs; the Lord taunts them.

title: Psalms 2:5
content: 5 Then He rebukes them in His anger, and terrifies them in His fury:

title: Psalms 2:6
content: 6 “I have installed My King on Zion, upon My holy mountain.”

title: Psalms 2:7
content: 7 I will proclaim the decree spoken to Me by the LORD: “You are My Son; today I have become Your Father.

title: Psalms 2:8
content: 8 Ask Me, and I will make the nations Your inheritance, the ends of the earth Your possession.

title: Psalms 2:9
content: 9 You will break them with an iron scepter; You will shatter them like pottery.”

title: Psalms 2:10
content: 10 Therefore be wise, O kings; be admonished, O judges of the earth.

title: Psalms 2:11
content: 11 Serve the LORD with fear, and rejoice with trembling.

title: Psalms 2:12
content: 12 Kiss the Son, lest He be angry and you perish in your rebellion, when His wrath ignites in an instant. Blessed are all who take refuge in Him.

title: Psalms 3:0
content: 0 A Psalm of David, when he fled from his son Absalom.

title: Psalms 3:1
content: 1 O LORD, how my foes have increased! How many rise up against me!

title: Psalms 3:2
content: 2 Many say of me, “God will not deliver him.” Selah

title: Psalms 3:3
content: 3 But You, O LORD, are a shield around me, my glory, and the One who lifts my head.

title: Psalms 3:4
content: 4 To the LORD I cry aloud, and He answers me from His holy mountain. Selah

title: Psalms 3:5
content: 5 I lie down and sleep; I wake again, for the LORD sustains me.

title: Psalms 3:6
content: 6 I will not fear the myriads set against me on every side.

title: Psalms 3:7
content: 7 Arise, O LORD! Save me, O my God! Strike all my enemies on the jaw; break the teeth of the wicked.

title: Psalms 3:8
content: 8 Salvation belongs to the LORD; may Your blessing be on Your people. Selah

title: Psalms 4:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. With stringed instruments. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 4:1
content: 1 Answer me when I call, O God of my righteousness! You have relieved my distress; show me grace and hear my prayer.

title: Psalms 4:2
content: 2 How long, O men, will my honor be maligned? How long will you love vanity and seek after lies? Selah

title: Psalms 4:3
content: 3 Know that the LORD has set apart the godly for Himself; the LORD hears when I call to Him.

title: Psalms 4:4
content: 4 Be angry, yet do not sin; on your bed, search your heart and be still. Selah

title: Psalms 4:5
content: 5 Offer the sacrifices of the righteous and trust in the LORD.

title: Psalms 4:6
content: 6 Many ask, “Who can show us the good?” Shine the light of Your face upon us, O LORD.

title: Psalms 4:7
content: 7 You have filled my heart with more joy than when grain and new wine abound.

title: Psalms 4:8
content: 8 I will lie down and sleep in peace, for You alone, O LORD, make me dwell in safety.

title: Psalms 5:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster, to be accompanied by flutes. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 5:1
content: 1 Give ear to my words, O LORD; consider my groaning.

title: Psalms 5:2
content: 2 Attend to the sound of my cry, my King and my God, for to You I pray.

title: Psalms 5:3
content: 3 In the morning, O LORD, You hear my voice; at daybreak I lay my plea before You and wait in expectation.

title: Psalms 5:4
content: 4 For You are not a God who delights in wickedness; no evil can dwell with You.

title: Psalms 5:5
content: 5 The boastful cannot stand in Your presence; You hate all workers of iniquity.

title: Psalms 5:6
content: 6 You destroy those who tell lies; the LORD abhors the man of bloodshed and deceit.

title: Psalms 5:7
content: 7 But I will enter Your house by the abundance of Your loving devotion; in reverence I will bow down toward Your holy temple.

title: Psalms 5:8
content: 8 Lead me, O LORD, in Your righteousness because of my enemies; make straight Your way before me.

title: Psalms 5:9
content: 9 For not a word they speak can be trusted; destruction lies within them. Their throats are open graves; their tongues practice deceit.

title: Psalms 5:10
content: 10 Declare them guilty, O God; let them fall by their own devices. Drive them out for their many transgressions, for they have rebelled against You.

title: Psalms 5:11
content: 11 But let all who take refuge in You rejoice; let them ever shout for joy. May You shelter them, that those who love Your name may rejoice in You.

title: Psalms 5:12
content: 12 For surely You, O LORD, bless the righteous; You surround them with the shield of Your favor.

title: Psalms 6:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. With stringed instruments, according to Sheminith. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 6:1
content: 1 O LORD, do not rebuke me in Your anger or discipline me in Your wrath.

title: Psalms 6:2
content: 2 Be merciful to me, O LORD, for I am frail; heal me, O LORD, for my bones are in agony.

title: Psalms 6:3
content: 3 My soul is deeply distressed. How long, O LORD, how long?

title: Psalms 6:4
content: 4 Turn, O LORD, and deliver my soul; save me because of Your loving devotion.

title: Psalms 6:5
content: 5 For there is no mention of You in death; who can praise You from Sheol?

title: Psalms 6:6
content: 6 I am weary from groaning; all night I flood my bed with weeping and drench my couch with tears.

title: Psalms 6:7
content: 7 My eyes fail from grief; they grow dim because of all my foes.

title: Psalms 6:8
content: 8 Depart from me, all you workers of iniquity, for the LORD has heard my weeping.

title: Psalms 6:9
content: 9 The LORD has heard my cry for mercy; the LORD accepts my prayer.

title: Psalms 6:10
content: 10 All my enemies will be ashamed and dismayed; they will turn back in sudden disgrace.

title: Psalms 7:0
content: 0 A Shiggaion of David, which he sang to the LORD concerning the words of Cush, a Benjamite.

title: Psalms 7:1
content: 1 O LORD my God, I take refuge in You; save me and deliver me from all my pursuers,

title: Psalms 7:2
content: 2 or they will shred my soul like a lion and tear me to pieces with no one to rescue me.

title: Psalms 7:3
content: 3 O LORD my God, if I have done this, if injustice is on my hands,

title: Psalms 7:4
content: 4 if I have rewarded my ally with evil, if I have plundered my foe without cause,

title: Psalms 7:5
content: 5 then may my enemy pursue me and overtake me; may he trample me to the ground and leave my honor in the dust. Selah

title: Psalms 7:6
content: 6 Arise, O LORD, in Your anger; rise up against the fury of my enemies. Awake, my God, and ordain judgment.

title: Psalms 7:7
content: 7 Let the assembled peoples gather around You; take Your seat over them on high.

title: Psalms 7:8
content: 8 The LORD judges the peoples; vindicate me, O LORD, according to my righteousness and integrity.

title: Psalms 7:9
content: 9 Put an end to the evil of the wicked, but establish the righteous, O righteous God who searches hearts and minds.

title: Psalms 7:10
content: 10 My shield is with God, who saves the upright in heart.

title: Psalms 7:11
content: 11 God is a righteous judge and a God who feels indignation each day.

title: Psalms 7:12
content: 12 If one does not repent, God will sharpen His sword; He has bent and strung His bow.

title: Psalms 7:13
content: 13 He has prepared His deadly weapons; He ordains His arrows with fire.

title: Psalms 7:14
content: 14 Behold, the wicked man travails with evil; he conceives trouble and births falsehood.

title: Psalms 7:15
content: 15 He has dug a hole and hollowed it out; he has fallen into a pit of his own making.

title: Psalms 7:16
content: 16 His trouble recoils on himself, and his violence falls on his own head.

title: Psalms 7:17
content: 17 I will thank the LORD for His righteousness and sing praise to the name of the LORD Most High.

title: Psalms 8:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. According to Gittith. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 8:1
content: 1 O LORD, our Lord, how majestic is Your name in all the earth! You have set Your glory above the heavens.

title: Psalms 8:2
content: 2 From the mouths of children and infants You have ordained praise on account of Your adversaries, to silence the enemy and avenger.

title: Psalms 8:3
content: 3 When I behold Your heavens, the work of Your fingers, the moon and the stars, which You have set in place—

title: Psalms 8:4
content: 4 what is man that You are mindful of him, or the son of man that You care for him?

title: Psalms 8:5
content: 5 You made him a little lower than the angels; You crowned him with glory and honor.

title: Psalms 8:6
content: 6 You made him ruler of the works of Your hands; You have placed everything under his feet:

title: Psalms 8:7
content: 7 all sheep and oxen, and even the beasts of the field,

title: Psalms 8:8
content: 8 the birds of the air and the fish of the sea, all that swim the paths of the seas.

title: Psalms 8:9
content: 9 O LORD, our Lord, how majestic is Your name in all the earth!

title: Psalms 9:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. To the tune of “The Death of the Son.” A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 9:1
content: 1 I will give thanks to the LORD with all my heart; I will recount all Your wonders.

title: Psalms 9:2
content: 2 I will be glad and rejoice in You; I will sing praise to Your name, O Most High.

title: Psalms 9:3
content: 3 When my enemies retreat, they stumble and perish before You.

title: Psalms 9:4
content: 4 For You have upheld my just cause; You sit on Your throne judging righteously.

title: Psalms 9:5
content: 5 You have rebuked the nations; You have destroyed the wicked; You have erased their name forever and ever.

title: Psalms 9:6
content: 6 The enemy has come to eternal ruin, and You have uprooted their cities; the very memory of them has vanished.

title: Psalms 9:7
content: 7 But the LORD abides forever; He has established His throne for judgment.

title: Psalms 9:8
content: 8 He judges the world with justice; He governs the people with equity.

title: Psalms 9:9
content: 9 The LORD is a refuge for the oppressed, a stronghold in times of trouble.

title: Psalms 9:10
content: 10 Those who know Your name trust in You, for You, O LORD, have not forsaken those who seek You.

title: Psalms 9:11
content: 11 Sing praises to the LORD, who dwells in Zion; proclaim His deeds among the nations.

title: Psalms 9:12
content: 12 For the Avenger of bloodshed remembers; He does not ignore the cry of the afflicted.

title: Psalms 9:13
content: 13 Be merciful to me, O LORD; see how my enemies afflict me! Lift me up from the gates of death,

title: Psalms 9:14
content: 14 that I may declare all Your praises—that within the gates of Daughter Zion I may rejoice in Your salvation.

title: Psalms 9:15
content: 15 The nations have fallen into a pit of their making; their feet are caught in the net they have hidden.

title: Psalms 9:16
content: 16 The LORD is known by the justice He brings; the wicked are ensnared by the work of their hands. Higgaion Selah

title: Psalms 9:17
content: 17 The wicked will return to Sheol—all the nations who forget God.

title: Psalms 9:18
content: 18 For the needy will not always be forgotten; nor the hope of the oppressed forever dashed.

title: Psalms 9:19
content: 19 Rise up, O LORD, do not let man prevail; let the nations be judged in Your presence.

title: Psalms 9:20
content: 20 Lay terror upon them, O LORD; let the nations know they are but men. Selah

title: Psalms 10:1
content: 1 Why, O LORD, do You stand far off? Why do You hide in times of trouble?

title: Psalms 10:2
content: 2 In pride the wicked pursue the needy; let them be caught in the schemes they devise.

title: Psalms 10:3
content: 3 For the wicked man boasts in the cravings of his heart; he blesses the greedy and reviles the LORD.

title: Psalms 10:4
content: 4 In his pride the wicked man does not seek Him; in all his schemes there is no God.

title: Psalms 10:5
content: 5 He is secure in his ways at all times; Your lofty judgments are far from him; he sneers at all his foes.

title: Psalms 10:6
content: 6 He says to himself, “I will not be moved; from age to age I am free of distress.”

title: Psalms 10:7
content: 7 His mouth is full of cursing, deceit, and violence; trouble and malice are under his tongue.

title: Psalms 10:8
content: 8 He lies in wait near the villages; in ambush he slays the innocent; his eyes watch in stealth for the helpless.

title: Psalms 10:9
content: 9 He lies in wait like a lion in a thicket; he lurks to seize the oppressed; he catches the lowly in his net.

title: Psalms 10:10
content: 10 They are crushed and beaten down; the helpless fall prey to his strength.

title: Psalms 10:11
content: 11 He says to himself, “God has forgotten; He hides His face and never sees.”

title: Psalms 10:12
content: 12 Arise, O LORD! Lift up Your hand, O God! Do not forget the helpless.

title: Psalms 10:13
content: 13 Why has the wicked man renounced God? He says to himself, “You will never call me to account.”

title: Psalms 10:14
content: 14 But You have regarded trouble and grief; You see to repay it by Your hand. The victim entrusts himself to You; You are the helper of the fatherless.

title: Psalms 10:15
content: 15 Break the arm of the wicked and evildoer; call him to account for his wickedness until none is left to be found.

title: Psalms 10:16
content: 16 The LORD is King forever and ever; the nations perish from His land.

title: Psalms 10:17
content: 17 You have heard, O LORD, the desire of the humble; You will strengthen their hearts. You will incline Your ear,

title: Psalms 10:18
content: 18 to vindicate the fatherless and oppressed, that the men of the earth may strike terror no more.

title: Psalms 11:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. Of David.

title: Psalms 11:1
content: 1 In the LORD I take refuge. How then can you say to me: “Flee like a bird to your mountain!

title: Psalms 11:2
content: 2 For behold, the wicked bend their bows. They set their arrow on the string to shoot from the shadows at the upright in heart.

title: Psalms 11:3
content: 3 If the foundations are destroyed, what can the righteous do?”

title: Psalms 11:4
content: 4 The LORD is in His holy temple; the LORD is on His heavenly throne. His eyes are watching closely; they examine the sons of men.

title: Psalms 11:5
content: 5 The LORD tests the righteous and the wicked; His soul hates the lover of violence.

title: Psalms 11:6
content: 6 On the wicked He will rain down fiery coals and sulfur; a scorching wind will be their portion.

title: Psalms 11:7
content: 7 For the LORD is righteous; He loves justice. The upright will see His face.

title: Psalms 12:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. According to Sheminith. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 12:1
content: 1 Help, O LORD, for the godly are no more; the faithful have vanished from among men.

title: Psalms 12:2
content: 2 They lie to one another; they speak with flattering lips and a double heart.

title: Psalms 12:3
content: 3 May the LORD cut off all flattering lips and every boastful tongue.

title: Psalms 12:4
content: 4 They say, “With our tongues we will prevail. We own our lips—who can be our master?”

title: Psalms 12:5
content: 5 “For the cause of the oppressed and for the groaning of the needy, I will now arise,” says the LORD. “I will bring safety to him who yearns.”

title: Psalms 12:6
content: 6 The words of the LORD are flawless, like silver refined in a furnace, like gold purified sevenfold.

title: Psalms 12:7
content: 7 You, O LORD, will keep us; You will forever guard us from this generation.

title: Psalms 12:8
content: 8 The wicked wander freely, and vileness is exalted among men.

title: Psalms 13:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 13:1
content: 1 How long, O LORD? Will You forget me forever? How long will You hide Your face from me?

title: Psalms 13:2
content: 2 How long must I wrestle in my soul, with sorrow in my heart each day? How long will my enemy dominate me?

title: Psalms 13:3
content: 3 Consider me and respond, O LORD my God. Give light to my eyes, lest I sleep in death,

title: Psalms 13:4
content: 4 lest my enemy say, “I have overcome him,” and my foes rejoice when I fall.

title: Psalms 13:5
content: 5 But I have trusted in Your loving devotion; my heart will rejoice in Your salvation.

title: Psalms 13:6
content: 6 I will sing to the LORD, for He has been good to me.

title: Psalms 14:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. Of David.

title: Psalms 14:1
content: 1 The fool says in his heart, “There is no God.” They are corrupt; their acts are vile. There is no one who does good.

title: Psalms 14:2
content: 2 The LORD looks down from heaven upon the sons of men to see if any understand, if any seek God.

title: Psalms 14:3
content: 3 All have turned away, they have together become corrupt; there is no one who does good, not even one.

title: Psalms 14:4
content: 4 Will the workers of iniquity never learn? They devour my people like bread; they refuse to call upon the LORD.

title: Psalms 14:5
content: 5 There they are, overwhelmed with dread, for God is in the company of the righteous.

title: Psalms 14:6
content: 6 You sinners frustrate the plans of the oppressed, yet the LORD is their shelter.

title: Psalms 14:7
content: 7 Oh, that the salvation of Israel would come from Zion! When the LORD restores His captive people, let Jacob rejoice, let Israel be glad!

title: Psalms 15:0
content: 0 A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 15:1
content: 1 O LORD, who may abide in Your tent? Who may dwell on Your holy mountain?

title: Psalms 15:2
content: 2 He who walks with integrity and practices righteousness, who speaks the truth from his heart,

title: Psalms 15:3
content: 3 who has no slander on his tongue, who does no harm to his neighbor, who casts no scorn on his friend,

title: Psalms 15:4
content: 4 who despises the vile but honors those who fear the LORD, who does not revise a costly oath,

title: Psalms 15:5
content: 5 who lends his money without interest and refuses a bribe against the innocent. He who does these things will never be shaken.

title: Psalms 16:0
content: 0 A Miktam of David.

title: Psalms 16:1
content: 1 Preserve me, O God, for in You I take refuge.

title: Psalms 16:2
content: 2 I said to the LORD, “You are my Lord; apart from You I have no good thing.”

title: Psalms 16:3
content: 3 As for the saints in the land, they are the excellence in whom all my delight resides.

title: Psalms 16:4
content: 4 Sorrows will multiply to those who chase other gods. I will not pour out their libations of blood, or speak their names with my lips.

title: Psalms 16:5
content: 5 The LORD is my chosen portion and my cup; You have made my lot secure.

title: Psalms 16:6
content: 6 The lines of my boundary have fallen in pleasant places; surely my inheritance is delightful.

title: Psalms 16:7
content: 7 I will bless the LORD who counsels me; even at night my conscience instructs me.

title: Psalms 16:8
content: 8 I have set the LORD always before me. Because He is at my right hand, I will not be shaken.

title: Psalms 16:9
content: 9 Therefore my heart is glad and my tongue rejoices; my body also will dwell securely.

title: Psalms 16:10
content: 10 For You will not abandon my soul to Sheol, nor will You let Your Holy One see decay.

title: Psalms 16:11
content: 11 You have made known to me the path of life; You will fill me with joy in Your presence, with eternal pleasures at Your right hand.

title: Psalms 17:0
content: 0 A prayer of David.

title: Psalms 17:1
content: 1 Hear, O LORD, my righteous plea; listen to my cry. Give ear to my prayer—it comes from lips free of deceit.

title: Psalms 17:2
content: 2 May my vindication come from Your presence; may Your eyes see what is right.

title: Psalms 17:3
content: 3 You have tried my heart; You have visited me in the night. You have tested me and found no evil; I have resolved not to sin with my mouth.

title: Psalms 17:4
content: 4 As for the deeds of men—by the word of Your lips I have avoided the ways of the violent.

title: Psalms 17:5
content: 5 My steps have held to Your paths; my feet have not slipped.

title: Psalms 17:6
content: 6 I call on You, O God, for You will answer me. Incline Your ear to me; hear my words.

title: Psalms 17:7
content: 7 Show the wonders of Your loving devotion, You who save by Your right hand those who seek refuge from their foes.

title: Psalms 17:8
content: 8 Keep me as the apple of Your eye; hide me in the shadow of Your wings

title: Psalms 17:9
content: 9 from the wicked who assail me, from my mortal enemies who surround me.

title: Psalms 17:10
content: 10 They have closed their callous hearts; their mouths speak with arrogance.

title: Psalms 17:11
content: 11 They have tracked us down, and now surround us; their eyes are set to cast us to the ground,

title: Psalms 17:12
content: 12 like a lion greedy for prey, like a young lion lurking in ambush.

title: Psalms 17:13
content: 13 Arise, O LORD, confront them! Bring them to their knees; deliver me from the wicked by Your sword,

title: Psalms 17:14
content: 14 from such men, O LORD, by Your hand—from men of the world whose portion is in this life. May You fill the bellies of Your treasured ones and satisfy their sons, so they leave their abundance to their children.

title: Psalms 17:15
content: 15 As for me, I will behold Your face in righteousness; when I awake, I will be satisfied in Your presence.

title: Psalms 18:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. Of David the servant of the LORD, who sang this song to the LORD on the day the LORD had delivered him from the hand of all his enemies and from the hand of Saul. He said:

title: Psalms 18:1
content: 1 I love You, O LORD, my strength.

title: Psalms 18:2
content: 2 The LORD is my rock, my fortress, and my deliverer. My God is my rock, in whom I take refuge, my shield, and the horn of my salvation, my stronghold.

title: Psalms 18:3
content: 3 I will call upon the LORD, who is worthy to be praised; so shall I be saved from my enemies.

title: Psalms 18:4
content: 4 The cords of death encompassed me; the torrents of chaos overwhelmed me.

title: Psalms 18:5
content: 5 The cords of Sheol entangled me; the snares of death confronted me.

title: Psalms 18:6
content: 6 In my distress I called upon the LORD; I cried to my God for help. From His temple He heard my voice, and my cry for His help reached His ears.

title: Psalms 18:7
content: 7 Then the earth shook and quaked, and the foundations of the mountains trembled; they were shaken because He burned with anger.

title: Psalms 18:8
content: 8 Smoke rose from His nostrils, and consuming fire came from His mouth; glowing coals blazed forth.

title: Psalms 18:9
content: 9 He parted the heavens and came down with dark clouds beneath His feet.

title: Psalms 18:10
content: 10 He mounted a cherub and flew; He soared on the wings of the wind.

title: Psalms 18:11
content: 11 He made darkness His hiding place, and storm clouds a canopy around Him.

title: Psalms 18:12
content: 12 From the brightness of His presence His clouds advanced—hailstones and coals of fire.

title: Psalms 18:13
content: 13 The LORD thundered from heaven; the voice of the Most High resounded—hailstones and coals of fire.

title: Psalms 18:14
content: 14 He shot His arrows and scattered the foes; He hurled lightning and routed them.

title: Psalms 18:15
content: 15 The channels of the sea appeared, and the foundations of the world were exposed, at Your rebuke, O LORD, at the blast of the breath of Your nostrils.

title: Psalms 18:16
content: 16 He reached down from on high and took hold of me; He drew me out of deep waters.

title: Psalms 18:17
content: 17 He rescued me from my powerful enemy, from foes too mighty for me.

title: Psalms 18:18
content: 18 They confronted me in my day of calamity, but the LORD was my support.

title: Psalms 18:19
content: 19 He brought me out into the open; He rescued me because He delighted in me.

title: Psalms 18:20
content: 20 The LORD has rewarded me according to my righteousness; He has repaid me according to the cleanness of my hands.

title: Psalms 18:21
content: 21 For I have kept the ways of the LORD and have not wickedly departed from my God.

title: Psalms 18:22
content: 22 For all His ordinances are before me; I have not disregarded His statutes.

title: Psalms 18:23
content: 23 And I have been blameless before Him and kept myself from iniquity.

title: Psalms 18:24
content: 24 So the LORD has repaid me according to my righteousness, according to the cleanness of my hands in His sight.

title: Psalms 18:25
content: 25 To the faithful You show Yourself faithful, to the blameless You show Yourself blameless;

title: Psalms 18:26
content: 26 to the pure You show Yourself pure, but to the crooked You show Yourself shrewd.

title: Psalms 18:27
content: 27 For You save an afflicted people, but You humble those with haughty eyes.

title: Psalms 18:28
content: 28 For You, O LORD, light my lamp; my God lights up my darkness.

title: Psalms 18:29
content: 29 For in You I can charge an army, and with my God I can scale a wall.

title: Psalms 18:30
content: 30 As for God, His way is perfect; the word of the LORD is flawless. He is a shield to all who take refuge in Him.

title: Psalms 18:31
content: 31 For who is God besides the LORD? And who is the Rock except our God?

title: Psalms 18:32
content: 32 It is God who arms me with strength and makes my way clear.

title: Psalms 18:33
content: 33 He makes my feet like those of a deer and stations me upon the heights.

title: Psalms 18:34
content: 34 He trains my hands for battle; my arms can bend a bow of bronze.

title: Psalms 18:35
content: 35 You have given me Your shield of salvation; Your right hand upholds me, and Your gentleness exalts me.

title: Psalms 18:36
content: 36 You broaden the path beneath me so that my ankles do not give way.

title: Psalms 18:37
content: 37 I pursued my enemies and overtook them; I did not turn back until they were consumed.

title: Psalms 18:38
content: 38 I crushed them so they could not rise; they have fallen under my feet.

title: Psalms 18:39
content: 39 You have armed me with strength for battle; You have subdued my foes beneath me.

title: Psalms 18:40
content: 40 You have made my enemies retreat before me; I destroyed those who hated me.

title: Psalms 18:41
content: 41 They cried for help, but there was no one to save them—to the LORD, but He did not answer.

title: Psalms 18:42
content: 42 I ground them as dust in the face of the wind; I trampled them like mud in the streets.

title: Psalms 18:43
content: 43 You have delivered me from the strife of the people; You have made me the head of nations; a people I had not known shall serve me.

title: Psalms 18:44
content: 44 When they hear me, they obey me; foreigners cower before me.

title: Psalms 18:45
content: 45 Foreigners lose heart and come trembling from their strongholds.

title: Psalms 18:46
content: 46 The LORD lives, and blessed be my Rock! And may the God of my salvation be exalted—

title: Psalms 18:47
content: 47 the God who avenges me and subdues nations beneath me,

title: Psalms 18:48
content: 48 who delivers me from my enemies. You exalt me above my foes; You rescue me from violent men.

title: Psalms 18:49
content: 49 Therefore I will praise You, O LORD, among the nations; I will sing praises to Your name.

title: Psalms 18:50
content: 50 Great salvation He brings to His king. He shows loving devotion to His anointed, to David and his descendants forever.

title: Psalms 19:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 19:1
content: 1 The heavens declare the glory of God; the skies proclaim the work of His hands.

title: Psalms 19:2
content: 2 Day after day they pour forth speech; night after night they reveal knowledge.

title: Psalms 19:3
content: 3 Without speech or language, without a sound to be heard,

title: Psalms 19:4
content: 4 their voice has gone out into all the earth, their words to the ends of the world. In the heavens He has pitched a tent for the sun.

title: Psalms 19:5
content: 5 Like a bridegroom emerging from his chamber, like a champion rejoicing to run his course,

title: Psalms 19:6
content: 6 it rises at one end of the heavens and runs its circuit to the other; nothing is deprived of its warmth.

title: Psalms 19:7
content: 7 The Law of the LORD is perfect, reviving the soul; the testimony of the LORD is trustworthy, making wise the simple.

title: Psalms 19:8
content: 8 The precepts of the LORD are right, bringing joy to the heart; the commandments of the LORD are radiant, giving light to the eyes.

title: Psalms 19:9
content: 9 The fear of the LORD is pure, enduring forever; the judgments of the LORD are true, being altogether righteous.

title: Psalms 19:10
content: 10 They are more precious than gold, than much pure gold; they are sweeter than honey, than honey from the comb.

title: Psalms 19:11
content: 11 By them indeed Your servant is warned; in keeping them is great reward.

title: Psalms 19:12
content: 12 Who can discern his own errors? Cleanse me from my hidden faults.

title: Psalms 19:13
content: 13 Keep Your servant also from willful sins; may they not rule over me. Then I will be blameless and cleansed of great transgression.

title: Psalms 19:14
content: 14 May the words of my mouth and the meditation of my heart be pleasing in Your sight, O LORD, my Rock and my Redeemer.

title: Psalms 20:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 20:1
content: 1 May the LORD answer you in the day of trouble; may the name of the God of Jacob protect you.

title: Psalms 20:2
content: 2 May He send you help from the sanctuary and sustain you from Zion.

title: Psalms 20:3
content: 3 May He remember all your gifts and look favorably on your burnt offerings. Selah

title: Psalms 20:4
content: 4 May He give you the desires of your heart and make all your plans succeed.

title: Psalms 20:5
content: 5 May we shout for joy at your victory and raise a banner in the name of our God. May the LORD grant all your petitions.

title: Psalms 20:6
content: 6 Now I know that the LORD saves His anointed; He answers him from His holy heaven with the saving power of His right hand.

title: Psalms 20:7
content: 7 Some trust in chariots and others in horses, but we trust in the name of the LORD our God.

title: Psalms 20:8
content: 8 They collapse and fall, but we rise up and stand firm.

title: Psalms 20:9
content: 9 O LORD, save the king. Answer us on the day we call.

title: Psalms 21:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 21:1
content: 1 O LORD, the king rejoices in Your strength. How greatly he exults in Your salvation!

title: Psalms 21:2
content: 2 You have granted his heart’s desire and have not withheld the request of his lips. Selah

title: Psalms 21:3
content: 3 For You welcomed him with rich blessings; You placed on his head a crown of pure gold.

title: Psalms 21:4
content: 4 He asked You for life, and You granted it—length of days, forever and ever.

title: Psalms 21:5
content: 5 Great is his glory in Your salvation; You bestow on him splendor and majesty.

title: Psalms 21:6
content: 6 For You grant him blessings forever; You cheer him with joy in Your presence.

title: Psalms 21:7
content: 7 For the king trusts in the LORD; through the loving devotion of the Most High, he will not be shaken.

title: Psalms 21:8
content: 8 Your hand will apprehend all Your enemies; Your right hand will seize those who hate You.

title: Psalms 21:9
content: 9 You will place them in a fiery furnace at the time of Your appearing. In His wrath the LORD will engulf them, and the fire will consume them.

title: Psalms 21:10
content: 10 You will wipe their descendants from the earth, and their offspring from the sons of men.

title: Psalms 21:11
content: 11 Though they intend You harm, the schemes they devise will not prevail.

title: Psalms 21:12
content: 12 For You will put them to flight when Your bow is trained upon them.

title: Psalms 21:13
content: 13 Be exalted, O LORD, in Your strength; we will sing and praise Your power.

title: Psalms 22:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. To the tune of “The Doe of the Dawn.” A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 22:1
content: 1 My God, my God, why have You forsaken me? Why are You so far from saving me, so far from my words of groaning?

title: Psalms 22:2
content: 2 I cry out by day, O my God, but You do not answer, and by night, but I have no rest.

title: Psalms 22:3
content: 3 Yet You are holy, enthroned on the praises of Israel.

title: Psalms 22:4
content: 4 In You our fathers trusted; they trusted and You delivered them.

title: Psalms 22:5
content: 5 They cried out to You and were set free; they trusted in You and were not disappointed.

title: Psalms 22:6
content: 6 But I am a worm and not a man, scorned by men and despised by the people.

title: Psalms 22:7
content: 7 All who see me mock me; they sneer and shake their heads:

title: Psalms 22:8
content: 8 “He trusts in the LORD, let the LORD deliver him; let the LORD rescue him, since He delights in him.”

title: Psalms 22:9
content: 9 Yet You brought me forth from the womb; You made me secure at my mother’s breast.

title: Psalms 22:10
content: 10 From birth I was cast upon You; from my mother’s womb You have been my God.

title: Psalms 22:11
content: 11 Be not far from me, for trouble is near and there is no one to help.

title: Psalms 22:12
content: 12 Many bulls surround me; strong bulls of Bashan encircle me.

title: Psalms 22:13
content: 13 They open their jaws against me like lions that roar and maul.

title: Psalms 22:14
content: 14 I am poured out like water, and all my bones are disjointed. My heart is like wax; it melts away within me.

title: Psalms 22:15
content: 15 My strength is dried up like a potsherd, and my tongue sticks to the roof of my mouth. You lay me in the dust of death.

title: Psalms 22:16
content: 16 For dogs surround me; a band of evil men encircles me; they have pierced my hands and feet.

title: Psalms 22:17
content: 17 I can count all my bones; they stare and gloat over me.

title: Psalms 22:18
content: 18 They divide my garments among them and cast lots for my clothing.

title: Psalms 22:19
content: 19 But You, O LORD, be not far off; O my Strength, come quickly to help me.

title: Psalms 22:20
content: 20 Deliver my soul from the sword, my precious life from the power of wild dogs.

title: Psalms 22:21
content: 21 Save me from the mouth of the lion; at the horns of the wild oxen You have answered me!

title: Psalms 22:22
content: 22 I will proclaim Your name to my brothers; I will praise You in the assembly.

title: Psalms 22:23
content: 23 You who fear the LORD, praise Him! All descendants of Jacob, honor Him! All offspring of Israel, revere Him!

title: Psalms 22:24
content: 24 For He has not despised or detested the torment of the afflicted. He has not hidden His face from him, but has attended to his cry for help.

title: Psalms 22:25
content: 25 My praise for You resounds in the great assembly; I will fulfill my vows before those who fear You.

title: Psalms 22:26
content: 26 The poor will eat and be satisfied; those who seek the LORD will praise Him. May your hearts live forever!

title: Psalms 22:27
content: 27 All the ends of the earth will remember and turn to the LORD. All the families of the nations will bow down before Him.

title: Psalms 22:28
content: 28 For dominion belongs to the LORD and He rules over the nations.

title: Psalms 22:29
content: 29 All the rich of the earth will feast and worship; all who go down to the dust will kneel before Him—even those unable to preserve their lives.

title: Psalms 22:30
content: 30 Posterity will serve Him; they will declare the Lord to a new generation.

title: Psalms 22:31
content: 31 They will come and proclaim His righteousness to a people yet unborn—all that He has done.

title: Psalms 23:0
content: 0 A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 23:1
content: 1 The LORD is my shepherd; I shall not want.

title: Psalms 23:2
content: 2 He makes me lie down in green pastures; He leads me beside quiet waters.

title: Psalms 23:3
content: 3 He restores my soul; He guides me in the paths of righteousness for the sake of His name.

title: Psalms 23:4
content: 4 Even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil, for You are with me; Your rod and Your staff, they comfort me.

title: Psalms 23:5
content: 5 You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies. You anoint my head with oil; my cup overflows.

title: Psalms 23:6
content: 6 Surely goodness and mercy will follow me all the days of my life, and I will dwell in the house of the LORD forever.

title: Psalms 24:0
content: 0 A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 24:1
content: 1 The earth is the LORD’s, and the fullness thereof, the world and all who dwell therein.

title: Psalms 24:2
content: 2 For He has founded it upon the seas and established it upon the waters.

title: Psalms 24:3
content: 3 Who may ascend the hill of the LORD? Who may stand in His holy place?

title: Psalms 24:4
content: 4 He who has clean hands and a pure heart, who does not lift up his soul to an idol or swear deceitfully.

title: Psalms 24:5
content: 5 He will receive blessing from the LORD and vindication from the God of his salvation.

title: Psalms 24:6
content: 6 Such is the generation of those who seek Him, who seek Your face, O God of Jacob. Selah

title: Psalms 24:7
content: 7 Lift up your heads, O gates! Be lifted up, O ancient doors, that the King of Glory may enter!

title: Psalms 24:8
content: 8 Who is this King of Glory? The LORD strong and mighty, the LORD mighty in battle.

title: Psalms 24:9
content: 9 Lift up your heads, O gates! Be lifted up, O ancient doors, that the King of Glory may enter!

title: Psalms 24:10
content: 10 Who is He, this King of Glory? The LORD of Hosts—He is the King of Glory. Selah

title: Psalms 25:0
content: 0 Of David.

title: Psalms 25:1
content: 1 To You, O LORD, I lift up my soul;

title: Psalms 25:2
content: 2 in You, my God, I trust. Do not let me be put to shame; do not let my enemies exult over me.

title: Psalms 25:3
content: 3 Surely none who wait for You will be put to shame; but those who engage in treachery without cause will be disgraced.

title: Psalms 25:4
content: 4 Show me Your ways, O LORD; teach me Your paths.

title: Psalms 25:5
content: 5 Guide me in Your truth and teach me, for You are the God of my salvation; all day long I wait for You.

title: Psalms 25:6
content: 6 Remember, O LORD, Your compassion and loving devotion, for they are from age to age.

title: Psalms 25:7
content: 7 Remember not the sins of my youth, nor my rebellious acts; remember me according to Your loving devotion, because of Your goodness, O LORD.

title: Psalms 25:8
content: 8 Good and upright is the LORD; therefore He shows sinners the way.

title: Psalms 25:9
content: 9 He guides the humble in what is right and teaches them His way.

title: Psalms 25:10
content: 10 All the LORD’s ways are loving and faithful to those who keep His covenant and His decrees.

title: Psalms 25:11
content: 11 For the sake of Your name, O LORD, forgive my iniquity, for it is great.

title: Psalms 25:12
content: 12 Who is the man who fears the LORD? He will instruct him in the path chosen for him.

title: Psalms 25:13
content: 13 His soul will dwell in prosperity, and his descendants will inherit the land.

title: Psalms 25:14
content: 14 The LORD confides in those who fear Him, and reveals His covenant to them.

title: Psalms 25:15
content: 15 My eyes are always on the LORD, for He will free my feet from the mesh.

title: Psalms 25:16
content: 16 Turn to me and be gracious, for I am lonely and afflicted.

title: Psalms 25:17
content: 17 The troubles of my heart increase; free me from my distress.

title: Psalms 25:18
content: 18 Consider my affliction and trouble, and take away all my sins.

title: Psalms 25:19
content: 19 Consider my enemies, for they are many, and they hate me with vicious hatred.

title: Psalms 25:20
content: 20 Guard my soul and deliver me; let me not be put to shame, for I take refuge in You.

title: Psalms 25:21
content: 21 May integrity and uprightness preserve me, because I wait for You.

title: Psalms 25:22
content: 22 Redeem Israel, O God, from all its distress.

title: Psalms 26:0
content: 0 Of David.

title: Psalms 26:1
content: 1 Vindicate me, O LORD! For I have walked with integrity; I have trusted in the LORD without wavering.

title: Psalms 26:2
content: 2 Test me, O LORD, and try me; examine my heart and mind.

title: Psalms 26:3
content: 3 For Your loving devotion is before my eyes, and I have walked in Your truth.

title: Psalms 26:4
content: 4 I do not sit with deceitful men, nor keep company with hypocrites.

title: Psalms 26:5
content: 5 I hate the mob of evildoers, and refuse to sit with the wicked.

title: Psalms 26:6
content: 6 I wash my hands in innocence that I may go about Your altar, O LORD,

title: Psalms 26:7
content: 7 to raise my voice in thanksgiving and declare all Your wonderful works.

title: Psalms 26:8
content: 8 O LORD, I love the house where You dwell, the place where Your glory resides.

title: Psalms 26:9
content: 9 Do not take my soul away with sinners, or my life with men of bloodshed,

title: Psalms 26:10
content: 10 in whose hands are wicked schemes, whose right hands are full of bribes.

title: Psalms 26:11
content: 11 But I will walk with integrity; redeem me and be merciful to me.

title: Psalms 26:12
content: 12 My feet stand on level ground; in the congregations I will bless the LORD.

title: Psalms 27:0
content: 0 Of David.

title: Psalms 27:1
content: 1 The LORD is my light and my salvation—whom shall I fear? The LORD is the stronghold of my life—whom shall I dread?

title: Psalms 27:2
content: 2 When the wicked came upon me to devour my flesh, my enemies and foes stumbled and fell.

title: Psalms 27:3
content: 3 Though an army encamps around me, my heart will not fear; though a war breaks out against me, I will keep my trust.

title: Psalms 27:4
content: 4 One thing I have asked of the LORD; this is what I desire: to dwell in the house of the LORD all the days of my life, to gaze on the beauty of the LORD and seek Him in His temple.

title: Psalms 27:5
content: 5 For in the day of trouble He will hide me in His shelter; He will conceal me under the cover of His tent; He will set me high upon a rock.

title: Psalms 27:6
content: 6 Then my head will be held high above my enemies around me. At His tabernacle I will offer sacrifices with shouts of joy; I will sing and make music to the LORD.

title: Psalms 27:7
content: 7 Hear, O LORD, my voice when I call; be merciful and answer me.

title: Psalms 27:8
content: 8 My heart said, “Seek His face.” Your face, O LORD, I will seek.

title: Psalms 27:9
content: 9 Hide not Your face from me, nor turn away Your servant in anger. You have been my helper; do not leave me or forsake me, O God of my salvation.

title: Psalms 27:10
content: 10 Though my father and mother forsake me, the LORD will receive me.

title: Psalms 27:11
content: 11 Teach me Your way, O LORD, and lead me on a level path, because of my oppressors.

title: Psalms 27:12
content: 12 Do not hand me over to the will of my foes, for false witnesses rise up against me, breathing out violence.

title: Psalms 27:13
content: 13 Still I am certain to see the goodness of the LORD in the land of the living.

title: Psalms 27:14
content: 14 Wait patiently for the LORD; be strong and courageous. Wait patiently for the LORD!

title: Psalms 28:0
content: 0 Of David.

title: Psalms 28:1
content: 1 To You, O LORD, I call; be not deaf to me, O my Rock. For if You remain silent, I will be like those descending to the Pit.

title: Psalms 28:2
content: 2 Hear my cry for mercy when I call to You for help, when I lift up my hands toward Your holy sanctuary.

title: Psalms 28:3
content: 3 Do not drag me away with the wicked, and with the workers of iniquity, who speak peace to their neighbors while malice is in their hearts.

title: Psalms 28:4
content: 4 Repay them according to their deeds and for their works of evil. Repay them for what their hands have done; bring back on them what they deserve.

title: Psalms 28:5
content: 5 Since they show no regard for the works of the LORD or what His hands have done, He will tear them down and never rebuild them.

title: Psalms 28:6
content: 6 Blessed be the LORD, for He has heard my cry for mercy.

title: Psalms 28:7
content: 7 The LORD is my strength and my shield; my heart trusts in Him, and I am helped. Therefore my heart rejoices, and I give thanks to Him with my song.

title: Psalms 28:8
content: 8 The LORD is the strength of His people, a stronghold of salvation for His anointed.

title: Psalms 28:9
content: 9 Save Your people and bless Your inheritance; shepherd them and carry them forever.

title: Psalms 29:0
content: 0 A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 29:1
content: 1 Ascribe to the LORD, O heavenly beings, ascribe to the LORD glory and strength.

title: Psalms 29:2
content: 2 Ascribe to the LORD the glory due His name; worship the LORD in the splendor of His holiness.

title: Psalms 29:3
content: 3 The voice of the LORD is over the waters; the God of glory thunders; the LORD is heard over many waters.

title: Psalms 29:4
content: 4 The voice of the LORD is powerful; the voice of the LORD is majestic.

title: Psalms 29:5
content: 5 The voice of the LORD breaks the cedars; the LORD shatters the cedars of Lebanon.

title: Psalms 29:6
content: 6 He makes Lebanon skip like a calf, and Sirion like a young wild ox.

title: Psalms 29:7
content: 7 The voice of the LORD strikes with flames of fire.

title: Psalms 29:8
content: 8 The voice of the LORD shakes the wilderness; the LORD shakes the Wilderness of Kadesh.

title: Psalms 29:9
content: 9 The voice of the LORD twists the oaks and strips the forests bare. And in His temple all cry, “Glory!”

title: Psalms 29:10
content: 10 The LORD sits enthroned over the flood; the LORD is enthroned as King forever.

title: Psalms 29:11
content: 11 The LORD gives His people strength; the LORD blesses His people with peace.

title: Psalms 30:0
content: 0 A Psalm. A song for the dedication of the temple. Of David.

title: Psalms 30:1
content: 1 I will exalt You, O LORD, for You have lifted me up and have not allowed my foes to rejoice over me.

title: Psalms 30:2
content: 2 O LORD my God, I cried to You for help, and You healed me.

title: Psalms 30:3
content: 3 O LORD, You pulled me up from Sheol; You spared me from descending into the Pit.

title: Psalms 30:4
content: 4 Sing to the LORD, O you His saints, and praise His holy name.

title: Psalms 30:5
content: 5 For His anger is fleeting, but His favor lasts a lifetime. Weeping may stay the night, but joy comes in the morning.

title: Psalms 30:6
content: 6 In prosperity I said, “I will never be shaken.”

title: Psalms 30:7
content: 7 O LORD, You favored me; You made my mountain stand strong. When You hid Your face, I was dismayed.

title: Psalms 30:8
content: 8 To You, O LORD, I called, and I begged my Lord for mercy:

title: Psalms 30:9
content: 9 “What gain is there in my bloodshed, in my descent to the Pit? Will the dust praise You? Will it proclaim Your faithfulness?

title: Psalms 30:10
content: 10 Hear me, O LORD, and have mercy; O LORD, be my helper.”

title: Psalms 30:11
content: 11 You turned my mourning into dancing; You peeled off my sackcloth and clothed me with joy,

title: Psalms 30:12
content: 12 that my heart may sing Your praises and not be silent. O LORD my God, I will give thanks forever.

title: Psalms 31:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 31:1
content: 1 In You, O LORD, I have taken refuge; let me never be put to shame; save me by Your righteousness.

title: Psalms 31:2
content: 2 Incline Your ear to me; come quickly to my rescue. Be my rock of refuge, the stronghold of my deliverance.

title: Psalms 31:3
content: 3 For You are my rock and my fortress; lead me and guide me for the sake of Your name.

title: Psalms 31:4
content: 4 You free me from the net laid out for me, for You are my refuge.

title: Psalms 31:5
content: 5 Into Your hands I commit my spirit; You have redeemed me, O LORD, God of truth.

title: Psalms 31:6
content: 6 I hate those who cling to worthless idols, but in the LORD I trust.

title: Psalms 31:7
content: 7 I will be glad and rejoice in Your loving devotion, for You have seen my affliction; You have known the anguish of my soul.

title: Psalms 31:8
content: 8 You have not delivered me to the enemy; You have set my feet in the open.

title: Psalms 31:9
content: 9 Be merciful to me, O LORD, for I am in distress; my eyes fail from sorrow, my soul and body as well.

title: Psalms 31:10
content: 10 For my life is consumed with grief and my years with groaning; my iniquity has drained my strength, and my bones are wasting away.

title: Psalms 31:11
content: 11 Among all my enemies I am a disgrace, and among my neighbors even more. I am dreaded by my friends—they flee when they see me on the street.

title: Psalms 31:12
content: 12 I am forgotten like a dead man, out of mind. I am like a broken vessel.

title: Psalms 31:13
content: 13 For I hear the slander of many; there is terror on every side. They conspire against me and plot to take my life.

title: Psalms 31:14
content: 14 But I trust in You, O LORD; I say, “You are my God.”

title: Psalms 31:15
content: 15 My times are in Your hands; deliver me from my enemies and from those who pursue me.

title: Psalms 31:16
content: 16 Make Your face shine on Your servant; save me by Your loving devotion.

title: Psalms 31:17
content: 17 O LORD, let me not be ashamed, for I have called on You. Let the wicked be put to shame; let them lie silent in Sheol.

title: Psalms 31:18
content: 18 May lying lips be silenced—lips that speak with arrogance against the righteous, full of pride and contempt.

title: Psalms 31:19
content: 19 How great is Your goodness which You have laid up for those who fear You, which You have bestowed before the sons of men on those who take refuge in You!

title: Psalms 31:20
content: 20 You hide them in the secret place of Your presence from the schemes of men. You conceal them in Your shelter from accusing tongues.

title: Psalms 31:21
content: 21 Blessed be the LORD, for He has shown me His loving devotion in a city under siege.

title: Psalms 31:22
content: 22 In my alarm I said, “I am cut off from Your sight!” But You heard my plea for mercy when I called to You for help.

title: Psalms 31:23
content: 23 Love the LORD, all His saints. The LORD preserves the faithful, but fully repays the arrogant.

title: Psalms 31:24
content: 24 Be strong and courageous, all you who hope in the LORD.

title: Psalms 32:0
content: 0 Of David. A Maskil.

title: Psalms 32:1
content: 1 Blessed is he whose transgressions are forgiven, whose sins are covered.

title: Psalms 32:2
content: 2 Blessed is the man whose iniquity the LORD does not count against him, in whose spirit there is no deceit.

title: Psalms 32:3
content: 3 When I kept silent, my bones became brittle from my groaning all day long.

title: Psalms 32:4
content: 4 For day and night Your hand was heavy upon me; my strength was drained as in the summer heat. Selah

title: Psalms 32:5
content: 5 Then I acknowledged my sin to You and did not hide my iniquity. I said, “I will confess my transgressions to the LORD,” and You forgave the guilt of my sin. Selah

title: Psalms 32:6
content: 6 Therefore let all the godly pray to You while You may be found. Surely when great waters rise, they will not come near.

title: Psalms 32:7
content: 7 You are my hiding place. You protect me from trouble; You surround me with songs of deliverance. Selah

title: Psalms 32:8
content: 8 I will instruct you and teach you the way you should go; I will give you counsel and watch over you.

title: Psalms 32:9
content: 9 Do not be like the horse or mule, which have no understanding; they must be controlled with bit and bridle to make them come to you.

title: Psalms 32:10
content: 10 Many are the sorrows of the wicked, but loving devotion surrounds him who trusts in the LORD.

title: Psalms 32:11
content: 11 Be glad in the LORD and rejoice, O righteous ones; shout for joy, all you upright in heart.

title: Psalms 33:1
content: 1 Rejoice in the LORD, O righteous ones; it is fitting for the upright to praise Him.

title: Psalms 33:2
content: 2 Praise the LORD with the harp; make music to Him with ten strings.

title: Psalms 33:3
content: 3 Sing to Him a new song; play skillfully with a shout of joy.

title: Psalms 33:4
content: 4 For the word of the LORD is upright, and all His work is trustworthy.

title: Psalms 33:5
content: 5 The LORD loves righteousness and justice; the earth is full of His loving devotion.

title: Psalms 33:6
content: 6 By the word of the LORD the heavens were made, and all the stars by the breath of His mouth.

title: Psalms 33:7
content: 7 He piles up the waters of the sea; He puts the depths into storehouses.

title: Psalms 33:8
content: 8 Let all the earth fear the LORD; let all the people of the world revere Him.

title: Psalms 33:9
content: 9 For He spoke, and it came to be; He commanded, and it stood firm.

title: Psalms 33:10
content: 10 The LORD frustrates the plans of the nations; He thwarts the devices of the peoples.

title: Psalms 33:11
content: 11 The counsel of the LORD stands forever, the purposes of His heart to all generations.

title: Psalms 33:12
content: 12 Blessed is the nation whose God is the LORD, the people He has chosen as His inheritance!

title: Psalms 33:13
content: 13 The LORD looks down from heaven; He sees all the sons of men.

title: Psalms 33:14
content: 14 From His dwelling place He gazes on all who inhabit the earth.

title: Psalms 33:15
content: 15 He shapes the hearts of each; He considers all their works.

title: Psalms 33:16
content: 16 No king is saved by his vast army; no warrior is delivered by his great strength.

title: Psalms 33:17
content: 17 A horse is a vain hope for salvation; even its great strength cannot save.

title: Psalms 33:18
content: 18 Surely the eyes of the LORD are on those who fear Him, on those whose hope is in His loving devotion

title: Psalms 33:19
content: 19 to deliver them from death and keep them alive in famine.

title: Psalms 33:20
content: 20 Our soul waits for the LORD; He is our help and our shield.

title: Psalms 33:21
content: 21 For our hearts rejoice in Him, since we trust in His holy name.

title: Psalms 33:22
content: 22 May Your loving devotion rest on us, O LORD, as we put our hope in You.

title: Psalms 34:0
content: 0 Of David, when he pretended to be insane before Abimelech, so that the king drove him away.

title: Psalms 34:1
content: 1 I will bless the LORD at all times; His praise will always be on my lips.

title: Psalms 34:2
content: 2 My soul boasts in the LORD; let the oppressed hear and rejoice.

title: Psalms 34:3
content: 3 Magnify the LORD with me; let us exalt His name together.

title: Psalms 34:4
content: 4 I sought the LORD, and He answered me; He delivered me from all my fears.

title: Psalms 34:5
content: 5 Those who look to Him are radiant with joy; their faces shall never be ashamed.

title: Psalms 34:6
content: 6 This poor man called out, and the LORD heard him; He saved him from all his troubles.

title: Psalms 34:7
content: 7 The angel of the LORD encamps around those who fear Him, and he delivers them.

title: Psalms 34:8
content: 8 Taste and see that the LORD is good; blessed is the man who takes refuge in Him!

title: Psalms 34:9
content: 9 Fear the LORD, you His saints, for those who fear Him lack nothing.

title: Psalms 34:10
content: 10 Young lions go lacking and hungry, but those who seek the LORD lack no good thing.

title: Psalms 34:11
content: 11 Come, children, listen to me; I will teach you the fear of the LORD.

title: Psalms 34:12
content: 12 Who is the man who delights in life, who desires to see good days?

title: Psalms 34:13
content: 13 Keep your tongue from evil and your lips from deceitful speech.

title: Psalms 34:14
content: 14 Turn away from evil and do good; seek peace and pursue it.

title: Psalms 34:15
content: 15 The eyes of the LORD are on the righteous, and His ears are inclined to their cry.

title: Psalms 34:16
content: 16 But the face of the LORD is against those who do evil, to wipe out all memory of them from the earth.

title: Psalms 34:17
content: 17 The righteous cry out, and the LORD hears; He delivers them from all their troubles.

title: Psalms 34:18
content: 18 The LORD is near to the brokenhearted; He saves the contrite in spirit.

title: Psalms 34:19
content: 19 Many are the afflictions of the righteous, but the LORD delivers him from them all.

title: Psalms 34:20
content: 20 He protects all his bones; not one of them will be broken.

title: Psalms 34:21
content: 21 Evil will slay the wicked, and the haters of the righteous will be condemned.

title: Psalms 34:22
content: 22 The LORD redeems His servants, and none who take refuge in Him will be condemned.

title: Psalms 35:0
content: 0 Of David.

title: Psalms 35:1
content: 1 Contend with my opponents, O LORD; fight against those who fight against me.

title: Psalms 35:2
content: 2 Take up Your shield and buckler; arise and come to my aid.

title: Psalms 35:3
content: 3 Draw the spear and javelin against my pursuers; say to my soul: “I am your salvation.”

title: Psalms 35:4
content: 4 May those who seek my life be disgraced and put to shame; may those who plan to harm me be driven back and confounded.

title: Psalms 35:5
content: 5 May they be like chaff in the wind, as the angel of the LORD drives them away.

title: Psalms 35:6
content: 6 May their path be dark and slick, as the angel of the LORD pursues.

title: Psalms 35:7
content: 7 For without cause they laid their net for me; without reason they dug a pit for my soul.

title: Psalms 35:8
content: 8 May ruin befall them by surprise; may the net they hid ensnare them; may they fall into the hazard they created.

title: Psalms 35:9
content: 9 Then my soul will rejoice in the LORD and exult in His salvation.

title: Psalms 35:10
content: 10 All my bones will exclaim, “Who is like You, O LORD, who delivers the afflicted from the aggressor, the poor and needy from the robber?”

title: Psalms 35:11
content: 11 Hostile witnesses come forward; they make charges I know nothing about.

title: Psalms 35:12
content: 12 They repay me evil for good, to the bereavement of my soul.

title: Psalms 35:13
content: 13 Yet when they were ill, I put on sackcloth; I humbled myself with fasting, but my prayers returned unanswered.

title: Psalms 35:14
content: 14 I paced about as for my friend or brother; I was bowed down with grief, like one mourning for his mother.

title: Psalms 35:15
content: 15 But when I stumbled, they assembled in glee; they gathered together against me. Assailants I did not know slandered me without ceasing.

title: Psalms 35:16
content: 16 Like godless jesters at a feast, they gnashed their teeth at me.

title: Psalms 35:17
content: 17 How long, O Lord, will You look on? Rescue my soul from their ravages, my precious life from these lions.

title: Psalms 35:18
content: 18 Then I will give You thanks in the great assembly; I will praise You among many people.

title: Psalms 35:19
content: 19 Let not my enemies gloat over me without cause, nor those who hate me without reason wink in malice.

title: Psalms 35:20
content: 20 For they do not speak peace, but they devise deceitful schemes against those who live quietly in the land.

title: Psalms 35:21
content: 21 They gape at me and say, “Aha, aha! Our eyes have seen!”

title: Psalms 35:22
content: 22 O LORD, You have seen it; be not silent. O Lord, be not far from me.

title: Psalms 35:23
content: 23 Awake and rise to my defense, to my cause, my God and my Lord!

title: Psalms 35:24
content: 24 Vindicate me by Your righteousness, O LORD my God, and do not let them gloat over me.

title: Psalms 35:25
content: 25 Let them not say in their hearts, “Aha, just what we wanted!” Let them not say, “We have swallowed him up!”

title: Psalms 35:26
content: 26 May those who gloat in my distress be ashamed and confounded; may those who exalt themselves over me be clothed in shame and reproach.

title: Psalms 35:27
content: 27 May those who favor my vindication shout for joy and gladness; may they always say, “Exalted be the LORD who delights in His servant’s well-being.”

title: Psalms 35:28
content: 28 Then my tongue will proclaim Your righteousness and Your praises all day long.

title: Psalms 36:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David, the servant of the LORD.

title: Psalms 36:1
content: 1 An oracle is in my heart regarding the transgression of the wicked man: There is no fear of God before his eyes.

title: Psalms 36:2
content: 2 For his eyes are too full of conceit to detect or hate his own sin.

title: Psalms 36:3
content: 3 The words of his mouth are wicked and deceitful; he has ceased to be wise and well-doing.

title: Psalms 36:4
content: 4 Even on his bed he plots wickedness; he sets himself on a path that is not good; he fails to reject evil.

title: Psalms 36:5
content: 5 Your loving devotion, O LORD, reaches to the heavens, Your faithfulness to the clouds.

title: Psalms 36:6
content: 6 Your righteousness is like the highest mountains; Your judgments are like the deepest sea. O LORD, You preserve man and beast.

title: Psalms 36:7
content: 7 How precious is Your loving devotion, O God, that the children of men take refuge in the shadow of Your wings!

title: Psalms 36:8
content: 8 They feast on the abundance of Your house, and You give them drink from Your river of delights.

title: Psalms 36:9
content: 9 For with You is the fountain of life; in Your light we see light.

title: Psalms 36:10
content: 10 Extend Your loving devotion to those who know You, and Your righteousness to the upright in heart.

title: Psalms 36:11
content: 11 Let not the foot of the proud come against me, nor the hand of the wicked drive me away.

title: Psalms 36:12
content: 12 There the evildoers lie fallen, thrown down and unable to rise.

title: Psalms 37:0
content: 0 Of David.

title: Psalms 37:1
content: 1 Do not fret over those who do evil; do not envy those who do wrong.

title: Psalms 37:2
content: 2 For they wither quickly like grass and wilt like tender plants.

title: Psalms 37:3
content: 3 Trust in the LORD and do good; dwell in the land and cultivate faithfulness.

title: Psalms 37:4
content: 4 Delight yourself in the LORD, and He will give you the desires of your heart.

title: Psalms 37:5
content: 5 Commit your way to the LORD; trust in Him, and He will do it.

title: Psalms 37:6
content: 6 He will bring forth your righteousness like the dawn, your justice like the noonday sun.

title: Psalms 37:7
content: 7 Be still before the LORD and wait patiently for Him; do not fret when men prosper in their ways, when they carry out wicked schemes.

title: Psalms 37:8
content: 8 Refrain from anger and abandon wrath; do not fret—it can only bring harm.

title: Psalms 37:9
content: 9 For the evildoers will be cut off, but those who hope in the LORD will inherit the land.

title: Psalms 37:10
content: 10 Yet a little while, and the wicked will be no more; though you look for them, they will not be found.

title: Psalms 37:11
content: 11 But the meek will inherit the land and delight in abundant prosperity.

title: Psalms 37:12
content: 12 The wicked scheme against the righteous and gnash their teeth at them,

title: Psalms 37:13
content: 13 but the Lord laughs, seeing that their day is coming.

title: Psalms 37:14
content: 14 The wicked have drawn the sword and bent the bow to bring down the poor and needy, to slay those whose ways are upright.

title: Psalms 37:15
content: 15 But their swords will pierce their own hearts, and their bows will be broken.

title: Psalms 37:16
content: 16 Better is the little of the righteous than the abundance of many who are wicked.

title: Psalms 37:17
content: 17 For the arms of the wicked will be broken, but the LORD upholds the righteous.

title: Psalms 37:18
content: 18 The LORD knows the days of the blameless, and their inheritance will last forever.

title: Psalms 37:19
content: 19 In the time of evil they will not be ashamed, and in the days of famine they will be satisfied.

title: Psalms 37:20
content: 20 But the wicked and enemies of the LORD will perish like the glory of the fields. They will vanish; like smoke they will fade away.

title: Psalms 37:21
content: 21 The wicked borrow and do not repay, but the righteous are gracious and giving.

title: Psalms 37:22
content: 22 Surely those He blesses will inherit the land, but the cursed will be destroyed.

title: Psalms 37:23
content: 23 The steps of a man are ordered by the LORD who takes delight in his journey.

title: Psalms 37:24
content: 24 Though he falls, he will not be overwhelmed, for the LORD is holding his hand.

title: Psalms 37:25
content: 25 I once was young and now am old, yet never have I seen the righteous abandoned or their children begging for bread.

title: Psalms 37:26
content: 26 They are ever generous and quick to lend, and their children are a blessing.

title: Psalms 37:27
content: 27 Turn away from evil and do good, so that you will abide forever.

title: Psalms 37:28
content: 28 For the LORD loves justice and will not forsake His saints. They are preserved forever, but the offspring of the wicked will be cut off.

title: Psalms 37:29
content: 29 The righteous will inherit the land and dwell in it forever.

title: Psalms 37:30
content: 30 The mouth of the righteous man utters wisdom, and his tongue speaks justice.

title: Psalms 37:31
content: 31 The law of his God is in his heart; his steps do not falter.

title: Psalms 37:32
content: 32 Though the wicked lie in wait for the righteous, and seek to slay them,

title: Psalms 37:33
content: 33 the LORD will not leave them in their power or let them be condemned under judgment.

title: Psalms 37:34
content: 34 Wait for the LORD and keep His way, and He will raise you up to inherit the land. When the wicked are cut off, you will see it.

title: Psalms 37:35
content: 35 I have seen a wicked, ruthless man flourishing like a well-rooted native tree,

title: Psalms 37:36
content: 36 yet he passed away and was no more; though I searched, he could not be found.

title: Psalms 37:37
content: 37 Consider the blameless and observe the upright, for posterity awaits the man of peace.

title: Psalms 37:38
content: 38 But the transgressors will all be destroyed; the future of the wicked will be cut off.

title: Psalms 37:39
content: 39 The salvation of the righteous is from the LORD; He is their stronghold in time of trouble.

title: Psalms 37:40
content: 40 The LORD helps and delivers them; He rescues and saves them from the wicked, because they take refuge in Him.

title: Psalms 38:0
content: 0 A Psalm of David, for remembrance.

title: Psalms 38:1
content: 1 O LORD, do not rebuke me in Your anger or discipline me in Your wrath.

title: Psalms 38:2
content: 2 For Your arrows have pierced me deeply, and Your hand has pressed down on me.

title: Psalms 38:3
content: 3 There is no soundness in my body because of Your anger; there is no rest in my bones because of my sin.

title: Psalms 38:4
content: 4 For my iniquities have overwhelmed me; they are a burden too heavy to bear.

title: Psalms 38:5
content: 5 My wounds are foul and festering because of my sinful folly.

title: Psalms 38:6
content: 6 I am bent and brought low; all day long I go about mourning.

title: Psalms 38:7
content: 7 For my loins are full of burning pain, and no soundness remains in my body.

title: Psalms 38:8
content: 8 I am numb and badly crushed; I groan in anguish of heart.

title: Psalms 38:9
content: 9 O Lord, my every desire is before You; my groaning is not hidden from You.

title: Psalms 38:10
content: 10 My heart pounds, my strength fails, and even the light of my eyes has faded.

title: Psalms 38:11
content: 11 My beloved and friends shun my disease, and my kinsmen stand at a distance.

title: Psalms 38:12
content: 12 Those who seek my life lay snares; those who wish me harm speak destruction, plotting deceit all day long.

title: Psalms 38:13
content: 13 But like a deaf man, I do not hear; and like a mute man, I do not open my mouth.

title: Psalms 38:14
content: 14 I am like a man who cannot hear, whose mouth offers no reply.

title: Psalms 38:15
content: 15 I wait for You, O LORD; You will answer, O Lord my God.

title: Psalms 38:16
content: 16 For I said, “Let them not gloat over me—those who taunt me when my foot slips.”

title: Psalms 38:17
content: 17 For I am ready to fall, and my pain is ever with me.

title: Psalms 38:18
content: 18 Yes, I confess my iniquity; I am troubled by my sin.

title: Psalms 38:19
content: 19 Many are my enemies without cause, and many hate me without reason.

title: Psalms 38:20
content: 20 Those who repay my good with evil attack me for pursuing the good.

title: Psalms 38:21
content: 21 Do not forsake me, O LORD; be not far from me, O my God.

title: Psalms 38:22
content: 22 Come quickly to help me, O Lord my Savior.

title: Psalms 39:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. For Jeduthun. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 39:1
content: 1 I said, “I will watch my ways so that I will not sin with my tongue; I will guard my mouth with a muzzle as long as the wicked are present.”

title: Psalms 39:2
content: 2 I was speechless and still; I remained silent, even from speaking good, and my sorrow was stirred.

title: Psalms 39:3
content: 3 My heart grew hot within me; as I mused, the fire burned. Then I spoke with my tongue:

title: Psalms 39:4
content: 4 “Show me, O LORD, my end and the measure of my days. Let me know how fleeting my life is.

title: Psalms 39:5
content: 5 You, indeed, have made my days as handbreadths, and my lifetime as nothing before You. Truly each man at his best exists as but a breath. Selah

title: Psalms 39:6
content: 6 Surely every man goes about like a phantom; surely he bustles in vain; he heaps up riches not knowing who will haul them away.

title: Psalms 39:7
content: 7 And now, O Lord, for what do I wait? My hope is in You.

title: Psalms 39:8
content: 8 Deliver me from all my transgressions; do not make me the reproach of fools.

title: Psalms 39:9
content: 9 I have become mute; I do not open my mouth because of what You have done.

title: Psalms 39:10
content: 10 Remove Your scourge from me; I am perishing by the force of Your hand.

title: Psalms 39:11
content: 11 You discipline and correct a man for his iniquity, consuming like a moth what he holds dear; surely each man is but a vapor. Selah

title: Psalms 39:12
content: 12 Hear my prayer, O LORD, and give ear to my cry for help; do not be deaf to my weeping. For I am a foreigner dwelling with You, a stranger like all my fathers.

title: Psalms 39:13
content: 13 Turn Your gaze away from me, that I may again be cheered before I depart and am no more.”

title: Psalms 40:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 40:1
content: 1 I waited patiently for the LORD; He inclined to me and heard my cry.

title: Psalms 40:2
content: 2 He lifted me up from the pit of despair, out of the miry clay; He set my feet upon a rock, and made my footsteps firm.

title: Psalms 40:3
content: 3 He put a new song in my mouth, a hymn of praise to our God. Many will see and fear and put their trust in the LORD.

title: Psalms 40:4
content: 4 Blessed is the man who has made the LORD his trust, who has not turned to the proud, nor to those who lapse into falsehood.

title: Psalms 40:5
content: 5 Many, O LORD my God, are the wonders You have done, and the plans You have for us—none can compare to You—if I proclaim and declare them, they are more than I can count.

title: Psalms 40:6
content: 6 Sacrifice and offering You did not desire, but my ears You have opened. Burnt offerings and sin offerings You did not require.

title: Psalms 40:7
content: 7 Then I said, “Here I am, I have come—it is written about me in the scroll:

title: Psalms 40:8
content: 8 I delight to do Your will, O my God; Your law is within my heart.”

title: Psalms 40:9
content: 9 I proclaim righteousness in the great assembly; behold, I do not seal my lips, as You, O LORD, do know.

title: Psalms 40:10
content: 10 I have not covered up Your righteousness in my heart; I have declared Your faithfulness and salvation; I have not concealed Your loving devotion and faithfulness from the great assembly.

title: Psalms 40:11
content: 11 O LORD, do not withhold Your mercy from me; Your loving devotion and faithfulness will always guard me.

title: Psalms 40:12
content: 12 For evils without number surround me; my sins have overtaken me, so that I cannot see. They are more than the hairs of my head, and my heart has failed within me.

title: Psalms 40:13
content: 13 Be pleased, O LORD, to deliver me; hurry, O LORD, to help me.

title: Psalms 40:14
content: 14 May those who seek my life be ashamed and confounded; may those who wish me harm be repelled and humiliated.

title: Psalms 40:15
content: 15 May those who say to me, “Aha, aha!” be appalled at their own shame.

title: Psalms 40:16
content: 16 May all who seek You rejoice and be glad in You; may those who love Your salvation always say, “The LORD be magnified!”

title: Psalms 40:17
content: 17 But I am poor and needy; may the Lord think of me. You are my helper and deliverer; O my God, do not delay.

title: Psalms 41:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 41:1
content: 1 Blessed is the one who cares for the poor; the LORD will deliver him in the day of trouble.

title: Psalms 41:2
content: 2 The LORD will protect and preserve him; He will bless him in the land and refuse to give him over to the will of his foes.

title: Psalms 41:3
content: 3 The LORD will sustain him on his bed of illness and restore him from his bed of sickness.

title: Psalms 41:4
content: 4 I said, “O LORD, be gracious to me; heal me, for I have sinned against You.”

title: Psalms 41:5
content: 5 My enemies say with malice: “When will he die and be forgotten?”

title: Psalms 41:6
content: 6 My visitor speaks falsehood; he gathers slander in his heart; he goes out and spreads it abroad.

title: Psalms 41:7
content: 7 All who hate me whisper against me; they imagine the worst for me:

title: Psalms 41:8
content: 8 “A vile disease has been poured into him; he will never get up from where he lies!”

title: Psalms 41:9
content: 9 Even my close friend whom I trusted, the one who shared my bread, has lifted up his heel against me.

title: Psalms 41:10
content: 10 But You, O LORD, be gracious to me and raise me up, that I may repay them.

title: Psalms 41:11
content: 11 By this I know that You delight in me, for my enemy does not triumph over me.

title: Psalms 41:12
content: 12 In my integrity You uphold me and set me in Your presence forever.

title: Psalms 41:13
content: 13 Blessed be the LORD, the God of Israel, from everlasting to everlasting. Amen and Amen.

title: Psalms 42:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Maskil of the sons of Korah.

title: Psalms 42:1
content: 1 As the deer pants for streams of water, so my soul longs after You, O God.

title: Psalms 42:2
content: 2 My soul thirsts for God, the living God. When shall I come and appear in God’s presence?

title: Psalms 42:3
content: 3 My tears have been my food both day and night, while men ask me all day long, “Where is your God?”

title: Psalms 42:4
content: 4 These things come to mind as I pour out my soul: how I walked with the multitude, leading the festive procession to the house of God with shouts of joy and praise.

title: Psalms 42:5
content: 5 Why are you downcast, O my soul? Why the unease within me? Put your hope in God, for I will yet praise Him for the salvation of His presence.

title: Psalms 42:6
content: 6 O my God, my soul despairs within me. Therefore I remember You from the land of Jordan and the peaks of Hermon—even from Mount Mizar.

title: Psalms 42:7
content: 7 Deep calls to deep in the roar of Your waterfalls; all Your breakers and waves have rolled over me.

title: Psalms 42:8
content: 8 The LORD decrees His loving devotion by day, and at night His song is with me as a prayer to the God of my life.

title: Psalms 42:9
content: 9 I say to God my Rock, “Why have You forgotten me? Why must I walk in sorrow because of the enemy’s oppression?”

title: Psalms 42:10
content: 10 Like the crushing of my bones, my enemies taunt me, while they say to me all day long, “Where is your God?”

title: Psalms 42:11
content: 11 Why are you downcast, O my soul? Why the unease within me? Put your hope in God, for I will yet praise Him, my Savior and my God.

title: Psalms 43:1
content: 1 Vindicate me, O God, and plead my case against an ungodly nation; deliver me from deceitful and unjust men.

title: Psalms 43:2
content: 2 For You are the God of my refuge. Why have You rejected me? Why must I walk in sorrow because of the enemy’s oppression?

title: Psalms 43:3
content: 3 Send out Your light and Your truth; let them lead me. Let them bring me to Your holy mountain and to the place where You dwell.

title: Psalms 43:4
content: 4 Then I will go to the altar of God, to God, my greatest joy. I will praise You with the harp, O God, my God.

title: Psalms 43:5
content: 5 Why are you downcast, O my soul? Why the unease within me? Put your hope in God, for I will yet praise Him, my Savior and my God.

title: Psalms 44:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Maskil of the sons of Korah.

title: Psalms 44:1
content: 1 We have heard with our ears, O God; our fathers have told us the work You did in their days, in the days of old.

title: Psalms 44:2
content: 2 With Your hand You drove out the nations and planted our fathers there; You crushed the peoples and cast them out.

title: Psalms 44:3
content: 3 For it was not by their sword that they took the land; their arm did not bring them victory. It was by Your right hand, Your arm, and the light of Your face, because You favored them.

title: Psalms 44:4
content: 4 You are my King, O God, who ordains victories for Jacob.

title: Psalms 44:5
content: 5 Through You we repel our foes; through Your name we trample our enemies.

title: Psalms 44:6
content: 6 For I do not trust in my bow, nor does my sword save me.
