title: Psalms 44:7
content: 7 For You save us from our enemies; You put those who hate us to shame.

title: Psalms 44:8
content: 8 In God we have boasted all day long, and Your name we will praise forever. Selah

title: Psalms 44:9
content: 9 But You have rejected and humbled us; You no longer go forth with our armies.

title: Psalms 44:10
content: 10 You have made us retreat from the foe, and those who hate us have plundered us.

title: Psalms 44:11
content: 11 You have given us up as sheep to be devoured; You have scattered us among the nations.

title: Psalms 44:12
content: 12 You sell Your people for nothing; no profit do You gain from their sale.

title: Psalms 44:13
content: 13 You have made us a reproach to our neighbors, a mockery and derision to those around us.

title: Psalms 44:14
content: 14 You have made us a byword among the nations, a laughingstock among the peoples.

title: Psalms 44:15
content: 15 All day long my disgrace is before me, and shame has covered my face,

title: Psalms 44:16
content: 16 at the voice of the scorner and reviler, because of the enemy, bent on revenge.

title: Psalms 44:17
content: 17 All this has come upon us, though we have not forgotten You or betrayed Your covenant.

title: Psalms 44:18
content: 18 Our hearts have not turned back; our steps have not strayed from Your path.

title: Psalms 44:19
content: 19 But You have crushed us in the lair of jackals; You have covered us with deepest darkness.

title: Psalms 44:20
content: 20 If we had forgotten the name of our God or spread out our hands to a foreign god,

title: Psalms 44:21
content: 21 would not God have discovered, since He knows the secrets of the heart?

title: Psalms 44:22
content: 22 Yet for Your sake we face death all day long; we are considered as sheep to be slaughtered.

title: Psalms 44:23
content: 23 Wake up, O Lord! Why are You sleeping? Arise! Do not reject us forever.

title: Psalms 44:24
content: 24 Why do You hide Your face and forget our affliction and oppression?

title: Psalms 44:25
content: 25 For our soul has sunk to the dust; our bodies cling to the earth.

title: Psalms 44:26
content: 26 Rise up; be our help! Redeem us on account of Your loving devotion.

title: Psalms 45:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. To the tune of “The Lilies.” A Maskil of the sons of Korah. A love song.

title: Psalms 45:1
content: 1 My heart is stirred by a noble theme as I recite my verses to the king; my tongue is the pen of a skillful writer.

title: Psalms 45:2
content: 2 You are the most handsome of men; grace has anointed your lips; therefore God has blessed you forever.

title: Psalms 45:3
content: 3 Strap your sword at your side, O mighty warrior; appear in your majesty and splendor.

title: Psalms 45:4
content: 4 In your splendor ride forth in victory on behalf of truth and humility and justice; may your right hand show your awesome deeds.

title: Psalms 45:5
content: 5 Your arrows pierce the hearts of the king’s foes; the nations fall beneath your feet.

title: Psalms 45:6
content: 6 Your throne, O God, endures forever and ever, and justice is the scepter of Your kingdom.

title: Psalms 45:7
content: 7 You have loved righteousness and hated wickedness; therefore God, your God, has anointed you above your companions with the oil of joy.

title: Psalms 45:8
content: 8 All your garments are fragrant with myrrh and aloes and cassia; from palaces of ivory the harps make you glad.

title: Psalms 45:9
content: 9 The daughters of kings are among your honored women; the queen stands at your right hand, adorned with the gold of Ophir.

title: Psalms 45:10
content: 10 Listen, O daughter! Consider and incline your ear: Forget your people and your father’s house,

title: Psalms 45:11
content: 11 and the king will desire your beauty; bow to him, for he is your lord.

title: Psalms 45:12
content: 12 The Daughter of Tyre will come with a gift; men of wealth will seek your favor.

title: Psalms 45:13
content: 13 All glorious is the princess in her chamber; her gown is embroidered with gold.

title: Psalms 45:14
content: 14 In colorful garments she is led to the king; her virgin companions are brought before you.

title: Psalms 45:15
content: 15 They are led in with joy and gladness; they enter the palace of the king.

title: Psalms 45:16
content: 16 Your sons will succeed your fathers; you will make them princes throughout the land.

title: Psalms 45:17
content: 17 I will commemorate your name through all generations; therefore the nations will praise you forever and ever.

title: Psalms 46:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. Of the sons of Korah. According to Alamoth. A song.

title: Psalms 46:1
content: 1 God is our refuge and strength, an ever-present help in times of trouble.

title: Psalms 46:2
content: 2 Therefore we will not fear, though the earth is transformed and the mountains are toppled into the depths of the seas,

title: Psalms 46:3
content: 3 though their waters roar and foam and the mountains quake in the surge. Selah

title: Psalms 46:4
content: 4 There is a river whose streams delight the city of God, the holy place where the Most High dwells.

title: Psalms 46:5
content: 5 God is within her; she will not be moved. God will help her when morning dawns.

title: Psalms 46:6
content: 6 Nations rage, kingdoms crumble; the earth melts when He lifts His voice.

title: Psalms 46:7
content: 7 The LORD of Hosts is with us; the God of Jacob is our fortress. Selah

title: Psalms 46:8
content: 8 Come, see the works of the LORD, who brings devastation upon the earth.

title: Psalms 46:9
content: 9 He makes wars to cease throughout the earth; He breaks the bow and shatters the spear; He burns the shields in the fire.

title: Psalms 46:10
content: 10 “Be still and know that I am God; I will be exalted among the nations, I will be exalted over the earth.”

title: Psalms 46:11
content: 11 The LORD of Hosts is with us; the God of Jacob is our fortress. Selah

title: Psalms 47:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of the sons of Korah.

title: Psalms 47:1
content: 1 Clap your hands, all you peoples; shout unto God with a voice of triumph.

title: Psalms 47:2
content: 2 How awesome is the LORD Most High, the great King over all the earth!

title: Psalms 47:3
content: 3 He subdues nations beneath us, and peoples under our feet.

title: Psalms 47:4
content: 4 He chooses our inheritance for us, the pride of Jacob, whom He loves. Selah

title: Psalms 47:5
content: 5 God has ascended amid shouts of joy, the LORD with the sound of the horn.

title: Psalms 47:6
content: 6 Sing praises to God, sing praises; sing praises to our King, sing praises!

title: Psalms 47:7
content: 7 For God is King of all the earth; sing to Him a psalm of praise.

title: Psalms 47:8
content: 8 God reigns over the nations; God is seated on His holy throne.

title: Psalms 47:9
content: 9 The nobles of the nations have assembled as the people of the God of Abraham; for the shields of the earth belong to God; He is highly exalted.

title: Psalms 48:0
content: 0 A song. A Psalm of the sons of Korah.

title: Psalms 48:1
content: 1 Great is the LORD, and greatly to be praised in the city of our God, His holy mountain.

title: Psalms 48:2
content: 2 Beautiful in loftiness, the joy of all the earth, like the peaks of Zaphon is Mount Zion, the city of the great King.

title: Psalms 48:3
content: 3 God is in her citadels; He has shown Himself to be a fortress.

title: Psalms 48:4
content: 4 For behold, the kings assembled; they all advanced together.

title: Psalms 48:5
content: 5 They saw and were astounded; they fled in terror.

title: Psalms 48:6
content: 6 Trembling seized them there, anguish like a woman in labor.

title: Psalms 48:7
content: 7 With a wind from the east You wrecked the ships of Tarshish.

title: Psalms 48:8
content: 8 As we have heard, so we have seen in the city of the LORD of Hosts, in the city of our God: God will establish her forever. Selah

title: Psalms 48:9
content: 9 Within Your temple, O God, we contemplate Your loving devotion.

title: Psalms 48:10
content: 10 Your name, O God, like Your praise, reaches to the ends of the earth; Your right hand is full of righteousness.

title: Psalms 48:11
content: 11 Mount Zion is glad, the daughters of Judah rejoice, on account of Your judgments.

title: Psalms 48:12
content: 12 March around Zion, encircle her, count her towers,

title: Psalms 48:13
content: 13 consider her ramparts, tour her citadels, that you may tell the next generation.

title: Psalms 48:14
content: 14 For this God is our God forever and ever; He will be our guide even till death.

title: Psalms 49:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of the sons of Korah.

title: Psalms 49:1
content: 1 Hear this, all you peoples; listen, all inhabitants of the world,

title: Psalms 49:2
content: 2 both low and high, rich and poor alike.

title: Psalms 49:3
content: 3 My mouth will impart wisdom, and the meditation of my heart will bring understanding.

title: Psalms 49:4
content: 4 I will incline my ear to a proverb; I will express my riddle with the harp:

title: Psalms 49:5
content: 5 Why should I fear in times of trouble, when wicked usurpers surround me?

title: Psalms 49:6
content: 6 They trust in their wealth and boast in their great riches.

title: Psalms 49:7
content: 7 No man can possibly redeem his brother or pay his ransom to God.

title: Psalms 49:8
content: 8 For the redemption of his soul is costly, and never can payment suffice,

title: Psalms 49:9
content: 9 that he should live on forever and not see decay.

title: Psalms 49:10
content: 10 For it is clear that wise men die, and the foolish and the senseless both perish and leave their wealth to others.

title: Psalms 49:11
content: 11 Their graves are their eternal homes—their dwellings for endless generations—even though their lands were their namesakes.

title: Psalms 49:12
content: 12 But a man, despite his wealth, cannot endure; he is like the beasts that perish.

title: Psalms 49:13
content: 13 This is the fate of the foolish and their followers who endorse their sayings. Selah

title: Psalms 49:14
content: 14 Like sheep they are destined for Sheol. Death will be their shepherd. The upright will rule them in the morning, and their form will decay in Sheol, far from their lofty abode.

title: Psalms 49:15
content: 15 But God will redeem my life from Sheol, for He will surely take me to Himself. Selah

title: Psalms 49:16
content: 16 Do not be afraid when a man grows rich, when the splendor of his house increases.

title: Psalms 49:17
content: 17 For when he dies, he will carry nothing away; his abundance will not follow him down.

title: Psalms 49:18
content: 18 Though in his lifetime he blesses his soul—and men praise you when you prosper—

title: Psalms 49:19
content: 19 he will join the generation of his fathers, who will never see the light of day.

title: Psalms 49:20
content: 20 A man who has riches without understanding is like the beasts that perish.

title: Psalms 50:0
content: 0 A Psalm of Asaph.

title: Psalms 50:1
content: 1 The Mighty One, God the LORD, speaks and summons the earth from where the sun rises to where it sets.

title: Psalms 50:2
content: 2 From Zion, perfect in beauty, God shines forth.

title: Psalms 50:3
content: 3 Our God approaches and will not be silent! Consuming fire precedes Him, and a tempest rages around Him.

title: Psalms 50:4
content: 4 He summons the heavens above, and the earth, that He may judge His people:

title: Psalms 50:5
content: 5 “Gather to Me My saints, who made a covenant with Me by sacrifice.”

title: Psalms 50:6
content: 6 And the heavens proclaim His righteousness, for God Himself is Judge. Selah

title: Psalms 50:7
content: 7 “Hear, O My people, and I will speak, O Israel, and I will testify against you: I am God, your God.

title: Psalms 50:8
content: 8 I do not rebuke you for your sacrifices, and your burnt offerings are ever before Me.

title: Psalms 50:9
content: 9 I have no need for a bull from your stall or goats from your pens,

title: Psalms 50:10
content: 10 for every beast of the forest is Mine—the cattle on a thousand hills.

title: Psalms 50:11
content: 11 I know every bird in the mountains, and the creatures of the field are Mine.

title: Psalms 50:12
content: 12 If I were hungry, I would not tell you, for the world is Mine, and the fullness thereof.

title: Psalms 50:13
content: 13 Do I eat the flesh of bulls, or drink the blood of goats?

title: Psalms 50:14
content: 14 Sacrifice a thank offering to God, and fulfill your vows to the Most High.

title: Psalms 50:15
content: 15 Call upon Me in the day of trouble; I will deliver you, and you will honor Me.”

title: Psalms 50:16
content: 16 To the wicked, however, God says, “What right have you to recite My statutes and to bear My covenant on your lips?

title: Psalms 50:17
content: 17 For you hate My instruction and cast My words behind you.

title: Psalms 50:18
content: 18 When you see a thief, you befriend him, and throw in your lot with adulterers.

title: Psalms 50:19
content: 19 You unleash your mouth for evil and harness your tongue to deceit.

title: Psalms 50:20
content: 20 You sit and malign your brother; you slander your own mother’s son.

title: Psalms 50:21
content: 21 You have done these things, and I kept silent; you thought I was just like you. But now I rebuke you and accuse you to your face.

title: Psalms 50:22
content: 22 Now consider this, you who forget God, lest I tear you to pieces, with no one to rescue you:

title: Psalms 50:23
content: 23 He who sacrifices a thank offering honors Me, and to him who rightly orders his way, I will show the salvation of God.”

title: Psalms 51:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David. When Nathan the prophet came to him after his adultery with Bathsheba.

title: Psalms 51:1
content: 1 Have mercy on me, O God, according to Your loving devotion; according to Your great compassion, blot out my transgressions.

title: Psalms 51:2
content: 2 Wash me clean of my iniquity and cleanse me from my sin.

title: Psalms 51:3
content: 3 For I know my transgressions, and my sin is always before me.

title: Psalms 51:4
content: 4 Against You, You only, have I sinned and done what is evil in Your sight, so that You may be proved right when You speak and blameless when You judge.

title: Psalms 51:5
content: 5 Surely I was brought forth in iniquity; I was sinful when my mother conceived me.

title: Psalms 51:6
content: 6 Surely You desire truth in the inmost being; You teach me wisdom in the inmost place.

title: Psalms 51:7
content: 7 Purify me with hyssop, and I will be clean; wash me, and I will be whiter than snow.

title: Psalms 51:8
content: 8 Let me hear joy and gladness; let the bones You have crushed rejoice.

title: Psalms 51:9
content: 9 Hide Your face from my sins and blot out all my iniquities.

title: Psalms 51:10
content: 10 Create in me a clean heart, O God, and renew a right spirit within me.

title: Psalms 51:11
content: 11 Cast me not away from Your presence; take not Your Holy Spirit from me.

title: Psalms 51:12
content: 12 Restore to me the joy of Your salvation, and sustain me with a willing spirit.

title: Psalms 51:13
content: 13 Then I will teach transgressors Your ways, and sinners will return to You.

title: Psalms 51:14
content: 14 Deliver me from bloodguilt, O God, the God of my salvation, and my tongue will sing of Your righteousness.

title: Psalms 51:15
content: 15 O Lord, open my lips, and my mouth will declare Your praise.

title: Psalms 51:16
content: 16 For You do not delight in sacrifice, or I would bring it; You take no pleasure in burnt offerings.

title: Psalms 51:17
content: 17 The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit; a broken and a contrite heart, O God, You will not despise.

title: Psalms 51:18
content: 18 In Your good pleasure, cause Zion to prosper; build up the walls of Jerusalem.

title: Psalms 51:19
content: 19 Then You will delight in righteous sacrifices, in whole burnt offerings; then bulls will be offered on Your altar.

title: Psalms 52:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Maskil of David. After Doeg the Edomite went to Saul and told him, “David has gone to the house of Ahimelech.”

title: Psalms 52:1
content: 1 Why do you boast of evil, O mighty man? The loving devotion of God endures all day long.

title: Psalms 52:2
content: 2 Your tongue devises destruction like a sharpened razor, O worker of deceit.

title: Psalms 52:3
content: 3 You love evil more than good, falsehood more than speaking truth. Selah

title: Psalms 52:4
content: 4 You love every word that devours, O deceitful tongue.

title: Psalms 52:5
content: 5 Surely God will bring you down to everlasting ruin; He will snatch you up and tear you away from your tent; He will uproot you from the land of the living. Selah

title: Psalms 52:6
content: 6 The righteous will see and fear; they will mock the evildoer, saying,

title: Psalms 52:7
content: 7 “Look at the man who did not make God his refuge, but trusted in the abundance of his wealth and strengthened himself by destruction.”

title: Psalms 52:8
content: 8 But I am like an olive tree flourishing in the house of God; I trust in the loving devotion of God forever and ever.

title: Psalms 52:9
content: 9 I will praise You forever, because You have done it. I will wait on Your name—for it is good—in the presence of Your saints.

title: Psalms 53:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. According to Mahalath. A Maskil of David.

title: Psalms 53:1
content: 1 The fool says in his heart, “There is no God.” They are corrupt; their ways are vile. There is no one who does good.

title: Psalms 53:2
content: 2 God looks down from heaven upon the sons of men to see if any understand, if any seek God.

title: Psalms 53:3
content: 3 All have turned away, they have together become corrupt; there is no one who does good, not even one.

title: Psalms 53:4
content: 4 Will the workers of iniquity never learn? They devour my people like bread; they refuse to call upon God.

title: Psalms 53:5
content: 5 There they are, overwhelmed with dread, where there was nothing to fear. For God has scattered the bones of those who besieged you. You put them to shame, for God has despised them.

title: Psalms 53:6
content: 6 Oh, that the salvation of Israel would come from Zion! When God restores His captive people, let Jacob rejoice, let Israel be glad!

title: Psalms 54:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. With stringed instruments. A Maskil of David. When the Ziphites went to Saul and said, “Is David not hiding among us?”

title: Psalms 54:1
content: 1 Save me, O God, by Your name, and vindicate me by Your might!

title: Psalms 54:2
content: 2 Hear my prayer, O God; listen to the words of my mouth.

title: Psalms 54:3
content: 3 For strangers rise up against me, and ruthless men seek my life—men with no regard for God. Selah

title: Psalms 54:4
content: 4 Surely God is my helper; the Lord is the sustainer of my soul.

title: Psalms 54:5
content: 5 He will reward my enemies with evil. In Your faithfulness, destroy them.

title: Psalms 54:6
content: 6 Freely I will sacrifice to You; I will praise Your name, O LORD, for it is good.

title: Psalms 54:7
content: 7 For He has delivered me from every trouble, and my eyes have looked in triumph on my foes.

title: Psalms 55:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. With stringed instruments. A Maskil of David.

title: Psalms 55:1
content: 1 Listen to my prayer, O God, and do not ignore my plea.

title: Psalms 55:2
content: 2 Attend to me and answer me. I am restless in my complaint, and distraught

title: Psalms 55:3
content: 3 at the voice of the enemy, at the pressure of the wicked. For they bring down disaster upon me and resent me in their anger.

title: Psalms 55:4
content: 4 My heart pounds within me, and the terrors of death assail me.

title: Psalms 55:5
content: 5 Fear and trembling grip me, and horror has overwhelmed me.

title: Psalms 55:6
content: 6 I said, “Oh, that I had wings like a dove! I would fly away and find rest.

title: Psalms 55:7
content: 7 How far away I would flee! In the wilderness I would remain. Selah

title: Psalms 55:8
content: 8 I would hurry to my shelter, far from this raging tempest.”

title: Psalms 55:9
content: 9 O Lord, confuse and confound their speech, for I see violence and strife in the city.

title: Psalms 55:10
content: 10 Day and night they encircle the walls, while malice and trouble lie within.

title: Psalms 55:11
content: 11 Destruction is within; oppression and deceit never leave the streets.

title: Psalms 55:12
content: 12 For it is not an enemy who insults me; that I could endure. It is not a foe who rises against me; from him I could hide.

title: Psalms 55:13
content: 13 But it is you, a man like myself, my companion and close friend.

title: Psalms 55:14
content: 14 We shared sweet fellowship together; we walked with the crowd into the house of God.

title: Psalms 55:15
content: 15 Let death seize them by surprise; let them go down to Sheol alive, for evil is with them in their homes.

title: Psalms 55:16
content: 16 But I call to God, and the LORD saves me.

title: Psalms 55:17
content: 17 Morning, noon, and night, I cry out in distress, and He hears my voice.

title: Psalms 55:18
content: 18 He redeems my soul in peace from the battle waged against me, even though many oppose me.

title: Psalms 55:19
content: 19 God will hear and humiliate them—the One enthroned for the ages—Selah because they do not change and they have no fear of God.

title: Psalms 55:20
content: 20 My companion attacks his friends; he violates his covenant.

title: Psalms 55:21
content: 21 His speech is smooth as butter, but war is in his heart. His words are softer than oil, yet they are swords unsheathed.

title: Psalms 55:22
content: 22 Cast your burden upon the LORD and He will sustain you; He will never let the righteous be shaken.

title: Psalms 55:23
content: 23 But You, O God, will bring them down to the Pit of destruction; men of bloodshed and deceit will not live out half their days. But I will trust in You.

title: Psalms 56:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. To the tune of “A Dove on Distant Oaks.” A Miktam of David, when the Philistines seized him in Gath.

title: Psalms 56:1
content: 1 Be merciful to me, O God, for men are hounding me; all day they press their attack.

title: Psalms 56:2
content: 2 My enemies pursue me all day long, for many proudly assail me.

title: Psalms 56:3
content: 3 When I am afraid, I put my trust in You.

title: Psalms 56:4
content: 4 In God, whose word I praise—in God I trust. I will not be afraid. What can man do to me?

title: Psalms 56:5
content: 5 All day long they twist my words; all their thoughts are on my demise.

title: Psalms 56:6
content: 6 They conspire, they lurk, they watch my steps while they wait to take my life.

title: Psalms 56:7
content: 7 In spite of such sin, will they escape? In Your anger, O God, cast down the nations.

title: Psalms 56:8
content: 8 You have taken account of my wanderings. Put my tears in Your bottle—are they not in Your book?

title: Psalms 56:9
content: 9 Then my enemies will retreat on the day I cry for help. By this I will know that God is on my side.

title: Psalms 56:10
content: 10 In God, whose word I praise, in the LORD, whose word I praise,

title: Psalms 56:11
content: 11 in God I trust; I will not be afraid. What can man do to me?

title: Psalms 56:12
content: 12 Your vows are upon me, O God; I will render thank offerings to You.

title: Psalms 56:13
content: 13 For You have delivered my soul from death, and my feet from stumbling, that I may walk before God in the light of life.

title: Psalms 57:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. To the tune of “Do Not Destroy.” A Miktam of David, when he fled from Saul into the cave.

title: Psalms 57:1
content: 1 Have mercy on me, O God, have mercy, for in You my soul takes refuge. In the shadow of Your wings I will take shelter until the danger has passed.

title: Psalms 57:2
content: 2 I cry out to God Most High, to God who fulfills His purpose for me.

title: Psalms 57:3
content: 3 He reaches down from heaven and saves me; He rebukes those who trample me. Selah God sends forth His loving devotion and His truth.

title: Psalms 57:4
content: 4 My soul is among the lions; I lie down with ravenous beasts—with men whose teeth are spears and arrows, whose tongues are sharp swords.

title: Psalms 57:5
content: 5 Be exalted, O God, above the heavens; may Your glory cover all the earth.

title: Psalms 57:6
content: 6 They spread a net for my feet; my soul was despondent. They dug a pit before me, but they themselves have fallen into it! Selah

title: Psalms 57:7
content: 7 My heart is steadfast, O God, my heart is steadfast. I will sing and make music.

title: Psalms 57:8
content: 8 Awake, my glory! Awake, O harp and lyre! I will awaken the dawn.

title: Psalms 57:9
content: 9 I will praise You, O Lord, among the nations; I will sing Your praises among the peoples.

title: Psalms 57:10
content: 10 For Your loving devotion reaches to the heavens, and Your faithfulness to the clouds.

title: Psalms 57:11
content: 11 Be exalted, O God, above the heavens; may Your glory cover all the earth.

title: Psalms 58:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. To the tune of “Do Not Destroy.” A Miktam of David.

title: Psalms 58:1
content: 1 Do you indeed speak justly, O rulers? Do you judge uprightly, O sons of men?

title: Psalms 58:2
content: 2 No, in your hearts you devise injustice; with your hands you mete out violence on the earth.

title: Psalms 58:3
content: 3 The wicked are estranged from the womb; the liars go astray from birth.

title: Psalms 58:4
content: 4 Their venom is like the venom of a snake, like a cobra that shuts its ears,

title: Psalms 58:5
content: 5 refusing to hear the tune of the charmer who skillfully weaves his spell.

title: Psalms 58:6
content: 6 O God, shatter their teeth in their mouths; O LORD, tear out the fangs of the lions.

title: Psalms 58:7
content: 7 May they vanish like water that runs off; when they draw the bow, may their arrows be blunted.

title: Psalms 58:8
content: 8 Like a slug that dissolves in its slime, like a woman’s stillborn child, may they never see the sun.

title: Psalms 58:9
content: 9 Before your pots can feel the burning thorns—whether green or dry—He will sweep them away.

title: Psalms 58:10
content: 10 The righteous will rejoice when they see they are avenged; they will wash their feet in the blood of the wicked.

title: Psalms 58:11
content: 11 Then men will say, “There is surely a reward for the righteous! There is surely a God who judges the earth!”

title: Psalms 59:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. To the tune of “Do Not Destroy.” A Miktam of David, when Saul sent men to watch David’s house in order to kill him.

title: Psalms 59:1
content: 1 Deliver me from my enemies, O my God; protect me from those who rise against me.

title: Psalms 59:2
content: 2 Deliver me from workers of iniquity, and save me from men of bloodshed.

title: Psalms 59:3
content: 3 See how they lie in wait for me. Fierce men conspire against me for no transgression or sin of my own, O LORD.

title: Psalms 59:4
content: 4 For no fault of my own, they move swiftly to attack me. Arise to help me, and take notice.

title: Psalms 59:5
content: 5 O LORD God of Hosts, the God of Israel, rouse Yourself to punish all the nations; show no mercy to the wicked traitors. Selah

title: Psalms 59:6
content: 6 They return in the evening, snarling like dogs and prowling around the city.

title: Psalms 59:7
content: 7 See what they spew from their mouths—sharp words from their lips: “For who can hear us?”

title: Psalms 59:8
content: 8 But You, O LORD, laugh at them; You scoff at all the nations.

title: Psalms 59:9
content: 9 I will keep watch for You, O my strength, because You, O God, are my fortress.

title: Psalms 59:10
content: 10 My God of loving devotion will come to meet me; God will let me stare down my foes.

title: Psalms 59:11
content: 11 Do not kill them, or my people will forget. Scatter them by Your power, and bring them down, O Lord, our shield.

title: Psalms 59:12
content: 12 By the sins of their mouths and the words of their lips, let them be trapped in their pride, in the curses and lies they utter.

title: Psalms 59:13
content: 13 Consume them in wrath; consume them till they are no more, so it may be known to the ends of the earth that God rules over Jacob. Selah

title: Psalms 59:14
content: 14 They return in the evening, snarling like dogs and prowling around the city.

title: Psalms 59:15
content: 15 They scavenge for food, and growl if they are not satisfied.

title: Psalms 59:16
content: 16 But I will sing of Your strength and proclaim Your loving devotion in the morning. For You are my fortress, my refuge in times of trouble.

title: Psalms 59:17
content: 17 To You, O my strength, I sing praises, for You, O God, are my fortress, my God of loving devotion.

title: Psalms 60:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. To the tune of “The Lily of the Covenant.” A Miktam of David for instruction. When he fought Aram-naharaim and Aram-zobah, and Joab returned and struck down 12,000 Edomites in the Valley of Salt.

title: Psalms 60:1
content: 1 You have rejected us, O God; You have broken us; You have been angry; restore us!

title: Psalms 60:2
content: 2 You have shaken the land and torn it open. Heal its fractures, for it is quaking.

title: Psalms 60:3
content: 3 You have shown Your people hardship; we are staggered from the wine You made us drink.

title: Psalms 60:4
content: 4 You have raised a banner for those who fear You, that they may flee the bow. Selah

title: Psalms 60:5
content: 5 Respond and save us with Your right hand, that Your beloved may be delivered.

title: Psalms 60:6
content: 6 God has spoken from His sanctuary: “I will triumph! I will parcel out Shechem and apportion the Valley of Succoth.

title: Psalms 60:7
content: 7 Gilead is Mine, and Manasseh is Mine; Ephraim is My helmet, Judah is My scepter.

title: Psalms 60:8
content: 8 Moab is My washbasin; upon Edom I toss My sandal; over Philistia I shout in triumph.”

title: Psalms 60:9
content: 9 Who will bring me to the fortified city? Who will lead me to Edom?

title: Psalms 60:10
content: 10 Have You not rejected us, O God? Will You no longer march out, O God, with our armies?

title: Psalms 60:11
content: 11 Give us aid against the enemy, for the help of man is worthless.

title: Psalms 60:12
content: 12 With God we will perform with valor, and He will trample our enemies.

title: Psalms 61:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. With stringed instruments. Of David.

title: Psalms 61:1
content: 1 Hear my cry, O God; attend to my prayer.

title: Psalms 61:2
content: 2 From the ends of the earth I call out to You whenever my heart is faint. Lead me to the rock that is higher than I.

title: Psalms 61:3
content: 3 For You have been my refuge, a tower of strength against the enemy.

title: Psalms 61:4
content: 4 Let me dwell in Your tent forever and take refuge in the shelter of Your wings. Selah

title: Psalms 61:5
content: 5 For You have heard my vows, O God; You have given me the inheritance reserved for those who fear Your name.

title: Psalms 61:6
content: 6 Increase the days of the king’s life; may his years span many generations.

title: Psalms 61:7
content: 7 May he sit enthroned in God’s presence forever; appoint Your loving devotion and Your faithfulness to guard him.

title: Psalms 61:8
content: 8 Then I will ever sing praise to Your name and fulfill my vows day by day.

title: Psalms 62:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. According to Jeduthun. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 62:1
content: 1 In God alone my soul finds rest; my salvation comes from Him.

title: Psalms 62:2
content: 2 He alone is my rock and my salvation. He is my fortress; I will never be shaken.

title: Psalms 62:3
content: 3 How long will you threaten a man? Will all of you throw him down like a leaning wall or a tottering fence?

title: Psalms 62:4
content: 4 They fully intend to cast him down from his lofty perch; they delight in lies; with their mouths they bless, but inwardly they curse. Selah

title: Psalms 62:5
content: 5 Rest in God alone, O my soul, for my hope comes from Him.

title: Psalms 62:6
content: 6 He alone is my rock and my salvation; He is my fortress; I will not be shaken.

title: Psalms 62:7
content: 7 My salvation and my honor rest on God, my strong rock; my refuge is in God.

title: Psalms 62:8
content: 8 Trust in Him at all times, O people; pour out your hearts before Him. God is our refuge. Selah

title: Psalms 62:9
content: 9 Lowborn men are but a vapor; the exalted are but a lie. Weighed on the scale, they go up; together they are but a vapor.

title: Psalms 62:10
content: 10 Place no trust in extortion or false hope in stolen goods. If your riches increase, do not set your heart upon them.

title: Psalms 62:11
content: 11 God has spoken once; I have heard this twice: that power belongs to God,

title: Psalms 62:12
content: 12 and loving devotion to You, O Lord. For You will repay each man according to his deeds.

title: Psalms 63:0
content: 0 A Psalm of David, when he was in the Wilderness of Judah.

title: Psalms 63:1
content: 1 O God, You are my God. Earnestly I seek You; my soul thirsts for You. My body yearns for You in a dry and weary land without water.

title: Psalms 63:2
content: 2 So I have seen You in the sanctuary and beheld Your power and glory.

title: Psalms 63:3
content: 3 Because Your loving devotion is better than life, my lips will glorify You.

title: Psalms 63:4
content: 4 So I will bless You as long as I live; in Your name I will lift my hands.

title: Psalms 63:5
content: 5 My soul is satisfied as with the richest of foods; with joyful lips my mouth will praise You.

title: Psalms 63:6
content: 6 When I remember You on my bed, I think of You through the watches of the night.

title: Psalms 63:7
content: 7 For You are my help; I will sing for joy in the shadow of Your wings.

title: Psalms 63:8
content: 8 My soul clings to You; Your right hand upholds me.

title: Psalms 63:9
content: 9 But those who seek my life to destroy it will go into the depths of the earth.

title: Psalms 63:10
content: 10 They will fall to the power of the sword; they will become a portion for foxes.

title: Psalms 63:11
content: 11 But the king will rejoice in God; all who swear by Him will exult, for the mouths of liars will be shut.

title: Psalms 64:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 64:1
content: 1 Hear, O God, my voice of complaint; preserve my life from dread of the enemy.

title: Psalms 64:2
content: 2 Hide me from the scheming of the wicked, from the mob of workers of iniquity,

title: Psalms 64:3
content: 3 who sharpen their tongues like swords and aim their bitter words like arrows,

title: Psalms 64:4
content: 4 ambushing the innocent in seclusion, shooting suddenly, without fear.

title: Psalms 64:5
content: 5 They hold fast to their evil purpose; they speak of hiding their snares. “Who will see them?” they say.

title: Psalms 64:6
content: 6 They devise injustice and say, “We have perfected a secret plan.” For the inner man and the heart are mysterious.

title: Psalms 64:7
content: 7 But God will shoot them with arrows; suddenly they will be wounded.

title: Psalms 64:8
content: 8 They will be made to stumble, their own tongues turned against them. All who see will shake their heads.

title: Psalms 64:9
content: 9 Then all mankind will fear and proclaim the work of God; so they will ponder what He has done.

title: Psalms 64:10
content: 10 Let the righteous rejoice in the LORD and take refuge in Him; let all the upright in heart exult.

title: Psalms 65:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David. A song.

title: Psalms 65:1
content: 1 Praise awaits You, O God, in Zion; to You our vows will be fulfilled.

title: Psalms 65:2
content: 2 O You who listen to prayer, all people will come to You.

title: Psalms 65:3
content: 3 When iniquities prevail against me, You atone for our transgressions.

title: Psalms 65:4
content: 4 Blessed is the one You choose and bring near to dwell in Your courts! We are filled with the goodness of Your house, the holiness of Your temple.

title: Psalms 65:5
content: 5 With awesome deeds of righteousness You answer us, O God of our salvation, the hope of all the ends of the earth and of the farthest seas.

title: Psalms 65:6
content: 6 You formed the mountains by Your power, having girded Yourself with might.

title: Psalms 65:7
content: 7 You stilled the roaring of the seas, the pounding of their waves, and the tumult of the nations.

title: Psalms 65:8
content: 8 Those who live far away fear Your wonders; You make the dawn and sunset shout for joy.

title: Psalms 65:9
content: 9 You attend to the earth and water it; with abundance You enrich it. The streams of God are full of water, for You prepare our grain by providing for the earth.

title: Psalms 65:10
content: 10 You soak its furrows and level its ridges; You soften it with showers and bless its growth.

title: Psalms 65:11
content: 11 You crown the year with Your bounty, and Your paths overflow with plenty.

title: Psalms 65:12
content: 12 The pastures of the wilderness overflow; the hills are robed with joy.

title: Psalms 65:13
content: 13 The pastures are clothed with flocks, and the valleys are decked with grain. They shout in triumph; indeed, they sing.

title: Psalms 66:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A song. A Psalm.

title: Psalms 66:1
content: 1 Make a joyful noise to God, all the earth!

title: Psalms 66:2
content: 2 Sing the glory of His name; make His praise glorious.

title: Psalms 66:3
content: 3 Say to God, “How awesome are Your deeds! So great is Your power that Your enemies cower before You.

title: Psalms 66:4
content: 4 All the earth bows down to You; they sing praise to You; they sing praise to Your name.” Selah

title: Psalms 66:5
content: 5 Come and see the works of God; how awesome are His deeds toward mankind.

title: Psalms 66:6
content: 6 He turned the sea into dry land; they passed through the waters on foot; there we rejoiced in Him.

title: Psalms 66:7
content: 7 He rules forever by His power; His eyes watch the nations. Do not let the rebellious exalt themselves. Selah

title: Psalms 66:8
content: 8 Bless our God, O peoples; let the sound of His praise be heard.

title: Psalms 66:9
content: 9 He preserves our lives and keeps our feet from slipping.

title: Psalms 66:10
content: 10 For You, O God, have tested us; You have refined us like silver.

title: Psalms 66:11
content: 11 You led us into the net; You laid burdens on our backs.

title: Psalms 66:12
content: 12 You let men ride over our heads; we went through fire and water, but You brought us into abundance.

title: Psalms 66:13
content: 13 I will enter Your house with burnt offerings; I will fulfill my vows to You—

title: Psalms 66:14
content: 14 the vows that my lips promised and my mouth spoke in my distress.

title: Psalms 66:15
content: 15 I will offer You fatlings as burnt offerings, with the fragrant smoke of rams; I will offer bulls and goats. Selah

title: Psalms 66:16
content: 16 Come and listen, all you who fear God, and I will declare what He has done for me.

title: Psalms 66:17
content: 17 I cried out to Him with my mouth and praised Him with my tongue.

title: Psalms 66:18
content: 18 If I had cherished iniquity in my heart, the Lord would not have listened.

title: Psalms 66:19
content: 19 But God has surely heard; He has attended to the sound of my prayer.

title: Psalms 66:20
content: 20 Blessed be God, who has not rejected my prayer or withheld from me His loving devotion!

title: Psalms 67:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. With stringed instruments. A Psalm. A song.

title: Psalms 67:1
content: 1 May God be gracious to us and bless us, and cause His face to shine upon us, Selah

title: Psalms 67:2
content: 2 that Your ways may be known on earth, Your salvation among all nations.

title: Psalms 67:3
content: 3 Let the peoples praise You, O God; let all the peoples praise You.

title: Psalms 67:4
content: 4 Let the nations be glad and sing for joy, for You judge the peoples justly and lead the nations of the earth. Selah

title: Psalms 67:5
content: 5 Let the peoples praise You, O God; let all the peoples praise You.

title: Psalms 67:6
content: 6 The earth has yielded its harvest; God, our God, blesses us.

title: Psalms 67:7
content: 7 God blesses us, that all the ends of the earth shall fear Him.

title: Psalms 68:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David. A song.

title: Psalms 68:1
content: 1 God arises. His enemies are scattered, and those who hate Him flee His presence.

title: Psalms 68:2
content: 2 As smoke is blown away, You will drive them out; as wax melts before the fire, the wicked will perish in the presence of God.

title: Psalms 68:3
content: 3 But the righteous will be glad and rejoice before God; they will celebrate with joy.

title: Psalms 68:4
content: 4 Sing to God! Sing praises to His name. Exalt Him who rides on the clouds—His name is the LORD—and rejoice before Him.

title: Psalms 68:5
content: 5 A father of the fatherless and a defender of widows is God in His holy habitation.

title: Psalms 68:6
content: 6 God settles the lonely in families; He leads the prisoners out to prosperity, but the rebellious dwell in a sun-scorched land.

title: Psalms 68:7
content: 7 O God, when You went out before Your people, when You marched through the wasteland, Selah

title: Psalms 68:8
content: 8 the earth shook and the heavens poured down rain before God, the One on Sinai, before God, the God of Israel.

title: Psalms 68:9
content: 9 You sent abundant rain, O God; You refreshed Your weary inheritance.

title: Psalms 68:10
content: 10 Your flock settled therein; O God, from Your bounty You provided for the poor.

title: Psalms 68:11
content: 11 The Lord gives the command; a great company of women proclaim it:

title: Psalms 68:12
content: 12 “Kings and their armies flee in haste; she who waits at home divides the plunder.

title: Psalms 68:13
content: 13 Though you lie down among the sheepfolds, the wings of the dove are covered with silver, and her feathers with shimmering gold.”

title: Psalms 68:14
content: 14 When the Almighty scattered the kings in the land, it was like the snow falling on Zalmon.

title: Psalms 68:15
content: 15 A mountain of God is Mount Bashan; a mountain of many peaks is Mount Bashan.

title: Psalms 68:16
content: 16 Why do you gaze in envy, O mountains of many peaks? This is the mountain God chose for His dwelling, where the LORD will surely dwell forever.

title: Psalms 68:17
content: 17 The chariots of God are tens of thousands—thousands of thousands are they; the Lord is in His sanctuary as He was at Sinai.

title: Psalms 68:18
content: 18 You have ascended on high; You have led captives away. You have received gifts from men, even from the rebellious, that the LORD God may dwell there.

title: Psalms 68:19
content: 19 Blessed be the Lord, who daily bears our burden, the God of our salvation. Selah

title: Psalms 68:20
content: 20 Our God is a God of deliverance; the Lord GOD is our rescuer from death.

title: Psalms 68:21
content: 21 Surely God will crush the heads of His enemies, the hairy crowns of those who persist in guilty ways.

title: Psalms 68:22
content: 22 The Lord said, “I will retrieve them from Bashan, I will bring them up from the depths of the sea,

title: Psalms 68:23
content: 23 that your foot may be dipped in the blood of your foes—the tongues of your dogs in the same.”

title: Psalms 68:24
content: 24 They have seen Your procession, O God—the march of my God and King into the sanctuary.

title: Psalms 68:25
content: 25 The singers lead the way, the musicians follow after, among the maidens playing tambourines.

title: Psalms 68:26
content: 26 Bless God in the great congregation; bless the LORD from the fountain of Israel.

title: Psalms 68:27
content: 27 There is Benjamin, the youngest, ruling them, the princes of Judah in their company, the princes of Zebulun and of Naphtali.

title: Psalms 68:28
content: 28 Summon Your power, O God; show Your strength, O God, which You have exerted on our behalf.

title: Psalms 68:29
content: 29 Because of Your temple at Jerusalem kings will bring You gifts.

title: Psalms 68:30
content: 30 Rebuke the beast in the reeds, the herd of bulls among the calves of the nations, until it submits, bringing bars of silver. Scatter the nations who delight in war.

title: Psalms 68:31
content: 31 Envoys will arrive from Egypt; Cush will stretch out her hands to God.

title: Psalms 68:32
content: 32 Sing to God, O kingdoms of the earth; sing praises to the Lord—Selah

title: Psalms 68:33
content: 33 to Him who rides upon the highest heavens of old; behold, His mighty voice resounds.

title: Psalms 68:34
content: 34 Ascribe the power to God, whose majesty is over Israel, whose strength is in the skies.

title: Psalms 68:35
content: 35 O God, You are awesome in Your sanctuary; the God of Israel Himself gives strength and power to His people. Blessed be God!

title: Psalms 69:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. To the tune of “Lilies.” Of David.

title: Psalms 69:1
content: 1 Save me, O God, for the waters are up to my neck.

title: Psalms 69:2
content: 2 I have sunk into the miry depths, where there is no footing; I have drifted into deep waters, where the flood engulfs me.

title: Psalms 69:3
content: 3 I am weary from my crying; my throat is parched. My eyes fail, looking for my God.

title: Psalms 69:4
content: 4 Those who hate me without cause outnumber the hairs of my head; many are those who would destroy me—my enemies for no reason. Though I did not steal, I must repay.

title: Psalms 69:5
content: 5 You know my folly, O God, and my guilt is not hidden from You.

title: Psalms 69:6
content: 6 May those who hope in You not be ashamed through me, O Lord GOD of Hosts; may those who seek You not be dishonored through me, O God of Israel.

title: Psalms 69:7
content: 7 For I have endured scorn for Your sake, and shame has covered my face.

title: Psalms 69:8
content: 8 I have become a stranger to my brothers and a foreigner to my mother’s sons,

title: Psalms 69:9
content: 9 because zeal for Your house has consumed me, and the insults of those who insult You have fallen on me.

title: Psalms 69:10
content: 10 I wept and fasted, but it brought me reproach.

title: Psalms 69:11
content: 11 I made sackcloth my clothing, and I was sport to them.

title: Psalms 69:12
content: 12 Those who sit at the gate mock me, and I am the song of drunkards.

title: Psalms 69:13
content: 13 But my prayer to You, O LORD, is for a time of favor. In Your abundant loving devotion, O God, answer me with Your sure salvation.

title: Psalms 69:14
content: 14 Rescue me from the mire and do not let me sink; deliver me from my foes and out of the deep waters.

title: Psalms 69:15
content: 15 Do not let the floods engulf me or the depths swallow me up; let not the Pit close its mouth over me.

title: Psalms 69:16
content: 16 Answer me, O LORD, for Your loving devotion is good; turn to me in keeping with Your great compassion.

title: Psalms 69:17
content: 17 Hide not Your face from Your servant, for I am in distress. Answer me quickly!

title: Psalms 69:18
content: 18 Draw near to my soul and redeem me; ransom me because of my foes.

title: Psalms 69:19
content: 19 You know my reproach, my shame and disgrace. All my adversaries are before You.

title: Psalms 69:20
content: 20 Insults have broken my heart, and I am in despair. I looked for sympathy, but there was none, for comforters, but I found no one.

title: Psalms 69:21
content: 21 They poisoned my food with gall and gave me vinegar to quench my thirst.

title: Psalms 69:22
content: 22 May their table become a snare; may it be a retribution and a trap.

title: Psalms 69:23
content: 23 May their eyes be darkened so they cannot see, and their backs be bent forever.

title: Psalms 69:24
content: 24 Pour out Your wrath upon them, and let Your burning anger overtake them.

title: Psalms 69:25
content: 25 May their place be deserted; let there be no one to dwell in their tents.

title: Psalms 69:26
content: 26 For they persecute the one You struck and recount the pain of those You wounded.

title: Psalms 69:27
content: 27 Add iniquity to their iniquity; let them not share in Your righteousness.

title: Psalms 69:28
content: 28 May they be blotted out of the Book of Life and not listed with the righteous.

title: Psalms 69:29
content: 29 But I am in pain and distress; let Your salvation protect me, O God.

title: Psalms 69:30
content: 30 I will praise God’s name in song and exalt Him with thanksgiving.

title: Psalms 69:31
content: 31 And this will please the LORD more than an ox, more than a bull with horns and hooves.

title: Psalms 69:32
content: 32 The humble will see and rejoice. You who seek God, let your hearts be revived!

title: Psalms 69:33
content: 33 For the LORD listens to the needy and does not despise His captive people.

title: Psalms 69:34
content: 34 Let heaven and earth praise Him, the seas and everything that moves in them.

title: Psalms 69:35
content: 35 For God will save Zion and rebuild the cities of Judah, that they may dwell there and possess it.

title: Psalms 69:36
content: 36 The descendants of His servants will inherit it, and those who love His name will settle in it.

title: Psalms 70:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. Of David. To bring remembrance.

title: Psalms 70:1
content: 1 Make haste, O God, to deliver me! Hurry, O LORD, to help me!

title: Psalms 70:2
content: 2 May those who seek my life be ashamed and confounded; may those who wish me harm be repelled and humiliated.

title: Psalms 70:3
content: 3 May those who say, “Aha, aha!” retreat because of their shame.

title: Psalms 70:4
content: 4 May all who seek You rejoice and be glad in You; may those who love Your salvation always say, “Let God be magnified!”

title: Psalms 70:5
content: 5 But I am poor and needy; hurry to me, O God. You are my help and my deliverer; O LORD, do not delay.

title: Psalms 71:1
content: 1 In You, O LORD, I have taken refuge; let me never be put to shame.

title: Psalms 71:2
content: 2 In Your justice, rescue and deliver me; incline Your ear and save me.

title: Psalms 71:3
content: 3 Be my rock of refuge, where I can always go. Give the command to save me, for You are my rock and my fortress.

title: Psalms 71:4
content: 4 Deliver me, O my God, from the hand of the wicked, from the grasp of the unjust and ruthless.

title: Psalms 71:5
content: 5 For You are my hope, O Lord GOD, my confidence from my youth.

title: Psalms 71:6
content: 6 I have leaned on You since birth; You pulled me from my mother’s womb. My praise is always for You.

title: Psalms 71:7
content: 7 I have become a portent to many, but You are my strong refuge.

title: Psalms 71:8
content: 8 My mouth is filled with Your praise and with Your splendor all day long.

title: Psalms 71:9
content: 9 Do not discard me in my old age; do not forsake me when my strength fails.

title: Psalms 71:10
content: 10 For my enemies speak against me, and those who lie in wait for my life conspire,

title: Psalms 71:11
content: 11 saying, “God has forsaken him; pursue him and seize him, for there is no one to rescue him.”

title: Psalms 71:12
content: 12 Be not far from me, O God. Hurry, O my God, to help me.

title: Psalms 71:13
content: 13 May the accusers of my soul be ashamed and consumed; may those who seek my harm be covered with scorn and disgrace.

title: Psalms 71:14
content: 14 But I will always hope and will praise You more and more.

title: Psalms 71:15
content: 15 My mouth will declare Your righteousness and Your salvation all day long, though I cannot know their full measure.

title: Psalms 71:16
content: 16 I will come in the strength of the Lord GOD; I will proclaim Your righteousness—Yours alone.

title: Psalms 71:17
content: 17 O God, You have taught me from my youth, and to this day I proclaim Your marvelous deeds.

title: Psalms 71:18
content: 18 Even when I am old and gray, do not forsake me, O God, until I proclaim Your power to the next generation, Your might to all who are to come.

title: Psalms 71:19
content: 19 Your righteousness reaches to the heavens, O God, You who have done great things. Who, O God, is like You?

title: Psalms 71:20
content: 20 Though You have shown me many troubles and misfortunes, You will revive me once again. Even from the depths of the earth You will bring me back up.

title: Psalms 71:21
content: 21 You will increase my honor and comfort me once again.

title: Psalms 71:22
content: 22 So I will praise You with the harp for Your faithfulness, O my God; I will sing praise to You with the lyre, O Holy One of Israel.

title: Psalms 71:23
content: 23 When I sing praise to You my lips will shout for joy, along with my soul, which You have redeemed.

title: Psalms 71:24
content: 24 My tongue will indeed proclaim Your righteousness all day long, for those who seek my harm are disgraced and confounded.

title: Psalms 72:0
content: 0 Of Solomon.

title: Psalms 72:1
content: 1 Endow the king with Your justice, O God, and the son of the king with Your righteousness.

title: Psalms 72:2
content: 2 May he judge Your people with righteousness and Your afflicted with justice.

title: Psalms 72:3
content: 3 May the mountains bring peace to the people, and the hills bring righteousness.

title: Psalms 72:4
content: 4 May he vindicate the afflicted among the people; may he save the children of the needy and crush the oppressor.

title: Psalms 72:5
content: 5 May they fear him as long as the sun shines, as long as the moon remains, through all generations.

title: Psalms 72:6
content: 6 May he be like rain that falls on freshly cut grass, like spring showers that water the earth.

title: Psalms 72:7
content: 7 May the righteous flourish in his days and prosperity abound until the moon is no more.

title: Psalms 72:8
content: 8 May he rule from sea to sea, and from the Euphrates to the ends of the earth.

title: Psalms 72:9
content: 9 May the nomads bow before him, and his enemies lick the dust.

title: Psalms 72:10
content: 10 May the kings of Tarshish and distant shores bring tribute; may the kings of Sheba and Seba offer gifts.

title: Psalms 72:11
content: 11 May all kings bow down to him and all nations serve him.

title: Psalms 72:12
content: 12 For he will deliver the needy who cry out and the afflicted who have no helper.

title: Psalms 72:13
content: 13 He will take pity on the poor and needy and save the lives of the oppressed.

title: Psalms 72:14
content: 14 He will redeem them from oppression and violence, for their blood is precious in his sight.

title: Psalms 72:15
content: 15 Long may he live! May gold from Sheba be given him. May people ever pray for him; may they bless him all day long.

title: Psalms 72:16
content: 16 May there be an abundance of grain in the land; may it sway atop the hills. May its fruit trees flourish like the forests of Lebanon, the people of its cities like the grass of the field.

title: Psalms 72:17
content: 17 May his name endure forever; may his name continue as long as the sun shines. In him may all nations be blessed; may they call him blessed.

title: Psalms 72:18
content: 18 Blessed be the LORD God, the God of Israel, who alone does marvelous deeds.

title: Psalms 72:19
content: 19 And blessed be His glorious name forever; may all the earth be filled with His glory. Amen and amen.

title: Psalms 72:20
content: 20 Thus conclude the prayers of David son of Jesse.

title: Psalms 73:0
content: 0 A Psalm of Asaph.

title: Psalms 73:1
content: 1 Surely God is good to Israel, to those who are pure in heart.

title: Psalms 73:2
content: 2 But as for me, my feet had almost stumbled; my steps had nearly slipped.

title: Psalms 73:3
content: 3 For I envied the arrogant when I saw the prosperity of the wicked.

title: Psalms 73:4
content: 4 They have no struggle in their death; their bodies are well-fed.

title: Psalms 73:5
content: 5 They are free of the burdens others carry; they are not afflicted like other men.

title: Psalms 73:6
content: 6 Therefore pride is their necklace; a garment of violence covers them.

title: Psalms 73:7
content: 7 From their prosperity proceeds iniquity; the imaginations of their hearts run wild.

title: Psalms 73:8
content: 8 They mock and speak with malice; with arrogance they threaten oppression.

title: Psalms 73:9
content: 9 They set their mouths against the heavens, and their tongues strut across the earth.

title: Psalms 73:10
content: 10 So their people return to this place and drink up waters in abundance.

title: Psalms 73:11
content: 11 The wicked say, “How can God know? Does the Most High have knowledge?”

title: Psalms 73:12
content: 12 Behold, these are the wicked—always carefree as they increase their wealth.

title: Psalms 73:13
content: 13 Surely in vain I have kept my heart pure; in innocence I have washed my hands.

title: Psalms 73:14
content: 14 For I am afflicted all day long and punished every morning.

title: Psalms 73:15
content: 15 If I had said, “I will speak this way,” then I would have betrayed Your children.

title: Psalms 73:16
content: 16 When I tried to understand all this, it was troublesome in my sight

title: Psalms 73:17
content: 17 until I entered God’s sanctuary; then I discerned their end.

title: Psalms 73:18
content: 18 Surely You set them on slick ground; You cast them down into ruin.

title: Psalms 73:19
content: 19 How suddenly they are laid waste, completely swept away by terrors!

title: Psalms 73:20
content: 20 Like one waking from a dream, so You, O Lord, awaken and despise their form.

title: Psalms 73:21
content: 21 When my heart was grieved and I was pierced within,

title: Psalms 73:22
content: 22 I was senseless and ignorant; I was a brute beast before You.

title: Psalms 73:23
content: 23 Yet I am always with You; You hold my right hand.

title: Psalms 73:24
content: 24 You guide me with Your counsel, and later receive me in glory.

title: Psalms 73:25
content: 25 Whom have I in heaven but You? And on earth I desire no one besides You.

title: Psalms 73:26
content: 26 My flesh and my heart may fail, but God is the strength of my heart and my portion forever.

title: Psalms 73:27
content: 27 Those far from You will surely perish; You destroy all who are unfaithful to You.

title: Psalms 73:28
content: 28 But as for me, it is good to draw near to God. I have made the Lord GOD my refuge, that I may proclaim all Your works.

title: Psalms 74:0
content: 0 A Maskil of Asaph.

title: Psalms 74:1
content: 1 Why have You rejected us forever, O God? Why does Your anger smolder against the sheep of Your pasture?

title: Psalms 74:2
content: 2 Remember Your congregation, which You purchased long ago and redeemed as the tribe of Your inheritance—Mount Zion, where You dwell.

title: Psalms 74:3
content: 3 Turn Your steps to the everlasting ruins, to everything in the sanctuary the enemy has destroyed.

title: Psalms 74:4
content: 4 Your foes have roared within Your meeting place; they have unfurled their banners as signs,

title: Psalms 74:5
content: 5 like men wielding axes in a thicket of trees

title: Psalms 74:6
content: 6 and smashing all the carvings with hatchets and picks.

title: Psalms 74:7
content: 7 They have burned Your sanctuary to the ground; they have defiled the dwelling place of Your Name.

title: Psalms 74:8
content: 8 They said in their hearts, “We will crush them completely.” They burned down every place where God met us in the land.

title: Psalms 74:9
content: 9 There are no signs for us to see. There is no longer any prophet. And none of us knows how long this will last.

title: Psalms 74:10
content: 10 How long, O God, will the enemy taunt You? Will the foe revile Your name forever?

title: Psalms 74:11
content: 11 Why do You withdraw Your strong right hand? Stretch it out to destroy them!

title: Psalms 74:12
content: 12 Yet God is my King from ancient times, working salvation on the earth.

title: Psalms 74:13
content: 13 You divided the sea by Your strength; You smashed the heads of the dragons of the sea;

title: Psalms 74:14
content: 14 You crushed the heads of Leviathan; You fed him to the creatures of the desert.

title: Psalms 74:15
content: 15 You broke open the fountain and the flood; You dried up the ever-flowing rivers.

title: Psalms 74:16
content: 16 The day is Yours, and also the night; You established the moon and the sun.

title: Psalms 74:17
content: 17 You set all the boundaries of the earth; You made the summer and winter.

title: Psalms 74:18
content: 18 Remember how the enemy has mocked You, O LORD, how a foolish people has spurned Your name.

title: Psalms 74:19
content: 19 Do not deliver the soul of Your dove to beasts; do not forget the lives of Your afflicted forever.

title: Psalms 74:20
content: 20 Consider Your covenant, for haunts of violence fill the dark places of the land.

title: Psalms 74:21
content: 21 Do not let the oppressed retreat in shame; may the poor and needy praise Your name.

title: Psalms 74:22
content: 22 Rise up, O God; defend Your cause! Remember how the fool mocks You all day long.

title: Psalms 74:23
content: 23 Do not disregard the clamor of Your adversaries, the uproar of Your enemies that ascends continually.

title: Psalms 75:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster: To the tune of “Do Not Destroy.” A Psalm of Asaph. A song.

title: Psalms 75:1
content: 1 We give thanks to You, O God; we give thanks, for Your Name is near. The people declare Your wondrous works.

title: Psalms 75:2
content: 2 “When I choose a time, I will judge fairly.

title: Psalms 75:3
content: 3 When the earth and all its dwellers quake, it is I who bear up its pillars. Selah

title: Psalms 75:4
content: 4 I say to the proud, ‘Do not boast,’ and to the wicked, ‘Do not lift up your horn.

title: Psalms 75:5
content: 5 Do not lift up your horn against heaven or speak with an outstretched neck.’”

title: Psalms 75:6
content: 6 For exaltation comes neither from east nor west, nor out of the desert,

title: Psalms 75:7
content: 7 but it is God who judges; He brings down one and exalts another.

title: Psalms 75:8
content: 8 For a cup is in the hand of the LORD, full of foaming wine mixed with spices. He pours from His cup, and all the wicked of the earth drink it down to the dregs.

title: Psalms 75:9
content: 9 But I will proclaim Him forever; I will sing praise to the God of Jacob.

title: Psalms 75:10
content: 10 “All the horns of the wicked I will cut off, but the horns of the righteous will be exalted.”

title: Psalms 76:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. With stringed instruments. A Psalm of Asaph. A song.

title: Psalms 76:1
content: 1 God is known in Judah; His name is great in Israel.

title: Psalms 76:2
content: 2 His tent is in Salem, His dwelling place in Zion.

title: Psalms 76:3
content: 3 There He shattered the flaming arrows, the shield and sword and weapons of war. Selah

title: Psalms 76:4
content: 4 You are resplendent with light, more majestic than mountains filled with game.

title: Psalms 76:5
content: 5 The valiant lie plundered; they sleep their last sleep. No men of might could lift a hand.

title: Psalms 76:6
content: 6 At Your rebuke, O God of Jacob, both horse and rider lie stunned.

title: Psalms 76:7
content: 7 You alone are to be feared. When You are angry, who can stand before You?

title: Psalms 76:8
content: 8 From heaven You pronounced judgment, and the earth feared and was still

title: Psalms 76:9
content: 9 when God rose up to judge, to save all the lowly of the earth. Selah

title: Psalms 76:10
content: 10 Even the wrath of man shall praise You; with the survivors of wrath You will clothe Yourself.

title: Psalms 76:11
content: 11 Make and fulfill your vows to the LORD your God; let all the neighboring lands bring tribute to Him who is to be feared.

title: Psalms 76:12
content: 12 He breaks the spirits of princes; He is feared by the kings of the earth.

title: Psalms 77:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. According to Jeduthun. A Psalm of Asaph.

title: Psalms 77:1
content: 1 I cried out to God; I cried aloud to God to hear me.

title: Psalms 77:2
content: 2 In the day of trouble I sought the Lord; through the night my outstretched hands did not grow weary; my soul refused to be comforted.

title: Psalms 77:3
content: 3 I remembered You, O God, and I groaned; I mused and my spirit grew faint. Selah

title: Psalms 77:4
content: 4 You have kept my eyes from closing; I am too troubled to speak.

title: Psalms 77:5
content: 5 I considered the days of old, the years long in the past.

title: Psalms 77:6
content: 6 At night I remembered my song; in my heart I mused, and my spirit pondered:

title: Psalms 77:7
content: 7 “Will the Lord spurn us forever and never show His favor again?

title: Psalms 77:8
content: 8 Is His loving devotion gone forever? Has His promise failed for all time?

title: Psalms 77:9
content: 9 Has God forgotten to be gracious? Has His anger shut off His compassion?” Selah

title: Psalms 77:10
content: 10 So I said, “I am grieved that the right hand of the Most High has changed.”

title: Psalms 77:11
content: 11 I will remember the works of the LORD; yes, I will remember Your wonders of old.

title: Psalms 77:12
content: 12 I will reflect on all You have done and ponder Your mighty deeds.

title: Psalms 77:13
content: 13 Your way, O God, is holy. What god is so great as our God?

title: Psalms 77:14
content: 14 You are the God who works wonders; You display Your strength among the peoples.

title: Psalms 77:15
content: 15 With power You redeemed Your people, the sons of Jacob and Joseph. Selah

title: Psalms 77:16
content: 16 The waters saw You, O God; the waters saw You and swirled; even the depths were shaken.

title: Psalms 77:17
content: 17 The clouds poured down water; the skies resounded with thunder; Your arrows flashed back and forth.

title: Psalms 77:18
content: 18 Your thunder resounded in the whirlwind; the lightning lit up the world; the earth trembled and quaked.

title: Psalms 77:19
content: 19 Your path led through the sea, Your way through the mighty waters, but Your footprints were not to be found.

title: Psalms 77:20
content: 20 You led Your people like a flock by the hand of Moses and Aaron.

title: Psalms 78:0
content: 0 A Maskil of Asaph.

title: Psalms 78:1
content: 1 Give ear, O my people, to my instruction; listen to the words of my mouth.

title: Psalms 78:2
content: 2 I will open my mouth in parables; I will utter things hidden from the beginning,

title: Psalms 78:3
content: 3 that we have heard and known and our fathers have relayed to us.

title: Psalms 78:4
content: 4 We will not hide them from their children but will declare to the next generation the praises of the LORD and His might and the wonders He has performed.

title: Psalms 78:5
content: 5 For He established a testimony in Jacob and appointed a law in Israel, which He commanded our fathers to teach to their children,

title: Psalms 78:6
content: 6 that the coming generation would know them—even children yet to be born—to arise and tell their own children

title: Psalms 78:7
content: 7 that they should put their confidence in God, not forgetting His works, but keeping His commandments.

title: Psalms 78:8
content: 8 Then they will not be like their fathers, a stubborn and rebellious generation, whose heart was not loyal, whose spirit was not faithful to God.

title: Psalms 78:9
content: 9 The archers of Ephraim turned back on the day of battle.

title: Psalms 78:10
content: 10 They failed to keep God’s covenant and refused to live by His law.

title: Psalms 78:11
content: 11 They forgot what He had done, the wonders He had shown them.

title: Psalms 78:12
content: 12 He worked wonders before their fathers in the land of Egypt, in the region of Zoan.

title: Psalms 78:13
content: 13 He split the sea and brought them through; He set the waters upright like a wall.

title: Psalms 78:14
content: 14 He led them with a cloud by day and with a light of fire all night.

title: Psalms 78:15
content: 15 He split the rocks in the wilderness and gave them drink as abundant as the seas.

title: Psalms 78:16
content: 16 He brought streams from the stone and made water flow down like rivers.

title: Psalms 78:17
content: 17 But they continued to sin against Him, rebelling in the desert against the Most High.

title: Psalms 78:18
content: 18 They willfully tested God by demanding the food they craved.

title: Psalms 78:19
content: 19 They spoke against God, saying, “Can God really prepare a table in the wilderness?

title: Psalms 78:20
content: 20 When He struck the rock, water gushed out and torrents raged. But can He also give bread or supply His people with meat?”

title: Psalms 78:21
content: 21 Therefore the LORD heard and was filled with wrath; so a fire was kindled against Jacob, and His anger flared against Israel,

title: Psalms 78:22
content: 22 because they did not believe God or rely on His salvation.

title: Psalms 78:23
content: 23 Yet He commanded the clouds above and opened the doors of the heavens.

title: Psalms 78:24
content: 24 He rained down manna for them to eat; He gave them grain from heaven.

title: Psalms 78:25
content: 25 Man ate the bread of angels; He sent them food in abundance.

title: Psalms 78:26
content: 26 He stirred the east wind from the heavens and drove the south wind by His might.

title: Psalms 78:27
content: 27 He rained meat on them like dust, and winged birds like the sand of the sea.

title: Psalms 78:28
content: 28 He felled them in the midst of their camp, all around their dwellings.

title: Psalms 78:29
content: 29 So they ate and were well filled, for He gave them what they craved.

title: Psalms 78:30
content: 30 Yet before they had filled their desire, with the food still in their mouths,

title: Psalms 78:31
content: 31 God’s anger flared against them, and He put to death their strongest and subdued the young men of Israel.

title: Psalms 78:32
content: 32 In spite of all this, they kept on sinning; despite His wonderful works, they did not believe.

title: Psalms 78:33
content: 33 So He ended their days in futility, and their years in sudden terror.

title: Psalms 78:34
content: 34 When He slew them, they would seek Him; they repented and searched for God.

title: Psalms 78:35
content: 35 And they remembered that God was their Rock, that God Most High was their Redeemer.

title: Psalms 78:36
content: 36 But they deceived Him with their mouths, and lied to Him with their tongues.

title: Psalms 78:37
content: 37 Their hearts were disloyal to Him, and they were unfaithful to His covenant.

title: Psalms 78:38
content: 38 And yet He was compassionate; He forgave their iniquity and did not destroy them. He often restrained His anger and did not unleash His full wrath.

title: Psalms 78:39
content: 39 He remembered that they were but flesh, a passing breeze that does not return.

title: Psalms 78:40
content: 40 How often they disobeyed Him in the wilderness and grieved Him in the desert!

title: Psalms 78:41
content: 41 Again and again they tested God and provoked the Holy One of Israel.

title: Psalms 78:42
content: 42 They did not remember His power—the day He redeemed them from the adversary,

title: Psalms 78:43
content: 43 when He performed His signs in Egypt and His wonders in the fields of Zoan.

title: Psalms 78:44
content: 44 He turned their rivers to blood, and from their streams they could not drink.

title: Psalms 78:45
content: 45 He sent swarms of flies that devoured them, and frogs that devastated them.

title: Psalms 78:46
content: 46 He gave their crops to the grasshopper, the fruit of their labor to the locust.

title: Psalms 78:47
content: 47 He killed their vines with hailstones and their sycamore-figs with sleet.

title: Psalms 78:48
content: 48 He abandoned their cattle to the hail and their livestock to bolts of lightning.

title: Psalms 78:49
content: 49 He unleashed His fury against them, wrath, indignation, and calamity—a band of destroying angels.

title: Psalms 78:50
content: 50 He cleared a path for His anger; He did not spare them from death but delivered their lives to the plague.

title: Psalms 78:51
content: 51 He struck all the firstborn of Egypt, the virility in the tents of Ham.

title: Psalms 78:52
content: 52 He led out His people like sheep and guided them like a flock in the wilderness.

title: Psalms 78:53
content: 53 He led them safely, so they did not fear, but the sea engulfed their enemies.

title: Psalms 78:54
content: 54 He brought them to His holy land, to the mountain His right hand had acquired.

title: Psalms 78:55
content: 55 He drove out nations before them and apportioned their inheritance; He settled the tribes of Israel in their tents.

title: Psalms 78:56
content: 56 But they tested and disobeyed God Most High, for they did not keep His decrees.

title: Psalms 78:57
content: 57 They turned back and were faithless like their fathers, twisted like a faulty bow.

title: Psalms 78:58
content: 58 They enraged Him with their high places and provoked His jealousy with their idols.

title: Psalms 78:59
content: 59 On hearing it, God was furious and rejected Israel completely.

title: Psalms 78:60
content: 60 He abandoned the tabernacle of Shiloh, the tent He had pitched among men.

title: Psalms 78:61
content: 61 He delivered His strength to captivity, and His splendor to the hand of the adversary.

title: Psalms 78:62
content: 62 He surrendered His people to the sword because He was enraged by His heritage.

title: Psalms 78:63
content: 63 Fire consumed His young men, and their maidens were left without wedding songs.

title: Psalms 78:64
content: 64 His priests fell by the sword, but their widows could not lament.

title: Psalms 78:65
content: 65 Then the Lord awoke as from sleep, like a mighty warrior overcome by wine.

title: Psalms 78:66
content: 66 He beat back His foes; He put them to everlasting shame.

title: Psalms 78:67
content: 67 He rejected the tent of Joseph and refused the tribe of Ephraim.

title: Psalms 78:68
content: 68 But He chose the tribe of Judah, Mount Zion, which He loved.

title: Psalms 78:69
content: 69 He built His sanctuary like the heights, like the earth He has established forever.

title: Psalms 78:70
content: 70 He chose David His servant and took him from the sheepfolds;

title: Psalms 78:71
content: 71 from tending the ewes He brought him to be shepherd of His people Jacob, of Israel His inheritance.

title: Psalms 78:72
content: 72 So David shepherded them with integrity of heart and guided them with skillful hands.

title: Psalms 79:0
content: 0 A Psalm of Asaph.

title: Psalms 79:1
content: 1 The nations, O God, have invaded Your inheritance; they have defiled Your holy temple and reduced Jerusalem to rubble.

title: Psalms 79:2
content: 2 They have given the corpses of Your servants as food to the birds of the air, the flesh of Your saints to the beasts of the earth.

title: Psalms 79:3
content: 3 They have poured out their blood like water all around Jerusalem, and there is no one to bury the dead.

title: Psalms 79:4
content: 4 We have become a reproach to our neighbors, a scorn and derision to those around us.

title: Psalms 79:5
content: 5 How long, O LORD? Will You be angry forever? Will Your jealousy burn like fire?

title: Psalms 79:6
content: 6 Pour out Your wrath on the nations that do not acknowledge You, on the kingdoms that refuse to call on Your name,

title: Psalms 79:7
content: 7 for they have devoured Jacob and devastated his homeland.

title: Psalms 79:8
content: 8 Do not hold past sins against us; let Your compassion come quickly, for we are brought low.

title: Psalms 79:9
content: 9 Help us, O God of our salvation, for the glory of Your name; deliver us and atone for our sins, for the sake of Your name.

title: Psalms 79:10
content: 10 Why should the nations ask, “Where is their God?” Before our eyes, make known among the nations Your vengeance for the bloodshed of Your servants.

title: Psalms 79:11
content: 11 May the groans of the captives reach You; by the strength of Your arm preserve those condemned to death.

title: Psalms 79:12
content: 12 Pay back into the laps of our neighbors sevenfold the reproach they hurled at You, O Lord.

title: Psalms 79:13
content: 13 Then we Your people, the sheep of Your pasture, will thank You forever; from generation to generation we will declare Your praise.

title: Psalms 80:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. To the tune of “The Lilies of the Covenant.” A Psalm of Asaph.

title: Psalms 80:1
content: 1 Hear us, O Shepherd of Israel, who leads Joseph like a flock; You who sit enthroned between the cherubim, shine forth

title: Psalms 80:2
content: 2 before Ephraim, Benjamin, and Manasseh. Rally Your mighty power and come to save us.

title: Psalms 80:3
content: 3 Restore us, O God, and cause Your face to shine upon us, that we may be saved.

title: Psalms 80:4
content: 4 O LORD God of Hosts, how long will Your anger smolder against the prayers of Your people?

title: Psalms 80:5
content: 5 You fed them with the bread of tears and made them drink the full measure of their tears.

title: Psalms 80:6
content: 6 You make us contend with our neighbors; our enemies mock us.

title: Psalms 80:7
content: 7 Restore us, O God of Hosts, and cause Your face to shine upon us, that we may be saved.

title: Psalms 80:8
content: 8 You uprooted a vine from Egypt; You drove out the nations and transplanted it.

title: Psalms 80:9
content: 9 You cleared the ground for it, and it took root and filled the land.

title: Psalms 80:10
content: 10 The mountains were covered by its shade, and the mighty cedars with its branches.

title: Psalms 80:11
content: 11 It sent out its branches to the Sea, and its shoots toward the River.

title: Psalms 80:12
content: 12 Why have You broken down its walls, so that all who pass by pick its fruit?

title: Psalms 80:13
content: 13 The boar from the forest ravages it, and the creatures of the field feed upon it.

title: Psalms 80:14
content: 14 Return, O God of Hosts, we pray! Look down from heaven and see! Attend to this vine—

title: Psalms 80:15
content: 15 the root Your right hand has planted, the son You have raised up for Yourself.

title: Psalms 80:16
content: 16 Your vine has been cut down and burned; they perish at the rebuke of Your countenance.

title: Psalms 80:17
content: 17 Let Your hand be upon the man at Your right hand, on the son of man You have raised up for Yourself.

title: Psalms 80:18
content: 18 Then we will not turn away from You; revive us, and we will call on Your name.

title: Psalms 80:19
content: 19 Restore us, O LORD God of Hosts; cause Your face to shine upon us, that we may be saved.

title: Psalms 81:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. According to Gittith. Of Asaph.

title: Psalms 81:1
content: 1 Sing for joy to God our strength; make a joyful noise to the God of Jacob.

title: Psalms 81:2
content: 2 Lift up a song, strike the tambourine, play the sweet-sounding harp and lyre.

title: Psalms 81:3
content: 3 Sound the ram’s horn at the New Moon, and at the full moon on the day of our Feast.

title: Psalms 81:4
content: 4 For this is a statute for Israel, an ordinance of the God of Jacob.

title: Psalms 81:5
content: 5 He ordained it as a testimony for Joseph when he went out over the land of Egypt, where I heard an unfamiliar language:

title: Psalms 81:6
