content: 6 “I relieved his shoulder of the burden; his hands were freed from the basket.

title: Psalms 81:7
content: 7 You called out in distress, and I rescued you; I answered you from the cloud of thunder; I tested you at the waters of Meribah. Selah

title: Psalms 81:8
content: 8 Hear, O My people, and I will warn you: O Israel, if only you would listen to Me!

title: Psalms 81:9
content: 9 There must be no strange god among you, nor shall you bow to a foreign god.

title: Psalms 81:10
content: 10 I am the LORD your God, who brought you up out of Egypt. Open wide your mouth, and I will fill it.

title: Psalms 81:11
content: 11 But My people would not listen to Me, and Israel would not obey Me.

title: Psalms 81:12
content: 12 So I gave them up to their stubborn hearts to follow their own devices.

title: Psalms 81:13
content: 13 If only My people would listen to Me, if Israel would follow My ways,

title: Psalms 81:14
content: 14 how soon I would subdue their enemies and turn My hand against their foes!

title: Psalms 81:15
content: 15 Those who hate the LORD would feign obedience, and their doom would last forever.

title: Psalms 81:16
content: 16 But I would feed you the finest wheat; with honey from the rock I would satisfy you.”

title: Psalms 82:0
content: 0 A Psalm of Asaph.

title: Psalms 82:1
content: 1 God presides in the divine assembly; He renders judgment among the gods:

title: Psalms 82:2
content: 2 “How long will you judge unjustly and show partiality to the wicked? Selah

title: Psalms 82:3
content: 3 Defend the cause of the weak and fatherless; uphold the rights of the afflicted and oppressed.

title: Psalms 82:4
content: 4 Rescue the weak and needy; save them from the hand of the wicked.

title: Psalms 82:5
content: 5 They do not know or understand; they wander in the darkness; all the foundations of the earth are shaken.

title: Psalms 82:6
content: 6 I have said, ‘You are gods; you are all sons of the Most High.’

title: Psalms 82:7
content: 7 But like mortals you will die, and like rulers you will fall.”

title: Psalms 82:8
content: 8 Arise, O God, judge the earth, for all the nations are Your inheritance.

title: Psalms 83:0
content: 0 A song. A Psalm of Asaph.

title: Psalms 83:1
content: 1 O God, be not silent; be not speechless; be not still, O God.

title: Psalms 83:2
content: 2 See how Your enemies rage, how Your foes have reared their heads.

title: Psalms 83:3
content: 3 With cunning they scheme against Your people and conspire against those You cherish,

title: Psalms 83:4
content: 4 saying, “Come, let us erase them as a nation; may the name of Israel be remembered no more.”

title: Psalms 83:5
content: 5 For with one mind they plot together; they form an alliance against You—

title: Psalms 83:6
content: 6 the tents of Edom and the Ishmaelites, of Moab and the Hagrites,

title: Psalms 83:7
content: 7 of Gebal, Ammon, and Amalek, of Philistia with the people of Tyre.

title: Psalms 83:8
content: 8 Even Assyria has joined them, lending strength to the sons of Lot. Selah

title: Psalms 83:9
content: 9 Do to them as You did to Midian, as to Sisera and Jabin at the River Kishon,

title: Psalms 83:10
content: 10 who perished at Endor and became like dung on the ground.

title: Psalms 83:11
content: 11 Make their nobles like Oreb and Zeeb, and all their princes like Zebah and Zalmunna,

title: Psalms 83:12
content: 12 who said, “Let us possess for ourselves the pastures of God.”

title: Psalms 83:13
content: 13 Make them like tumbleweed, O my God, like chaff before the wind.

title: Psalms 83:14
content: 14 As fire consumes a forest, as a flame sets the mountains ablaze,

title: Psalms 83:15
content: 15 so pursue them with Your tempest, and terrify them with Your storm.

title: Psalms 83:16
content: 16 Cover their faces with shame, that they may seek Your name, O LORD.

title: Psalms 83:17
content: 17 May they be ever ashamed and terrified; may they perish in disgrace.

title: Psalms 83:18
content: 18 May they know that You alone, whose name is the LORD, are Most High over all the earth.

title: Psalms 84:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. According to Gittith. A Psalm of the sons of Korah.

title: Psalms 84:1
content: 1 How lovely is Your dwelling place, O LORD of Hosts!

title: Psalms 84:2
content: 2 My soul longs, even faints, for the courts of the LORD; my heart and my flesh cry out for the living God.

title: Psalms 84:3
content: 3 Even the sparrow has found a home, and the swallow a nest for herself, where she places her young near Your altars, O LORD of Hosts, my King and my God.

title: Psalms 84:4
content: 4 How blessed are those who dwell in Your house! They are ever praising You. Selah

title: Psalms 84:5
content: 5 Blessed are those whose strength is in You, whose hearts are set on pilgrimage.

title: Psalms 84:6
content: 6 As they pass through the Valley of Baca, they make it a place of springs; even the autumn rain covers it with pools.

title: Psalms 84:7
content: 7 They go from strength to strength, until each appears before God in Zion.

title: Psalms 84:8
content: 8 O LORD God of Hosts, hear my prayer; give ear, O God of Jacob. Selah

title: Psalms 84:9
content: 9 Take notice of our shield, O God, and look with favor on the face of Your anointed.

title: Psalms 84:10
content: 10 For better is one day in Your courts than a thousand elsewhere. I would rather be a doorkeeper in the house of my God than dwell in the tents of the wicked.

title: Psalms 84:11
content: 11 For the LORD God is a sun and a shield; the LORD gives grace and glory; He withholds no good thing from those who walk with integrity.

title: Psalms 84:12
content: 12 O LORD of Hosts, how blessed is the man who trusts in You!

title: Psalms 85:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of the sons of Korah.

title: Psalms 85:1
content: 1 You showed favor to Your land, O LORD; You restored Jacob from captivity.

title: Psalms 85:2
content: 2 You forgave the iniquity of Your people; You covered all their sin. Selah

title: Psalms 85:3
content: 3 You withheld all Your fury; You turned from Your burning anger.

title: Psalms 85:4
content: 4 Restore us, O God of our salvation, and put away Your displeasure toward us.

title: Psalms 85:5
content: 5 Will You be angry with us forever? Will You draw out Your anger to all generations?

title: Psalms 85:6
content: 6 Will You not revive us again, that Your people may rejoice in You?

title: Psalms 85:7
content: 7 Show us Your loving devotion, O LORD, and grant us Your salvation.

title: Psalms 85:8
content: 8 I will listen to what God the LORD will say; for He will surely speak peace to His people and His saints; He will not let them return to folly.

title: Psalms 85:9
content: 9 Surely His salvation is near to those who fear Him, that His glory may dwell in our land.

title: Psalms 85:10
content: 10 Loving devotion and faithfulness have joined together; righteousness and peace have kissed.

title: Psalms 85:11
content: 11 Faithfulness sprouts from the earth, and righteousness looks down from heaven.

title: Psalms 85:12
content: 12 The LORD will indeed provide what is good, and our land will yield its increase.

title: Psalms 85:13
content: 13 Righteousness will go before Him to prepare the way for His steps.

title: Psalms 86:0
content: 0 A prayer of David.

title: Psalms 86:1
content: 1 Incline Your ear, O LORD, and answer me, for I am poor and needy.

title: Psalms 86:2
content: 2 Preserve my soul, for I am godly. You are my God; save Your servant who trusts in You.

title: Psalms 86:3
content: 3 Be merciful to me, O Lord, for I call to You all day long.

title: Psalms 86:4
content: 4 Bring joy to Your servant, for to You, O Lord, I lift up my soul.

title: Psalms 86:5
content: 5 For You, O Lord, are kind and forgiving, rich in loving devotion to all who call on You.

title: Psalms 86:6
content: 6 Hear my prayer, O LORD, and attend to my plea for mercy.

title: Psalms 86:7
content: 7 In the day of my distress I call on You, because You answer me.

title: Psalms 86:8
content: 8 O Lord, there is none like You among the gods, nor any works like Yours.

title: Psalms 86:9
content: 9 All the nations You have made will come and bow before You, O Lord, and they will glorify Your name.

title: Psalms 86:10
content: 10 For You are great and perform wonders; You alone are God.

title: Psalms 86:11
content: 11 Teach me Your way, O LORD, that I may walk in Your truth. Give me an undivided heart, that I may fear Your name.

title: Psalms 86:12
content: 12 I will praise You, O Lord my God, with all my heart; I will glorify Your name forever.

title: Psalms 86:13
content: 13 For great is Your loving devotion to me; You have delivered me from the depths of Sheol.

title: Psalms 86:14
content: 14 The arrogant rise against me, O God; a band of ruthless men seeks my life; they have no regard for You.

title: Psalms 86:15
content: 15 But You, O Lord, are a compassionate and gracious God, slow to anger, abounding in loving devotion and faithfulness.

title: Psalms 86:16
content: 16 Turn to me and have mercy; grant Your strength to Your servant; save the son of Your maidservant.

title: Psalms 86:17
content: 17 Show me a sign of Your goodness, that my enemies may see and be ashamed; for You, O LORD, have helped me and comforted me.

title: Psalms 87:0
content: 0 A Psalm of the sons of Korah. A song.

title: Psalms 87:1
content: 1 He has founded His city on the holy mountains.

title: Psalms 87:2
content: 2 The LORD loves the gates of Zion more than all the dwellings of Jacob.

title: Psalms 87:3
content: 3 Glorious things are ascribed to you, O city of God. Selah

title: Psalms 87:4
content: 4 “I will mention Rahab and Babylon among those who know Me—along with Philistia, Tyre, and Cush—when I say, ‘This one was born in Zion.’”

title: Psalms 87:5
content: 5 And it will be said of Zion: “This one and that one were born in her, and the Most High Himself will establish her.”

title: Psalms 87:6
content: 6 The LORD will record in the register of the peoples: “This one was born in Zion.” Selah

title: Psalms 87:7
content: 7 Singers and pipers will proclaim, “All my springs of joy are in You.”

title: Psalms 88:0
content: 0 A song. A Psalm of the sons of Korah. For the choirmaster. According to Mahalath Leannoth. A Maskil of Heman the Ezrahite.

title: Psalms 88:1
content: 1 O LORD, the God of my salvation, day and night I cry out before You.

title: Psalms 88:2
content: 2 May my prayer come before You; incline Your ear to my cry.

title: Psalms 88:3
content: 3 For my soul is full of troubles, and my life draws near to Sheol.

title: Psalms 88:4
content: 4 I am counted among those descending to the Pit. I am like a man without strength.

title: Psalms 88:5
content: 5 I am forsaken among the dead, like the slain who lie in the grave, whom You remember no more, who are cut off from Your care.

title: Psalms 88:6
content: 6 You have laid me in the lowest Pit, in the darkest of the depths.

title: Psalms 88:7
content: 7 Your wrath weighs heavily upon me; all Your waves have submerged me. Selah

title: Psalms 88:8
content: 8 You have removed my friends from me; You have made me repulsive to them; I am confined and cannot escape.

title: Psalms 88:9
content: 9 My eyes grow dim with grief. I call to You daily, O LORD; I spread out my hands to You.

title: Psalms 88:10
content: 10 Do You work wonders for the dead? Do departed spirits rise up to praise You? Selah

title: Psalms 88:11
content: 11 Can Your loving devotion be proclaimed in the grave, Your faithfulness in Abaddon?

title: Psalms 88:12
content: 12 Will Your wonders be known in the darkness, or Your righteousness in the land of oblivion?

title: Psalms 88:13
content: 13 But to You, O LORD, I cry for help; in the morning my prayer comes before You.

title: Psalms 88:14
content: 14 Why, O LORD, do You reject me? Why do You hide Your face from me?

title: Psalms 88:15
content: 15 From my youth I was afflicted and near death. I have borne Your terrors; I am in despair.

title: Psalms 88:16
content: 16 Your wrath has swept over me; Your terrors have destroyed me.

title: Psalms 88:17
content: 17 All day long they engulf me like water; they enclose me on every side.

title: Psalms 88:18
content: 18 You have removed my beloved and my friend; darkness is my closest companion.

title: Psalms 89:0
content: 0 A Maskil of Ethan the Ezrahite.

title: Psalms 89:1
content: 1 I will sing of the loving devotion of the LORD forever; with my mouth I will proclaim Your faithfulness to all generations.

title: Psalms 89:2
content: 2 For I have said, “Loving devotion is built up forever; in the heavens You establish Your faithfulness.”

title: Psalms 89:3
content: 3 You said, “I have made a covenant with My chosen one, I have sworn to David My servant:

title: Psalms 89:4
content: 4 ‘I will establish your offspring forever and build up your throne for all generations.’” Selah

title: Psalms 89:5
content: 5 The heavens praise Your wonders, O LORD—Your faithfulness as well—in the assembly of the holy ones.

title: Psalms 89:6
content: 6 For who in the skies can compare with the LORD? Who among the heavenly beings is like the LORD?

title: Psalms 89:7
content: 7 In the council of the holy ones, God is greatly feared, and awesome above all who surround Him.

title: Psalms 89:8
content: 8 O LORD God of Hosts, who is like You? O mighty LORD, Your faithfulness surrounds You.

title: Psalms 89:9
content: 9 You rule the raging sea; when its waves mount up, You still them.

title: Psalms 89:10
content: 10 You crushed Rahab like a carcass; You scattered Your enemies with Your mighty arm.

title: Psalms 89:11
content: 11 The heavens are Yours, and also the earth. The earth and its fullness You founded.

title: Psalms 89:12
content: 12 North and south You created; Tabor and Hermon shout for joy at Your name.

title: Psalms 89:13
content: 13 Mighty is Your arm; strong is Your hand. Your right hand is exalted.

title: Psalms 89:14
content: 14 Righteousness and justice are the foundation of Your throne; loving devotion and faithfulness go before You.

title: Psalms 89:15
content: 15 Blessed are those who know the joyful sound, who walk, O LORD, in the light of Your presence.

title: Psalms 89:16
content: 16 They rejoice in Your name all day long, and in Your righteousness they exult.

title: Psalms 89:17
content: 17 For You are the glory of their strength, and by Your favor our horn is exalted.

title: Psalms 89:18
content: 18 Surely our shield belongs to the LORD, and our king to the Holy One of Israel.

title: Psalms 89:19
content: 19 You once spoke in a vision; to Your godly ones You said, “I have bestowed help on a warrior; I have exalted one chosen from the people.

title: Psalms 89:20
content: 20 I have found My servant David; with My sacred oil I have anointed him.

title: Psalms 89:21
content: 21 My hand will sustain him; surely My arm will strengthen him.

title: Psalms 89:22
content: 22 No enemy will exact tribute; no wicked man will oppress him.

title: Psalms 89:23
content: 23 I will crush his foes before him and strike down those who hate him.

title: Psalms 89:24
content: 24 My faithfulness and loving devotion will be with him, and through My name his horn will be exalted.

title: Psalms 89:25
content: 25 I will set his hand over the sea, and his right hand upon the rivers.

title: Psalms 89:26
content: 26 He will call to Me, ‘You are my Father, my God, the Rock of my salvation.’

title: Psalms 89:27
content: 27 I will indeed appoint him as My firstborn, the highest of the kings of the earth.

title: Psalms 89:28
content: 28 I will forever preserve My loving devotion for him, and My covenant with him will stand fast.

title: Psalms 89:29
content: 29 I will establish his line forever, his throne as long as the heavens endure.

title: Psalms 89:30
content: 30 If his sons forsake My law and do not walk in My judgments,

title: Psalms 89:31
content: 31 if they violate My statutes and fail to keep My commandments,

title: Psalms 89:32
content: 32 I will attend to their transgression with the rod, and to their iniquity with stripes.

title: Psalms 89:33
content: 33 But I will not withdraw My loving devotion from him, nor ever betray My faithfulness.

title: Psalms 89:34
content: 34 I will not violate My covenant or alter the utterance of My lips.

title: Psalms 89:35
content: 35 Once and for all I have sworn by My holiness—I will not lie to David—

title: Psalms 89:36
content: 36 his offspring shall endure forever, and his throne before Me like the sun,

title: Psalms 89:37
content: 37 like the moon, established forever, a faithful witness in the sky.” Selah

title: Psalms 89:38
content: 38 Now, however, You have spurned and rejected him; You are enraged by Your anointed one.

title: Psalms 89:39
content: 39 You have renounced the covenant with Your servant and sullied his crown in the dust.

title: Psalms 89:40
content: 40 You have broken down all his walls; You have reduced his strongholds to rubble.

title: Psalms 89:41
content: 41 All who pass by plunder him; he has become a reproach to his neighbors.

title: Psalms 89:42
content: 42 You have exalted the right hand of his foes; You have made all his enemies rejoice.

title: Psalms 89:43
content: 43 You have bent the edge of his sword and have not sustained him in battle.

title: Psalms 89:44
content: 44 You have ended his splendor and cast his throne to the ground.

title: Psalms 89:45
content: 45 You have cut short the days of his youth; You have covered him with shame. Selah

title: Psalms 89:46
content: 46 How long, O LORD? Will You hide Yourself forever? Will Your wrath keep burning like fire?

title: Psalms 89:47
content: 47 Remember the briefness of my lifespan! For what futility You have created all men!

title: Psalms 89:48
content: 48 What man can live and never see death? Can he deliver his soul from the power of Sheol? Selah

title: Psalms 89:49
content: 49 Where, O Lord, is Your loving devotion of old, which You faithfully swore to David?

title: Psalms 89:50
content: 50 Remember, O Lord, the reproach of Your servants, which I bear in my heart from so many people—

title: Psalms 89:51
content: 51 how Your enemies have taunted, O LORD, and have mocked every step of Your anointed one!

title: Psalms 89:52
content: 52 Blessed be the LORD forever! Amen and amen.

title: Psalms 90:0
content: 0 A prayer of Moses the man of God.

title: Psalms 90:1
content: 1 Lord, You have been our dwelling place through all generations.

title: Psalms 90:2
content: 2 Before the mountains were born or You brought forth the earth and the world, from everlasting to everlasting You are God.

title: Psalms 90:3
content: 3 You return man to dust, saying, “Return, O sons of mortals.”

title: Psalms 90:4
content: 4 For in Your sight a thousand years are but a day that passes, or a watch of the night.

title: Psalms 90:5
content: 5 You sweep them away in their sleep; they are like the new grass of the morning—

title: Psalms 90:6
content: 6 in the morning it springs up new, but by evening it fades and withers.

title: Psalms 90:7
content: 7 For we are consumed by Your anger and terrified by Your wrath.

title: Psalms 90:8
content: 8 You have set our iniquities before You, our secret sins in the light of Your presence.

title: Psalms 90:9
content: 9 For all our days decline in Your fury; we finish our years with a sigh.

title: Psalms 90:10
content: 10 The length of our days is seventy years—or eighty if we are strong—yet their pride is but labor and sorrow, for they quickly pass, and we fly away.

title: Psalms 90:11
content: 11 Who knows the power of Your anger? Your wrath matches the fear You are due.

title: Psalms 90:12
content: 12 So teach us to number our days, that we may present a heart of wisdom.

title: Psalms 90:13
content: 13 Return, O LORD! How long will it be? Have compassion on Your servants.

title: Psalms 90:14
content: 14 Satisfy us in the morning with Your loving devotion, that we may sing for joy and be glad all our days.

title: Psalms 90:15
content: 15 Make us glad for as many days as You have afflicted us, for as many years as we have seen evil.

title: Psalms 90:16
content: 16 May Your work be shown to Your servants, and Your splendor to their children.

title: Psalms 90:17
content: 17 May the favor of the Lord our God rest upon us; establish for us the work of our hands—yes, establish the work of our hands!

title: Psalms 91:1
content: 1 He who dwells in the shelter of the Most High will abide in the shadow of the Almighty.

title: Psalms 91:2
content: 2 I will say to the LORD, “You are my refuge and my fortress, my God, in whom I trust.”

title: Psalms 91:3
content: 3 Surely He will deliver you from the snare of the fowler, and from the deadly plague.

title: Psalms 91:4
content: 4 He will cover you with His feathers; under His wings you will find refuge; His faithfulness is a shield and rampart.

title: Psalms 91:5
content: 5 You will not fear the terror of the night, nor the arrow that flies by day,

title: Psalms 91:6
content: 6 nor the pestilence that stalks in the darkness, nor the calamity that destroys at noon.

title: Psalms 91:7
content: 7 Though a thousand may fall at your side, and ten thousand at your right hand, no harm will come near you.

title: Psalms 91:8
content: 8 You will only see it with your eyes and witness the punishment of the wicked.

title: Psalms 91:9
content: 9 Because you have made the LORD your dwelling—my refuge, the Most High—

title: Psalms 91:10
content: 10 no evil will befall you, no plague will approach your tent.

title: Psalms 91:11
content: 11 For He will command His angels concerning you to guard you in all your ways.

title: Psalms 91:12
content: 12 They will lift you up in their hands, so that you will not strike your foot against a stone.

title: Psalms 91:13
content: 13 You will tread on the lion and cobra; you will trample the young lion and serpent.

title: Psalms 91:14
content: 14 “Because he loves Me, I will deliver him; because he knows My name, I will protect him.

title: Psalms 91:15
content: 15 When he calls out to Me, I will answer him; I will be with him in trouble. I will deliver him and honor him.

title: Psalms 91:16
content: 16 With long life I will satisfy him and show him My salvation.”

title: Psalms 92:0
content: 0 A Psalm. A song for the Sabbath day.

title: Psalms 92:1
content: 1 It is good to praise the LORD, and to sing praises to Your name, O Most High,

title: Psalms 92:2
content: 2 to proclaim Your loving devotion in the morning and Your faithfulness at night

title: Psalms 92:3
content: 3 with the ten-stringed harp and the melody of the lyre.

title: Psalms 92:4
content: 4 For You, O LORD, have made me glad by Your deeds; I sing for joy at the works of Your hands.

title: Psalms 92:5
content: 5 How great are Your works, O LORD, how deep are Your thoughts!

title: Psalms 92:6
content: 6 A senseless man does not know, and a fool does not understand,

title: Psalms 92:7
content: 7 that though the wicked sprout like grass, and all evildoers flourish, they will be forever destroyed.

title: Psalms 92:8
content: 8 But You, O LORD, are exalted forever!

title: Psalms 92:9
content: 9 For surely Your enemies, O LORD, surely Your enemies will perish; all evildoers will be scattered.

title: Psalms 92:10
content: 10 But You have exalted my horn like that of a wild ox; with fine oil I have been anointed.

title: Psalms 92:11
content: 11 My eyes see the downfall of my enemies; my ears hear the wailing of my wicked foes.

title: Psalms 92:12
content: 12 The righteous will flourish like a palm tree, and grow like a cedar in Lebanon.

title: Psalms 92:13
content: 13 Planted in the house of the LORD, they will flourish in the courts of our God.

title: Psalms 92:14
content: 14 In old age they will still bear fruit; healthy and green they will remain,

title: Psalms 92:15
content: 15 to proclaim, “The LORD is upright; He is my Rock, and in Him there is no unrighteousness.”

title: Psalms 93:1
content: 1 The LORD reigns! He is robed in majesty; the LORD has clothed and armed Himself with strength. The world indeed is firmly established; it cannot be moved.

title: Psalms 93:2
content: 2 Your throne was established long ago; You are from all eternity.

title: Psalms 93:3
content: 3 The floodwaters have risen, O LORD; the rivers have raised their voice; the seas lift up their pounding waves.

title: Psalms 93:4
content: 4 Above the roar of many waters—the mighty breakers of the sea—the LORD on high is majestic.

title: Psalms 93:5
content: 5 Your testimonies are fully confirmed; holiness adorns Your house, O LORD, for all the days to come.

title: Psalms 94:1
content: 1 O LORD, God of vengeance, O God of vengeance, shine forth.

title: Psalms 94:2
content: 2 Rise up, O Judge of the earth; render a reward to the proud.

title: Psalms 94:3
content: 3 How long will the wicked, O LORD, how long will the wicked exult?

title: Psalms 94:4
content: 4 They pour out arrogant words; all workers of iniquity boast.

title: Psalms 94:5
content: 5 They crush Your people, O LORD; they oppress Your heritage.

title: Psalms 94:6
content: 6 They kill the widow and the foreigner; they murder the fatherless.

title: Psalms 94:7
content: 7 They say, “The LORD does not see; the God of Jacob pays no heed.”

title: Psalms 94:8
content: 8 Take notice, O senseless among the people! O fools, when will you be wise?

title: Psalms 94:9
content: 9 He who affixed the ear, can He not hear? He who formed the eye, can He not see?

title: Psalms 94:10
content: 10 He who admonishes the nations, does He not discipline? He who teaches man, does He lack knowledge?

title: Psalms 94:11
content: 11 The LORD knows the thoughts of man, that they are futile.

title: Psalms 94:12
content: 12 Blessed is the man You discipline, O LORD, and teach from Your law,

title: Psalms 94:13
content: 13 to grant him relief from days of trouble, until a pit is dug for the wicked.

title: Psalms 94:14
content: 14 For the LORD will not forsake His people; He will never abandon His heritage.

title: Psalms 94:15
content: 15 Surely judgment will again be righteous, and all the upright in heart will follow it.

title: Psalms 94:16
content: 16 Who will rise up for me against the wicked? Who will stand for me against the workers of iniquity?

title: Psalms 94:17
content: 17 Unless the LORD had been my helper, I would soon have dwelt in the abode of silence.

title: Psalms 94:18
content: 18 If I say, “My foot is slipping,” Your loving devotion, O LORD, supports me.

title: Psalms 94:19
content: 19 When anxiety overwhelms me, Your consolation delights my soul.

title: Psalms 94:20
content: 20 Can a corrupt throne be Your ally—one devising mischief by decree?

title: Psalms 94:21
content: 21 They band together against the righteous and condemn the innocent to death.

title: Psalms 94:22
content: 22 But the LORD has been my stronghold, and my God is my rock of refuge.

title: Psalms 94:23
content: 23 He will bring upon them their own iniquity and destroy them for their wickedness. The LORD our God will destroy them.

title: Psalms 95:1
content: 1 Come, let us sing for joy to the LORD; let us shout to the Rock of our salvation!

title: Psalms 95:2
content: 2 Let us enter His presence with thanksgiving; let us make a joyful noise to Him in song.

title: Psalms 95:3
content: 3 For the LORD is a great God, a great King above all gods.

title: Psalms 95:4
content: 4 In His hand are the depths of the earth, and the mountain peaks belong to Him.

title: Psalms 95:5
content: 5 The sea is His, for He made it, and His hands formed the dry land.

title: Psalms 95:6
content: 6 O come, let us worship and bow down; let us kneel before the LORD our Maker.

title: Psalms 95:7
content: 7 For He is our God, and we are the people of His pasture, the sheep under His care. Today, if you hear His voice,

title: Psalms 95:8
content: 8 do not harden your hearts as you did at Meribah, in the day at Massah in the wilderness,

title: Psalms 95:9
content: 9 where your fathers tested and tried Me, though they had seen My work.

title: Psalms 95:10
content: 10 For forty years I was angry with that generation, and I said, “They are a people whose hearts go astray, and they have not known My ways.”

title: Psalms 95:11
content: 11 So I swore on oath in My anger, “They shall never enter My rest.”

title: Psalms 96:1
content: 1 Sing to the LORD a new song; sing to the LORD, all the earth.

title: Psalms 96:2
content: 2 Sing to the LORD, bless His name; proclaim His salvation day after day.

title: Psalms 96:3
content: 3 Declare His glory among the nations, His wonders among all peoples.

title: Psalms 96:4
content: 4 For great is the LORD, and greatly to be praised; He is to be feared above all gods.

title: Psalms 96:5
content: 5 For all the gods of the nations are idols, but it is the LORD who made the heavens.

title: Psalms 96:6
content: 6 Splendor and majesty are before Him; strength and beauty fill His sanctuary.

title: Psalms 96:7
content: 7 Ascribe to the LORD, O families of the nations, ascribe to the LORD glory and strength.

title: Psalms 96:8
content: 8 Ascribe to the LORD the glory due His name; bring an offering and enter His courts.

title: Psalms 96:9
content: 9 Worship the LORD in the splendor of His holiness; tremble before Him, all the earth.

title: Psalms 96:10
content: 10 Declare among the nations: “The LORD reigns!” The world is firmly established; it cannot be moved; He will judge the peoples with equity.

title: Psalms 96:11
content: 11 Let the heavens be glad and the earth rejoice; let the sea resound, and all that fills it.

title: Psalms 96:12
content: 12 Let the fields exult, and all that is in them. Then all the trees of the forest will sing for joy

title: Psalms 96:13
content: 13 before the LORD, for He is coming—He is coming to judge the earth. He will judge the world in righteousness and the peoples in His faithfulness.

title: Psalms 97:1
content: 1 The LORD reigns, let the earth rejoice; let the distant shores be glad.

title: Psalms 97:2
content: 2 Clouds and darkness surround Him; righteousness and justice are His throne’s foundation.

title: Psalms 97:3
content: 3 Fire goes before Him and consumes His foes on every side.

title: Psalms 97:4
content: 4 His lightning illuminates the world; the earth sees and trembles.

title: Psalms 97:5
content: 5 The mountains melt like wax at the presence of the LORD, before the Lord of all the earth.

title: Psalms 97:6
content: 6 The heavens proclaim His righteousness; all the peoples see His glory.

title: Psalms 97:7
content: 7 All worshipers of images are put to shame—those who boast in idols. Worship Him, all you gods!

title: Psalms 97:8
content: 8 Zion hears and rejoices, and the towns of Judah exult because of Your judgments, O LORD.

title: Psalms 97:9
content: 9 For You, O LORD, are Most High over all the earth; You are exalted far above all gods.

title: Psalms 97:10
content: 10 Hate evil, O you who love the LORD! He preserves the souls of His saints; He delivers them from the hand of the wicked.

title: Psalms 97:11
content: 11 Light shines on the righteous, gladness on the upright in heart.

title: Psalms 97:12
content: 12 Rejoice in the LORD, you righteous ones, and praise His holy name.

title: Psalms 98:0
content: 0 A Psalm.

title: Psalms 98:1
content: 1 Sing to the LORD a new song, for He has done wonders; His right hand and holy arm have gained Him the victory.

title: Psalms 98:2
content: 2 The LORD has proclaimed His salvation and revealed His righteousness to the nations.

title: Psalms 98:3
content: 3 He has remembered His love and faithfulness to the house of Israel; all the ends of the earth have seen the salvation of our God.

title: Psalms 98:4
content: 4 Make a joyful noise to the LORD, all the earth; break forth—let your cry ring out, and sing praises!

title: Psalms 98:5
content: 5 Sing praises to the LORD with the lyre, in melodious song with the harp.

title: Psalms 98:6
content: 6 With trumpets and the blast of the ram’s horn shout for joy before the LORD, the King.

title: Psalms 98:7
content: 7 Let the sea resound, and all that fills it, the world, and all who dwell in it.

title: Psalms 98:8
content: 8 Let the rivers clap their hands, let the mountains sing together for joy

title: Psalms 98:9
content: 9 before the LORD, for He comes to judge the earth. He will judge the world with righteousness and the peoples with equity.

title: Psalms 99:1
content: 1 The LORD reigns; let the nations tremble! He is enthroned above the cherubim; let the earth quake!

title: Psalms 99:2
content: 2 Great is the LORD in Zion; He is exalted above all the peoples.

title: Psalms 99:3
content: 3 Let them praise Your great and awesome name—He is holy!

title: Psalms 99:4
content: 4 The mighty King loves justice. You have established equity; You have exercised justice and righteousness in Jacob.

title: Psalms 99:5
content: 5 Exalt the LORD our God, and worship at His footstool; He is holy!

title: Psalms 99:6
content: 6 Moses and Aaron were among His priests; Samuel was among those who called on His name. They called to the LORD and He answered.

title: Psalms 99:7
content: 7 He spoke to them from the pillar of cloud; they kept His decrees and the statutes He gave them.

title: Psalms 99:8
content: 8 O LORD our God, You answered them. You were a forgiving God to them, yet an avenger of their misdeeds.

title: Psalms 99:9
content: 9 Exalt the LORD our God and worship at His holy mountain, for the LORD our God is holy.

title: Psalms 100:0
content: 0 A Psalm of thanksgiving.

title: Psalms 100:1
content: 1 Make a joyful noise to the LORD, all the earth.

title: Psalms 100:2
content: 2 Serve the LORD with gladness; come into His presence with joyful songs.

title: Psalms 100:3
content: 3 Know that the LORD is God. It is He who made us, and we are His; we are His people, and the sheep of His pasture.

title: Psalms 100:4
content: 4 Enter His gates with thanksgiving and His courts with praise; give thanks to Him and bless His name.

title: Psalms 100:5
content: 5 For the LORD is good, and His loving devotion endures forever; His faithfulness continues to all generations.

title: Psalms 101:0
content: 0 A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 101:1
content: 1 I will sing of Your loving devotion and justice; to You, O LORD, I will sing praises.

title: Psalms 101:2
content: 2 I will ponder the way that is blameless—when will You come to me? I will walk in my house with integrity of heart.

title: Psalms 101:3
content: 3 I will set no worthless thing before my eyes. I hate the work of those who fall away; it shall not cling to me.

title: Psalms 101:4
content: 4 A perverse heart shall depart from me; I will know nothing of evil.

title: Psalms 101:5
content: 5 Whoever slanders his neighbor in secret, I will put to silence; the one with haughty eyes and a proud heart, I will not endure.

title: Psalms 101:6
content: 6 My eyes favor the faithful of the land, that they may dwell with me; he who walks in the way of integrity shall minister to me.

title: Psalms 101:7
content: 7 No one who practices deceit shall dwell in my house; no one who tells lies shall stand in my presence.

title: Psalms 101:8
content: 8 Every morning I will remove all the wicked of the land, that I may cut off every evildoer from the city of the LORD.

title: Psalms 102:0
content: 0 A prayer of one who is afflicted, when he grows faint and pours out his lament before the LORD.

title: Psalms 102:1
content: 1 Hear my prayer, O LORD; let my cry for help come before You.

title: Psalms 102:2
content: 2 Do not hide Your face from me in my day of distress. Incline Your ear to me; answer me quickly when I call.

title: Psalms 102:3
content: 3 For my days vanish like smoke, and my bones burn like glowing embers.

title: Psalms 102:4
content: 4 My heart is afflicted, and withered like grass; I even forget to eat my bread.

title: Psalms 102:5
content: 5 Through my loud groaning my skin hangs on my bones.

title: Psalms 102:6
content: 6 I am like a desert owl, like an owl among the ruins.

title: Psalms 102:7
content: 7 I lie awake; I am like a lone bird on a housetop.

title: Psalms 102:8
content: 8 All day long my enemies taunt me; they ridicule me and curse me.

title: Psalms 102:9
content: 9 For I have eaten ashes like bread and mixed my drink with tears

title: Psalms 102:10
content: 10 because of Your indignation and wrath, for You have picked me up and cast me aside.

title: Psalms 102:11
content: 11 My days are like lengthening shadows, and I wither away like grass.

title: Psalms 102:12
content: 12 But You, O LORD, sit enthroned forever; Your renown endures to all generations.

title: Psalms 102:13
content: 13 You will rise up and have compassion on Zion, for it is time to show her favor—the appointed time has come.

title: Psalms 102:14
content: 14 For Your servants delight in her stones and take pity on her dust.

title: Psalms 102:15
content: 15 So the nations will fear the name of the LORD, and all the kings of the earth will fear Your glory.

title: Psalms 102:16
content: 16 For the LORD will rebuild Zion; He has appeared in His glory.

title: Psalms 102:17
content: 17 He will turn toward the prayer of the destitute; He will not despise their prayer.

title: Psalms 102:18
content: 18 Let this be written for the generation to come, so that a people not yet created may praise the LORD.

title: Psalms 102:19
content: 19 For He looked down from the heights of His sanctuary; the LORD gazed out from heaven to earth

title: Psalms 102:20
content: 20 to hear a prisoner’s groaning, to release those condemned to death,

title: Psalms 102:21
content: 21 that they may proclaim the name of the LORD in Zion and praise Him in Jerusalem,

title: Psalms 102:22
content: 22 when peoples and kingdoms assemble to serve the LORD.

title: Psalms 102:23
content: 23 He has broken my strength on the way; He has cut short my days.

title: Psalms 102:24
content: 24 I say: “O my God, do not take me in the midst of my days! Your years go on through all generations.

title: Psalms 102:25
content: 25 In the beginning You laid the foundations of the earth, and the heavens are the work of Your hands.

title: Psalms 102:26
content: 26 They will perish, but You remain; they will all wear out like a garment. Like clothing You will change them, and they will be passed on.

title: Psalms 102:27
content: 27 But You remain the same, and Your years will never end.

title: Psalms 102:28
content: 28 The children of Your servants will dwell securely, and their descendants will be established before You.”

title: Psalms 103:0
content: 0 Of David.

title: Psalms 103:1
content: 1 Bless the LORD, O my soul; all that is within me, bless His holy name.

title: Psalms 103:2
content: 2 Bless the LORD, O my soul, and do not forget all His kind deeds—

title: Psalms 103:3
content: 3 He who forgives all your iniquities and heals all your diseases,

title: Psalms 103:4
content: 4 who redeems your life from the Pit and crowns you with loving devotion and compassion,

title: Psalms 103:5
content: 5 who satisfies you with good things, so that your youth is renewed like the eagle’s.

title: Psalms 103:6
content: 6 The LORD executes righteousness and justice for all the oppressed.

title: Psalms 103:7
content: 7 He made known His ways to Moses, His deeds to the people of Israel.

title: Psalms 103:8
content: 8 The LORD is compassionate and gracious, slow to anger, abounding in loving devotion.

title: Psalms 103:9
content: 9 He will not always accuse us, nor harbor His anger forever.

title: Psalms 103:10
content: 10 He has not dealt with us according to our sins or repaid us according to our iniquities.

title: Psalms 103:11
content: 11 For as high as the heavens are above the earth, so great is His loving devotion for those who fear Him.

title: Psalms 103:12
content: 12 As far as the east is from the west, so far has He removed our transgressions from us.

title: Psalms 103:13
content: 13 As a father has compassion on his children, so the LORD has compassion on those who fear Him.

title: Psalms 103:14
content: 14 For He knows our frame; He is mindful that we are dust.

title: Psalms 103:15
content: 15 As for man, his days are like grass—he blooms like a flower of the field;

title: Psalms 103:16
content: 16 when the wind passes over, it vanishes, and its place remembers it no more.

title: Psalms 103:17
content: 17 But from everlasting to everlasting the loving devotion of the LORD extends to those who fear Him, and His righteousness to their children’s children—

title: Psalms 103:18
content: 18 to those who keep His covenant and remember to obey His precepts.

title: Psalms 103:19
content: 19 The LORD has established His throne in heaven, and His kingdom rules over all.

title: Psalms 103:20
content: 20 Bless the LORD, all His angels mighty in strength who carry out His word, who hearken to the voice of His command.

title: Psalms 103:21
content: 21 Bless the LORD, all His hosts, you servants who do His will.

title: Psalms 103:22
content: 22 Bless the LORD, all His works in all places of His dominion. Bless the LORD, O my soul!

title: Psalms 104:1
content: 1 Bless the LORD, O my soul! O LORD my God, You are very great; You are clothed with splendor and majesty.

title: Psalms 104:2
content: 2 He wraps Himself in light as with a garment; He stretches out the heavens like a tent,

title: Psalms 104:3
content: 3 laying the beams of His chambers in the waters above, making the clouds His chariot, walking on the wings of the wind.

title: Psalms 104:4
content: 4 He makes the winds His messengers, flames of fire His servants.

title: Psalms 104:5
content: 5 He set the earth on its foundations, never to be moved.

title: Psalms 104:6
content: 6 You covered it with the deep like a garment; the waters stood above the mountains.

title: Psalms 104:7
content: 7 At Your rebuke the waters fled; at the sound of Your thunder they hurried away—

title: Psalms 104:8
content: 8 the mountains rose and the valleys sank to the place You assigned for them—

title: Psalms 104:9
content: 9 You set a boundary they cannot cross, that they may never again cover the earth.

title: Psalms 104:10
content: 10 He sends forth springs in the valleys; they flow between the mountains.

title: Psalms 104:11
content: 11 They give drink to every beast of the field; the wild donkeys quench their thirst.

title: Psalms 104:12
content: 12 The birds of the air nest beside the springs; they sing among the branches.

title: Psalms 104:13
content: 13 He waters the mountains from His chambers; the earth is satisfied by the fruit of His works.

title: Psalms 104:14
content: 14 He makes the grass grow for the livestock and provides crops for man to cultivate, bringing forth food from the earth:

title: Psalms 104:15
content: 15 wine that gladdens the heart of man, oil that makes his face to shine, and bread that sustains his heart.

title: Psalms 104:16
content: 16 The trees of the LORD have their fill, the cedars of Lebanon that He planted,

title: Psalms 104:17
content: 17 where the birds build their nests; the stork makes her home in the cypresses.

title: Psalms 104:18
content: 18 The high mountains are for the wild goats, the cliffs a refuge for the rock badgers.

title: Psalms 104:19
content: 19 He made the moon to mark the seasons; the sun knows when to set.

title: Psalms 104:20
content: 20 You bring darkness, and it becomes night, when all the beasts of the forest prowl.

title: Psalms 104:21
content: 21 The young lions roar for their prey and seek their food from God.

title: Psalms 104:22
content: 22 The sun rises, and they withdraw; they lie down in their dens.

title: Psalms 104:23
content: 23 Man goes forth to his work and to his labor until evening.

title: Psalms 104:24
content: 24 How many are Your works, O LORD! In wisdom You have made them all; the earth is full of Your creatures.

title: Psalms 104:25
content: 25 Here is the sea, vast and wide, teeming with creatures beyond number, living things both great and small.

title: Psalms 104:26
content: 26 There the ships pass, and Leviathan, which You formed to frolic there.

title: Psalms 104:27
content: 27 All creatures look to You to give them their food in due season.

title: Psalms 104:28
content: 28 When You give it to them, they gather it up; when You open Your hand, they are satisfied with good things.

title: Psalms 104:29
content: 29 When You hide Your face, they are terrified; when You take away their breath, they die and return to dust.

title: Psalms 104:30
content: 30 When You send Your Spirit, they are created, and You renew the face of the earth.

title: Psalms 104:31
content: 31 May the glory of the LORD endure forever; may the LORD rejoice in His works.

title: Psalms 104:32
content: 32 He looks on the earth, and it trembles; He touches the mountains, and they smolder.

title: Psalms 104:33
content: 33 I will sing to the LORD all my life; I will sing praise to my God while I have my being.

title: Psalms 104:34
content: 34 May my meditation be pleasing to Him, for I rejoice in the LORD.

title: Psalms 104:35
content: 35 May sinners vanish from the earth and the wicked be no more. Bless the LORD, O my soul. Hallelujah!

title: Psalms 105:1
content: 1 Give thanks to the LORD, call upon His name; make known His deeds among the nations.

title: Psalms 105:2
content: 2 Sing to Him, sing praises to Him; tell of all His wonders.

title: Psalms 105:3
content: 3 Glory in His holy name; let the hearts of those who seek the LORD rejoice.

title: Psalms 105:4
content: 4 Seek out the LORD and His strength; seek His face always.

title: Psalms 105:5
content: 5 Remember the wonders He has done, His marvels, and the judgments He has pronounced,

title: Psalms 105:6
content: 6 O offspring of His servant Abraham, O sons of Jacob, His chosen ones.

title: Psalms 105:7
content: 7 He is the LORD our God; His judgments carry throughout the earth.

title: Psalms 105:8
content: 8 He remembers His covenant forever, the word He ordained for a thousand generations—

title: Psalms 105:9
content: 9 the covenant He made with Abraham, and the oath He swore to Isaac.

title: Psalms 105:10
content: 10 He confirmed it to Jacob as a decree, to Israel as an everlasting covenant:

title: Psalms 105:11
content: 11 “I will give you the land of Canaan as the portion of your inheritance.”

title: Psalms 105:12
content: 12 When they were few in number, few indeed, and strangers in the land,

title: Psalms 105:13
content: 13 they wandered from nation to nation, from one kingdom to another.

title: Psalms 105:14
content: 14 He let no man oppress them; He rebuked kings on their behalf:

title: Psalms 105:15
content: 15 “Do not touch My anointed ones! Do no harm to My prophets!”

title: Psalms 105:16
content: 16 He called down famine on the land and cut off all their supplies of food.

title: Psalms 105:17
content: 17 He sent a man before them—Joseph, sold as a slave.

title: Psalms 105:18
content: 18 They bruised his feet with shackles and placed his neck in irons,

title: Psalms 105:19
content: 19 until his prediction came true and the word of the LORD proved him right.

title: Psalms 105:20
content: 20 The king sent and released him; the ruler of peoples set him free.

title: Psalms 105:21
content: 21 He made him master of his household, ruler over all his substance,

title: Psalms 105:22
content: 22 to instruct his princes as he pleased and teach his elders wisdom.

title: Psalms 105:23
content: 23 Then Israel entered Egypt; Jacob dwelt in the land of Ham.

title: Psalms 105:24
content: 24 And the LORD made His people very fruitful, more numerous than their foes,

title: Psalms 105:25
content: 25 whose hearts He turned to hate His people, to conspire against His servants.

title: Psalms 105:26
content: 26 He sent Moses His servant, and Aaron, whom He had chosen.

title: Psalms 105:27
content: 27 They performed His miraculous signs among them, and wonders in the land of Ham.

title: Psalms 105:28
content: 28 He sent darkness, and it became dark—yet they defied His words.

title: Psalms 105:29
content: 29 He turned their waters to blood and caused their fish to die.

title: Psalms 105:30
content: 30 Their land teemed with frogs, even in their royal chambers.

title: Psalms 105:31
content: 31 He spoke, and insects swarmed—gnats throughout their country.

title: Psalms 105:32
content: 32 He gave them hail for rain, with lightning throughout their land.

title: Psalms 105:33
content: 33 He struck their vines and fig trees and shattered the trees of their country.

title: Psalms 105:34
content: 34 He spoke, and the locusts came—young locusts without number.

title: Psalms 105:35
content: 35 They devoured every plant in their land and consumed the produce of their soil.

title: Psalms 105:36
content: 36 Then He struck all the firstborn in their land, the firstfruits of all their vigor.

title: Psalms 105:37
content: 37 He brought Israel out with silver and gold, and none among His tribes stumbled.

title: Psalms 105:38
content: 38 Egypt was glad when they departed, for the dread of Israel had fallen on them.

title: Psalms 105:39
content: 39 He spread a cloud as a covering and a fire to light up the night.

title: Psalms 105:40
content: 40 They asked, and He brought quail and satisfied them with the bread of heaven.

title: Psalms 105:41
content: 41 He opened a rock, and water gushed out; it flowed like a river in the desert.

title: Psalms 105:42
content: 42 For He remembered His holy promise to Abraham His servant.

title: Psalms 105:43
content: 43 He brought forth His people with rejoicing, His chosen with shouts of joy.

title: Psalms 105:44
content: 44 He gave them the lands of the nations, that they might inherit the fruit of others’ labor,

title: Psalms 105:45
content: 45 that they might keep His statutes and obey His laws. Hallelujah!

title: Psalms 106:1
content: 1 Hallelujah! Give thanks to the LORD, for He is good; His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 106:2
content: 2 Who can describe the mighty acts of the LORD or fully proclaim His praise?

title: Psalms 106:3
content: 3 Blessed are those who uphold justice, who practice righteousness at all times.

title: Psalms 106:4
content: 4 Remember me, O LORD, in Your favor to Your people; visit me with Your salvation,

title: Psalms 106:5
content: 5 that I may see the prosperity of Your chosen ones, and rejoice in the gladness of Your nation, and give glory with Your inheritance.

title: Psalms 106:6
content: 6 We have sinned like our fathers; we have done wrong and acted wickedly.

title: Psalms 106:7
content: 7 Our fathers in Egypt did not grasp Your wonders or remember Your abundant kindness; but they rebelled by the sea, there at the Red Sea.

title: Psalms 106:8
content: 8 Yet He saved them for the sake of His name, to make His power known.

title: Psalms 106:9
content: 9 He rebuked the Red Sea, and it dried up; He led them through the depths as through a desert.

title: Psalms 106:10
content: 10 He saved them from the hand that hated them; He redeemed them from the hand of the enemy.

title: Psalms 106:11
content: 11 The waters covered their foes; not one of them remained.

title: Psalms 106:12
content: 12 Then they believed His promises and sang His praise.

title: Psalms 106:13
content: 13 Yet they soon forgot His works and failed to wait for His counsel.

title: Psalms 106:14
content: 14 They craved intensely in the wilderness and tested God in the desert.

title: Psalms 106:15
content: 15 So He granted their request, but sent a wasting disease upon them.

title: Psalms 106:16
content: 16 In the camp they envied Moses, as well as Aaron, the holy one of the LORD.

title: Psalms 106:17
content: 17 The earth opened up and swallowed Dathan; it covered the assembly of Abiram.

title: Psalms 106:18
content: 18 Then fire blazed through their company; flames consumed the wicked.

title: Psalms 106:19
content: 19 At Horeb they made a calf and worshiped a molten image.

title: Psalms 106:20
content: 20 They exchanged their Glory for the image of a grass-eating ox.

title: Psalms 106:21
content: 21 They forgot God their Savior, who did great things in Egypt,

title: Psalms 106:22
content: 22 wondrous works in the land of Ham, and awesome deeds by the Red Sea.

title: Psalms 106:23
content: 23 So He said He would destroy them—had not Moses His chosen one stood before Him in the breach to divert His wrath from destroying them.

title: Psalms 106:24
content: 24 They despised the pleasant land; they did not believe His promise.

title: Psalms 106:25
content: 25 They grumbled in their tents and did not listen to the voice of the LORD.

title: Psalms 106:26
content: 26 So He raised His hand and swore to cast them down in the wilderness,

title: Psalms 106:27
content: 27 to disperse their offspring among the nations and scatter them throughout the lands.

title: Psalms 106:28
content: 28 They yoked themselves to Baal of Peor and ate sacrifices offered to lifeless gods.

title: Psalms 106:29
content: 29 So they provoked the LORD to anger with their deeds, and a plague broke out among them.

title: Psalms 106:30
content: 30 But Phinehas stood and intervened, and the plague was restrained.

title: Psalms 106:31
content: 31 It was credited to him as righteousness for endless generations to come.

title: Psalms 106:32
content: 32 At the waters of Meribah they angered the LORD, and trouble came to Moses because of them.

title: Psalms 106:33
content: 33 For they rebelled against His Spirit, and Moses spoke rashly with his lips.

title: Psalms 106:34
content: 34 They did not destroy the peoples as the LORD had commanded them,

title: Psalms 106:35
content: 35 but they mingled with the nations and adopted their customs.

title: Psalms 106:36
content: 36 They worshiped their idols, which became a snare to them.

title: Psalms 106:37
content: 37 They sacrificed their sons and their daughters to demons.

title: Psalms 106:38
content: 38 They shed innocent blood—the blood of their sons and daughters, whom they sacrificed to the idols of Canaan, and the land was polluted with blood.

title: Psalms 106:39
content: 39 They defiled themselves by their actions and prostituted themselves by their deeds.

title: Psalms 106:40
content: 40 So the anger of the LORD burned against His people, and He abhorred His own inheritance.

title: Psalms 106:41
content: 41 He delivered them into the hand of the nations, and those who hated them ruled over them.

title: Psalms 106:42
content: 42 Their enemies oppressed them and subdued them under their hand.

title: Psalms 106:43
content: 43 Many times He rescued them, but they were bent on rebellion and sank down in their iniquity.

title: Psalms 106:44
content: 44 Nevertheless He heard their cry; He took note of their distress.

title: Psalms 106:45
content: 45 And He remembered His covenant with them, and relented by the abundance of His loving devotion.

title: Psalms 106:46
content: 46 He made them objects of compassion to all who held them captive.

title: Psalms 106:47
content: 47 Save us, O LORD our God, and gather us from the nations, that we may give thanks to Your holy name, that we may glory in Your praise.

title: Psalms 106:48
content: 48 Blessed be the LORD, the God of Israel, from everlasting to everlasting. Let all the people say, “Amen!” Hallelujah!

title: Psalms 107:1
content: 1 Give thanks to the LORD, for He is good; His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 107:2
content: 2 Let the redeemed of the LORD say so, whom He has redeemed from the hand of the enemy

title: Psalms 107:3
content: 3 and gathered from the lands, from east and west, from north and south.

title: Psalms 107:4
content: 4 Some wandered in desert wastelands, finding no path to a city in which to dwell.

title: Psalms 107:5
content: 5 They were hungry and thirsty; their soul fainted within them.

title: Psalms 107:6
content: 6 Then they cried out to the LORD in their trouble, and He delivered them from their distress.

title: Psalms 107:7
content: 7 He led them on a straight path to reach a city where they could live.

title: Psalms 107:8
content: 8 Let them give thanks to the LORD for His loving devotion and His wonders to the sons of men.

title: Psalms 107:9
content: 9 For He satisfies the thirsty and fills the hungry with good things.

title: Psalms 107:10
content: 10 Some sat in darkness and in the shadow of death, prisoners in affliction and chains,

title: Psalms 107:11
content: 11 because they rebelled against the words of God and despised the counsel of the Most High.

title: Psalms 107:12
content: 12 He humbled their hearts with hard labor; they stumbled, and there was no one to help.

title: Psalms 107:13
content: 13 Then they cried out to the LORD in their trouble, and He saved them from their distress.

title: Psalms 107:14
content: 14 He brought them out of darkness and the shadow of death and broke away their chains.

title: Psalms 107:15
content: 15 Let them give thanks to the LORD for His loving devotion and His wonders to the sons of men.

title: Psalms 107:16
content: 16 For He has broken down the gates of bronze and cut through the bars of iron.

title: Psalms 107:17
content: 17 Fools, in their rebellious ways, and through their iniquities, suffered affliction.

title: Psalms 107:18
content: 18 They loathed all food and drew near to the gates of death.

title: Psalms 107:19
content: 19 Then they cried out to the LORD in their trouble, and He saved them from their distress.

title: Psalms 107:20
content: 20 He sent forth His word and healed them; He rescued them from the Pit.

title: Psalms 107:21
content: 21 Let them give thanks to the LORD for His loving devotion and His wonders to the sons of men.

title: Psalms 107:22
content: 22 Let them offer sacrifices of thanksgiving and declare His works with rejoicing.

title: Psalms 107:23
content: 23 Others went out to sea in ships, conducting trade on the mighty waters.

title: Psalms 107:24
content: 24 They saw the works of the LORD, and His wonders in the deep.

title: Psalms 107:25
content: 25 For He spoke and raised a tempest that lifted the waves of the sea.

title: Psalms 107:26
content: 26 They mounted up to the heavens, then sunk to the depths; their courage melted in their anguish.

title: Psalms 107:27
content: 27 They reeled and staggered like drunkards, and all their skill was useless.

title: Psalms 107:28
content: 28 Then they cried out to the LORD in their trouble, and He brought them out of their distress.

title: Psalms 107:29
content: 29 He calmed the storm to a whisper, and the waves of the sea were hushed.

title: Psalms 107:30
content: 30 They rejoiced in the silence, and He guided them to the harbor they desired.

title: Psalms 107:31
content: 31 Let them give thanks to the LORD for His loving devotion and His wonders to the sons of men.

title: Psalms 107:32
content: 32 Let them exalt Him in the assembly of the people and praise Him in the council of the elders.

title: Psalms 107:33
content: 33 He turns rivers into deserts, springs of water into thirsty ground,

title: Psalms 107:34
content: 34 and fruitful land into fields of salt, because of the wickedness of its dwellers.

title: Psalms 107:35
content: 35 He turns a desert into pools of water and a dry land into flowing springs.

title: Psalms 107:36
content: 36 He causes the hungry to settle there, that they may establish a city in which to dwell.

title: Psalms 107:37
content: 37 They sow fields and plant vineyards that yield a fruitful harvest.

title: Psalms 107:38
content: 38 He blesses them, and they multiply greatly; He does not let their herds diminish.

title: Psalms 107:39
content: 39 When they are decreased and humbled by oppression, evil, and sorrow,

title: Psalms 107:40
content: 40 He pours out contempt on the nobles and makes them wander in a trackless wasteland.

title: Psalms 107:41
content: 41 But He lifts the needy from affliction and increases their families like flocks.

title: Psalms 107:42
content: 42 The upright see and rejoice, and all iniquity shuts its mouth.

title: Psalms 107:43
content: 43 Let him who is wise pay heed to these things and consider the loving devotion of the LORD.

title: Psalms 108:0
content: 0 A song. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 108:1
content: 1 My heart is steadfast, O God; I will sing and make music with all my being.

title: Psalms 108:2
content: 2 Awake, O harp and lyre! I will awaken the dawn.

title: Psalms 108:3
content: 3 I will praise You, O LORD, among the nations; I will sing Your praises among the peoples.

title: Psalms 108:4
content: 4 For Your loving devotion extends beyond the heavens, and Your faithfulness reaches to the clouds.

title: Psalms 108:5
content: 5 Be exalted, O God, above the heavens; may Your glory cover all the earth.

title: Psalms 108:6
content: 6 Respond and save us with Your right hand, that Your beloved may be delivered.

title: Psalms 108:7
content: 7 God has spoken from His sanctuary: “I will triumph! I will parcel out Shechem and apportion the Valley of Succoth.

title: Psalms 108:8
content: 8 Gilead is Mine, and Manasseh is Mine; Ephraim is My helmet, Judah is My scepter.

title: Psalms 108:9
content: 9 Moab is My washbasin; upon Edom I toss My sandal; over Philistia I shout in triumph.”

title: Psalms 108:10
content: 10 Who will bring me to the fortified city? Who will lead me to Edom?

title: Psalms 108:11
content: 11 Have You not rejected us, O God? Will You no longer march out, O God, with our armies?

title: Psalms 108:12
content: 12 Give us aid against the enemy, for the help of man is worthless.

title: Psalms 108:13
content: 13 With God we will perform with valor, and He will trample our enemies.

title: Psalms 109:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 109:1
content: 1 O God of my praise, be not silent.

title: Psalms 109:2
content: 2 For wicked and deceitful mouths open against me; they speak against me with lying tongues.

title: Psalms 109:3
content: 3 They surround me with hateful words and attack me without cause.

title: Psalms 109:4
content: 4 In return for my love they accuse me, but I am a man of prayer.

title: Psalms 109:5
content: 5 They repay me evil for good, and hatred for my love.

title: Psalms 109:6
content: 6 Set over him a wicked man; let an accuser stand at his right hand.

title: Psalms 109:7
content: 7 When he is tried, let him be found guilty, and may his prayer be regarded as sin.

title: Psalms 109:8
content: 8 May his days be few; may another take his position.

title: Psalms 109:9
content: 9 May his children be fatherless and his wife a widow.

title: Psalms 109:10
content: 10 May his children wander as beggars, seeking sustenance far from their ruined homes.

title: Psalms 109:11
content: 11 May the creditor seize all he owns, and strangers plunder the fruits of his labor.

title: Psalms 109:12
content: 12 May there be no one to extend kindness to him, and no one to favor his fatherless children.

title: Psalms 109:13
content: 13 May his descendants be cut off; may their name be blotted out from the next generation.

title: Psalms 109:14
content: 14 May the iniquity of his fathers be remembered before the LORD, and the sin of his mother never be blotted out.

title: Psalms 109:15
content: 15 May their sins always remain before the LORD, that He may cut off their memory from the earth.

title: Psalms 109:16
content: 16 For he never thought to show kindness, but pursued the poor and needy and brokenhearted, even to their death.

title: Psalms 109:17
content: 17 The cursing that he loved, may it fall on him; the blessing in which he refused to delight, may it be far from him.

title: Psalms 109:18
content: 18 The cursing that he wore like a coat, may it soak into his body like water, and into his bones like oil.

title: Psalms 109:19
content: 19 May it be like a robe wrapped about him, like a belt tied forever around him.

title: Psalms 109:20
content: 20 May this be the LORD’s reward to my accusers, to those who speak evil against me.

title: Psalms 109:21
content: 21 But You, O GOD, the Lord, deal kindly with me for the sake of Your name; deliver me by the goodness of Your loving devotion.

title: Psalms 109:22
content: 22 For I am poor and needy; my heart is wounded within me.

title: Psalms 109:23
content: 23 I am fading away like a lengthening shadow; I am shaken off like a locust.

title: Psalms 109:24
content: 24 My knees are weak from fasting, and my body grows lean and gaunt.

title: Psalms 109:25
content: 25 I am an object of scorn to my accusers; when they see me, they shake their heads.

title: Psalms 109:26
content: 26 Help me, O LORD my God; save me according to Your loving devotion.

title: Psalms 109:27
content: 27 Let them know that this is Your hand, that You, O LORD, have done it.

title: Psalms 109:28
content: 28 Though they curse, You will bless. When they rise up, they will be put to shame, but Your servant will rejoice.

title: Psalms 109:29
content: 29 May my accusers be clothed with disgrace; may they wear their shame like a robe.

title: Psalms 109:30
content: 30 With my mouth I will thank the LORD profusely; I will praise Him in the presence of many.

title: Psalms 109:31
content: 31 For He stands at the right hand of the needy one, to save him from the condemners of his soul.

title: Psalms 110:0
content: 0 A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 110:1
content: 1 The LORD said to my Lord: “Sit at My right hand until I make Your enemies a footstool for Your feet.”

title: Psalms 110:2
content: 2 The LORD extends Your mighty scepter from Zion: “Rule in the midst of Your enemies.”

title: Psalms 110:3
content: 3 Your people shall be willing on Your day of battle. Arrayed in holy splendor, from the womb of the dawn, to You belongs the dew of Your youth.

title: Psalms 110:4
content: 4 The LORD has sworn and will not change His mind: “You are a priest forever in the order of Melchizedek.”

title: Psalms 110:5
content: 5 The Lord is at Your right hand; He will crush kings in the day of His wrath.

title: Psalms 110:6
content: 6 He will judge the nations, heaping up the dead; He will crush the leaders far and wide.

title: Psalms 110:7
content: 7 He will drink from the brook by the road; therefore He will lift up His head.

title: Psalms 111:1
content: 1 Hallelujah! I will give thanks to the LORD with all my heart in the council of the upright and in the assembly.

title: Psalms 111:2
content: 2 Great are the works of the LORD; they are pondered by all who delight in them.

title: Psalms 111:3
content: 3 Splendid and majestic is His work; His righteousness endures forever.

title: Psalms 111:4
content: 4 He has caused His wonders to be remembered; the LORD is gracious and compassionate.

title: Psalms 111:5
content: 5 He provides food for those who fear Him; He remembers His covenant forever.

title: Psalms 111:6
content: 6 He has shown His people the power of His works by giving them the inheritance of the nations.

title: Psalms 111:7
content: 7 The works of His hands are truth and justice; all His precepts are trustworthy.

title: Psalms 111:8
content: 8 They are upheld forever and ever, enacted in truth and uprightness.

title: Psalms 111:9
content: 9 He has sent redemption to His people; He has ordained His covenant forever; holy and awesome is His name.

title: Psalms 111:10
content: 10 The fear of the LORD is the beginning of wisdom; all who follow His precepts gain rich understanding. His praise endures forever!

title: Psalms 112:1
content: 1 Hallelujah! Blessed is the man who fears the LORD, who greatly delights in His commandments.

title: Psalms 112:2
content: 2 His descendants will be mighty in the land; the generation of the upright will be blessed.

title: Psalms 112:3
content: 3 Wealth and riches are in his house, and his righteousness endures forever.

title: Psalms 112:4
content: 4 Light dawns in the darkness for the upright—for the gracious, compassionate, and righteous.

title: Psalms 112:5
content: 5 It is well with the man who is generous and lends freely, whose affairs are guided by justice.

title: Psalms 112:6
content: 6 Surely he will never be shaken; the righteous man will be remembered forever.

title: Psalms 112:7
content: 7 He does not fear bad news; his heart is steadfast, trusting in the LORD.

title: Psalms 112:8
content: 8 His heart is assured; he does not fear, until he looks in triumph on his foes.

title: Psalms 112:9
content: 9 He has scattered abroad his gifts to the poor; his righteousness endures forever; his horn will be lifted high in honor.

title: Psalms 112:10
content: 10 The wicked man will see and be grieved; he will gnash his teeth and waste away; the desires of the wicked will perish.

title: Psalms 113:1
content: 1 Hallelujah! Give praise, O servants of the LORD; praise the name of the LORD.

title: Psalms 113:2
content: 2 Blessed be the name of the LORD both now and forevermore.

title: Psalms 113:3
content: 3 From where the sun rises to where it sets, the name of the LORD is praised.

title: Psalms 113:4
content: 4 The LORD is exalted over all the nations, His glory above the heavens.

title: Psalms 113:5
content: 5 Who is like the LORD our God, the One enthroned on high?

title: Psalms 113:6
content: 6 He humbles Himself to behold the heavens and the earth.

title: Psalms 113:7
content: 7 He raises the poor from the dust and lifts the needy from the dump

title: Psalms 113:8
content: 8 to seat them with nobles, with the princes of His people.

title: Psalms 113:9
content: 9 He settles the barren woman in her home as a joyful mother to her children. Hallelujah!

title: Psalms 114:1
content: 1 When Israel departed from Egypt, the house of Jacob from a people of foreign tongue,

title: Psalms 114:2
content: 2 Judah became God’s sanctuary, Israel His dominion.

title: Psalms 114:3
content: 3 The sea observed and fled; the Jordan turned back;

title: Psalms 114:4
content: 4 the mountains skipped like rams, the hills like lambs.

title: Psalms 114:5
content: 5 Why was it, O sea, that you fled, O Jordan, that you turned back,

title: Psalms 114:6
content: 6 O mountains, that you skipped like rams, O hills, like lambs?

title: Psalms 114:7
content: 7 Tremble, O earth, at the presence of the Lord, at the presence of the God of Jacob,

title: Psalms 114:8
content: 8 who turned the rock into a pool, the flint into a fountain of water!

title: Psalms 115:1
content: 1 Not to us, O LORD, not to us, but to Your name be the glory, because of Your loving devotion, because of Your faithfulness.

title: Psalms 115:2
content: 2 Why should the nations say, “Where is their God?”

title: Psalms 115:3
content: 3 Our God is in heaven; He does as He pleases.

title: Psalms 115:4
content: 4 Their idols are silver and gold, made by the hands of men.

title: Psalms 115:5
content: 5 They have mouths, but cannot speak; they have eyes, but cannot see;

title: Psalms 115:6
content: 6 they have ears, but cannot hear; they have noses, but cannot smell;

title: Psalms 115:7
content: 7 they have hands, but cannot feel; they have feet, but cannot walk; they cannot even clear their throats.

title: Psalms 115:8
content: 8 Those who make them become like them, as do all who trust in them.

title: Psalms 115:9
content: 9 O Israel, trust in the LORD! He is their help and shield.

title: Psalms 115:10
content: 10 O house of Aaron, trust in the LORD! He is their help and shield.

title: Psalms 115:11
content: 11 You who fear the LORD, trust in the LORD! He is their help and shield.

title: Psalms 115:12
content: 12 The LORD is mindful of us; He will bless us. He will bless the house of Israel; He will bless the house of Aaron;

title: Psalms 115:13
content: 13 He will bless those who fear the LORD—small and great alike.

title: Psalms 115:14
content: 14 May the LORD give you increase, both you and your children.

title: Psalms 115:15
content: 15 May you be blessed by the LORD, the Maker of heaven and earth.

title: Psalms 115:16
content: 16 The highest heavens belong to the LORD, but the earth He has given to mankind.

title: Psalms 115:17
content: 17 It is not the dead who praise the LORD, nor any who descend into silence.

title: Psalms 115:18
content: 18 But it is we who will bless the LORD, both now and forevermore. Hallelujah!

title: Psalms 116:1
content: 1 I love the LORD, for He has heard my voice—my appeal for mercy.

title: Psalms 116:2
content: 2 Because He has inclined His ear to me, I will call on Him as long as I live.

title: Psalms 116:3
content: 3 The ropes of death entangled me; the anguish of Sheol overcame me; I was confronted by trouble and sorrow.

title: Psalms 116:4
content: 4 Then I called on the name of the LORD: “O LORD, deliver my soul!”

title: Psalms 116:5
content: 5 The LORD is gracious and righteous; our God is full of compassion.

title: Psalms 116:6
content: 6 The LORD preserves the simplehearted; I was helpless, and He saved me.

title: Psalms 116:7
content: 7 Return to your rest, O my soul, for the LORD has been good to you.

title: Psalms 116:8
content: 8 For You have delivered my soul from death, my eyes from tears, my feet from stumbling.

title: Psalms 116:9
content: 9 I will walk before the LORD in the land of the living.

title: Psalms 116:10
content: 10 I believed, therefore I said, “I am greatly afflicted.”

title: Psalms 116:11
content: 11 In my alarm I said, “All men are liars!”

title: Psalms 116:12
content: 12 How can I repay the LORD for all His goodness to me?

title: Psalms 116:13
content: 13 I will lift the cup of salvation and call on the name of the LORD.

title: Psalms 116:14
content: 14 I will fulfill my vows to the LORD in the presence of all His people.

title: Psalms 116:15
content: 15 Precious in the sight of the LORD is the death of His saints.

title: Psalms 116:16
content: 16 Truly, O LORD, I am Your servant; I am Your servant, the son of Your maidservant; You have broken my bonds.

title: Psalms 116:17
content: 17 I will offer to You a sacrifice of thanksgiving and call on the name of the LORD.

title: Psalms 116:18
content: 18 I will fulfill my vows to the LORD in the presence of all His people,

title: Psalms 116:19
content: 19 in the courts of the LORD’s house, in your midst, O Jerusalem. Hallelujah!

title: Psalms 117:1
content: 1 Praise the LORD, all you nations! Extol Him, all you peoples!

title: Psalms 117:2
content: 2 For great is His loving devotion toward us, and the faithfulness of the LORD endures forever. Hallelujah!

title: Psalms 118:1
content: 1 Give thanks to the LORD, for He is good; His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 118:2
content: 2 Let Israel say, “His loving devotion endures forever.”

title: Psalms 118:3
content: 3 Let the house of Aaron say, “His loving devotion endures forever.”

title: Psalms 118:4
content: 4 Let those who fear the LORD say, “His loving devotion endures forever.”

title: Psalms 118:5
content: 5 In my distress I called to the LORD, and He answered and set me free.

title: Psalms 118:6
content: 6 The LORD is on my side; I will not be afraid. What can man do to me?

title: Psalms 118:7
content: 7 The LORD is on my side; He is my helper. Therefore I will look in triumph on those who hate me.

title: Psalms 118:8
content: 8 It is better to take refuge in the LORD than to trust in man.

title: Psalms 118:9
content: 9 It is better to take refuge in the LORD than to trust in princes.

title: Psalms 118:10
content: 10 All the nations surrounded me, but in the name of the LORD I cut them off.

title: Psalms 118:11
content: 11 They surrounded me on every side, but in the name of the LORD I cut them off.

title: Psalms 118:12
content: 12 They swarmed around me like bees, but they were extinguished like burning thorns; in the name of the LORD I cut them off.

title: Psalms 118:13
content: 13 I was pushed so hard I was falling, but the LORD helped me.

title: Psalms 118:14
content: 14 The LORD is my strength and my song, and He has become my salvation.

title: Psalms 118:15
content: 15 Shouts of joy and salvation resound in the tents of the righteous: “The right hand of the LORD performs with valor!

title: Psalms 118:16
content: 16 The right hand of the LORD is exalted! The right hand of the LORD performs with valor!”

title: Psalms 118:17
content: 17 I will not die, but I will live and proclaim what the LORD has done.

title: Psalms 118:18
content: 18 The LORD disciplined me severely, but He has not given me over to death.

title: Psalms 118:19
content: 19 Open to me the gates of righteousness, that I may enter and give thanks to the LORD.

title: Psalms 118:20
content: 20 This is the gate of the LORD; the righteous shall enter through it.

title: Psalms 118:21
content: 21 I will give You thanks, for You have answered me, and You have become my salvation.

title: Psalms 118:22
content: 22 The stone the builders rejected has become the cornerstone.

title: Psalms 118:23
content: 23 This is from the LORD, and it is marvelous in our eyes.

title: Psalms 118:24
content: 24 This is the day that the LORD has made; we will rejoice and be glad in it.

title: Psalms 118:25
content: 25 O LORD, save us, we pray. We beseech You, O LORD, cause us to prosper!

title: Psalms 118:26
content: 26 Blessed is he who comes in the name of the LORD. From the house of the LORD we bless you.

title: Psalms 118:27
content: 27 The LORD is God; He has made His light to shine upon us. Bind the festal sacrifice with cords to the horns of the altar.

title: Psalms 118:28
content: 28 You are my God, and I will give You thanks. You are my God, and I will exalt You.

title: Psalms 118:29
content: 29 Give thanks to the LORD, for He is good; His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 119:1
content: 1 Blessed are those whose way is blameless, who walk in the Law of the LORD.

title: Psalms 119:2
content: 2 Blessed are those who keep His testimonies and seek Him with all their heart.

title: Psalms 119:3
content: 3 They do no iniquity; they walk in His ways.

title: Psalms 119:4
content: 4 You have ordained Your precepts, that we should keep them diligently.

title: Psalms 119:5
content: 5 Oh, that my ways were committed to keeping Your statutes!

title: Psalms 119:6
content: 6 Then I would not be ashamed when I consider all Your commandments.

title: Psalms 119:7
content: 7 I will praise You with an upright heart when I learn Your righteous judgments.

title: Psalms 119:8
content: 8 I will keep Your statutes; do not utterly forsake me.

title: Psalms 119:9
content: 9 How can a young man keep his way pure? By guarding it according to Your word.

title: Psalms 119:10
content: 10 With all my heart I have sought You; do not let me stray from Your commandments.

title: Psalms 119:11
content: 11 I have hidden Your word in my heart that I might not sin against You.

title: Psalms 119:12
content: 12 Blessed are You, O LORD; teach me Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:13
content: 13 With my lips I proclaim all the judgments of Your mouth.

title: Psalms 119:14
content: 14 I rejoice in the way of Your testimonies as much as in all riches.

title: Psalms 119:15
content: 15 I will meditate on Your precepts and regard Your ways.

title: Psalms 119:16
content: 16 I will delight in Your statutes; I will not forget Your word.

title: Psalms 119:17
content: 17 Deal bountifully with Your servant, that I may live and keep Your word.

title: Psalms 119:18
content: 18 Open my eyes that I may see wondrous things from Your law.

title: Psalms 119:19
content: 19 I am a stranger on the earth; do not hide Your commandments from me.

title: Psalms 119:20
