content: 20 My soul is consumed with longing for Your judgments at all times.

title: Psalms 119:21
content: 21 You rebuke the arrogant—the cursed who stray from Your commandments.

title: Psalms 119:22
content: 22 Remove my scorn and contempt, for I have kept Your testimonies.

title: Psalms 119:23
content: 23 Though rulers sit and slander me, Your servant meditates on Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:24
content: 24 Your testimonies are indeed my delight; they are my counselors.

title: Psalms 119:25
content: 25 My soul cleaves to the dust; revive me according to Your word.

title: Psalms 119:26
content: 26 I recounted my ways, and You answered me; teach me Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:27
content: 27 Make clear to me the way of Your precepts; then I will meditate on Your wonders.

title: Psalms 119:28
content: 28 My soul melts with sorrow; strengthen me according to Your word.

title: Psalms 119:29
content: 29 Remove me from the path of deceit and graciously grant me Your law.

title: Psalms 119:30
content: 30 I have chosen the way of truth; I have set Your ordinances before me.

title: Psalms 119:31
content: 31 I cling to Your testimonies, O LORD; let me not be put to shame.

title: Psalms 119:32
content: 32 I run in the path of Your commandments, for You will enlarge my heart.

title: Psalms 119:33
content: 33 Teach me, O LORD, the way of Your statutes, and I will keep them to the end.

title: Psalms 119:34
content: 34 Give me understanding that I may obey Your law, and follow it with all my heart.

title: Psalms 119:35
content: 35 Direct me in the path of Your commandments, for there I find delight.

title: Psalms 119:36
content: 36 Turn my heart to Your testimonies and not to covetous gain.

title: Psalms 119:37
content: 37 Turn my eyes away from worthless things; revive me with Your word.

title: Psalms 119:38
content: 38 Establish Your word to Your servant, to produce reverence for You.

title: Psalms 119:39
content: 39 Turn away the disgrace I dread, for Your judgments are good.

title: Psalms 119:40
content: 40 How I long for Your precepts! Revive me in Your righteousness.

title: Psalms 119:41
content: 41 May Your loving devotion come to me, O LORD, Your salvation, according to Your promise.

title: Psalms 119:42
content: 42 Then I can answer him who taunts, for I trust in Your word.

title: Psalms 119:43
content: 43 Never take Your word of truth from my mouth, for I hope in Your judgments.

title: Psalms 119:44
content: 44 I will always obey Your law, forever and ever.

title: Psalms 119:45
content: 45 And I will walk in freedom, for I have sought Your precepts.

title: Psalms 119:46
content: 46 I will speak of Your testimonies before kings, and I will not be ashamed.

title: Psalms 119:47
content: 47 I delight in Your commandments because I love them.

title: Psalms 119:48
content: 48 I lift up my hands to Your commandments, which I love, and I meditate on Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:49
content: 49 Remember Your word to Your servant, upon which You have given me hope.

title: Psalms 119:50
content: 50 This is my comfort in affliction, that Your promise has given me life.

title: Psalms 119:51
content: 51 The arrogant utterly deride me, but I do not turn from Your law.

title: Psalms 119:52
content: 52 I remember Your judgments of old, O LORD, and in them I find comfort.

title: Psalms 119:53
content: 53 Rage has taken hold of me because of the wicked who reject Your law.

title: Psalms 119:54
content: 54 Your statutes are songs to me in the house of my pilgrimage.

title: Psalms 119:55
content: 55 In the night, O LORD, I remember Your name, that I may keep Your law.

title: Psalms 119:56
content: 56 This is my practice, for I obey Your precepts.

title: Psalms 119:57
content: 57 The LORD is my portion; I have promised to keep Your words.

title: Psalms 119:58
content: 58 I have sought Your face with all my heart; be gracious to me according to Your promise.

title: Psalms 119:59
content: 59 I considered my ways and turned my steps to Your testimonies.

title: Psalms 119:60
content: 60 I hurried without hesitating to keep Your commandments.

title: Psalms 119:61
content: 61 Though the ropes of the wicked bind me, I do not forget Your law.

title: Psalms 119:62
content: 62 At midnight I rise to give You thanks for Your righteous judgments.

title: Psalms 119:63
content: 63 I am a friend to all who fear You, and to those who keep Your precepts.

title: Psalms 119:64
content: 64 The earth is filled with Your loving devotion, O LORD; teach me Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:65
content: 65 You are good to Your servant, O LORD, according to Your word.

title: Psalms 119:66
content: 66 Teach me good judgment and knowledge, for I believe in Your commandments.

title: Psalms 119:67
content: 67 Before I was afflicted, I went astray; but now I keep Your word.

title: Psalms 119:68
content: 68 You are good, and You do what is good; teach me Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:69
content: 69 Though the arrogant have smeared me with lies, I keep Your precepts with all my heart.

title: Psalms 119:70
content: 70 Their hearts are callous and insensitive, but I delight in Your law.

title: Psalms 119:71
content: 71 It was good for me to be afflicted, that I might learn Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:72
content: 72 The law from Your mouth is more precious to me than thousands of pieces of gold and silver.

title: Psalms 119:73
content: 73 Your hands have made me and fashioned me; give me understanding to learn Your commandments.

title: Psalms 119:74
content: 74 May those who fear You see me and rejoice, for I have hoped in Your word.

title: Psalms 119:75
content: 75 I know, O LORD, that Your judgments are righteous, and that in faithfulness You have afflicted me.

title: Psalms 119:76
content: 76 May Your loving devotion comfort me, I pray, according to Your promise to Your servant.

title: Psalms 119:77
content: 77 May Your compassion come to me, that I may live, for Your law is my delight.

title: Psalms 119:78
content: 78 May the arrogant be put to shame for subverting me with a lie; I will meditate on Your precepts.

title: Psalms 119:79
content: 79 May those who fear You turn to me, those who know Your testimonies.

title: Psalms 119:80
content: 80 May my heart be blameless in Your statutes, that I may not be put to shame.

title: Psalms 119:81
content: 81 My soul faints for Your salvation; I wait for Your word.

title: Psalms 119:82
content: 82 My eyes fail, looking for Your promise; I ask, “When will You comfort me?”

title: Psalms 119:83
content: 83 Though I am like a wineskin dried up by smoke, I do not forget Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:84
content: 84 How many days must Your servant wait? When will You execute judgment on my persecutors?

title: Psalms 119:85
content: 85 The arrogant have dug pits for me in violation of Your law.

title: Psalms 119:86
content: 86 All Your commandments are faithful; I am persecuted without cause—help me!

title: Psalms 119:87
content: 87 They almost wiped me from the earth, but I have not forsaken Your precepts.

title: Psalms 119:88
content: 88 Revive me according to Your loving devotion, that I may obey the testimony of Your mouth.

title: Psalms 119:89
content: 89 Your word, O LORD, is everlasting; it is firmly fixed in the heavens.

title: Psalms 119:90
content: 90 Your faithfulness continues through all generations; You established the earth, and it endures.

title: Psalms 119:91
content: 91 Your ordinances stand to this day, for all things are servants to You.

title: Psalms 119:92
content: 92 If Your law had not been my delight, then I would have perished in my affliction.

title: Psalms 119:93
content: 93 I will never forget Your precepts, for by them You have revived me.

title: Psalms 119:94
content: 94 I am Yours; save me, for I have sought Your precepts.

title: Psalms 119:95
content: 95 The wicked wait to destroy me, but I will ponder Your testimonies.

title: Psalms 119:96
content: 96 I have seen a limit to all perfection, but Your commandment is without limit.

title: Psalms 119:97
content: 97 Oh, how I love Your law! All day long it is my meditation.

title: Psalms 119:98
content: 98 Your commandments make me wiser than my enemies, for they are always with me.

title: Psalms 119:99
content: 99 I have more insight than all my teachers, for Your testimonies are my meditation.

title: Psalms 119:100
content: 100 I discern more than the elders, for I obey Your precepts.

title: Psalms 119:101
content: 101 I have kept my feet from every evil path, that I may keep Your word.

title: Psalms 119:102
content: 102 I have not departed from Your ordinances, for You Yourself have taught me.

title: Psalms 119:103
content: 103 How sweet are Your words to my taste—sweeter than honey in my mouth!

title: Psalms 119:104
content: 104 I gain understanding from Your precepts; therefore I hate every false way.

title: Psalms 119:105
content: 105 Your word is a lamp to my feet and a light to my path.

title: Psalms 119:106
content: 106 I have sworn and confirmed that I will keep Your righteous judgments.

title: Psalms 119:107
content: 107 I am severely afflicted, O LORD; revive me through Your word.

title: Psalms 119:108
content: 108 Accept the freewill offerings of my mouth, O LORD, and teach me Your judgments.

title: Psalms 119:109
content: 109 I constantly take my life in my hands, yet I do not forget Your law.

title: Psalms 119:110
content: 110 The wicked have set a snare for me, but I have not strayed from Your precepts.

title: Psalms 119:111
content: 111 Your testimonies are my heritage forever, for they are the joy of my heart.

title: Psalms 119:112
content: 112 I have inclined my heart to perform Your statutes, even to the very end.

title: Psalms 119:113
content: 113 The double-minded I despise, but Your law I love.

title: Psalms 119:114
content: 114 You are my hiding place and my shield; I put my hope in Your word.

title: Psalms 119:115
content: 115 Depart from me, you evildoers, that I may obey the commandments of my God.

title: Psalms 119:116
content: 116 Sustain me as You promised, that I may live; let me not be ashamed of my hope.

title: Psalms 119:117
content: 117 Uphold me, and I will be saved, that I may always regard Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:118
content: 118 You reject all who stray from Your statutes, for their deceitfulness is in vain.

title: Psalms 119:119
content: 119 All the wicked on earth You discard like dross; therefore I love Your testimonies.

title: Psalms 119:120
content: 120 My flesh trembles in awe of You; I stand in fear of Your judgments.

title: Psalms 119:121
content: 121 I have done what is just and right; do not leave me to my oppressors.

title: Psalms 119:122
content: 122 Ensure Your servant’s well-being; do not let the arrogant oppress me.

title: Psalms 119:123
content: 123 My eyes fail, looking for Your salvation, and for Your righteous promise.

title: Psalms 119:124
content: 124 Deal with Your servant according to Your loving devotion, and teach me Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:125
content: 125 I am Your servant; give me understanding, that I may know Your testimonies.

title: Psalms 119:126
content: 126 It is time for the LORD to act, for they have broken Your law.

title: Psalms 119:127
content: 127 Therefore I love Your commandments more than gold, even the purest gold.

title: Psalms 119:128
content: 128 Therefore I admire all Your precepts and hate every false way.

title: Psalms 119:129
content: 129 Wonderful are Your testimonies; therefore I obey them.

title: Psalms 119:130
content: 130 The unfolding of Your words gives light; it informs the simple.

title: Psalms 119:131
content: 131 I open my mouth and pant, longing for Your commandments.

title: Psalms 119:132
content: 132 Turn to me and show me mercy, as You do to those who love Your name.

title: Psalms 119:133
content: 133 Order my steps in Your word; let no sin rule over me.

title: Psalms 119:134
content: 134 Redeem me from the oppression of man, that I may keep Your precepts.

title: Psalms 119:135
content: 135 Make Your face shine upon Your servant, and teach me Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:136
content: 136 My eyes shed streams of tears because Your law is not obeyed.

title: Psalms 119:137
content: 137 Righteous are You, O LORD, and upright are Your judgments.

title: Psalms 119:138
content: 138 The testimonies You have laid down are righteous and altogether faithful.

title: Psalms 119:139
content: 139 My zeal has consumed me because my foes forget Your words.

title: Psalms 119:140
content: 140 Your promise is completely pure; therefore Your servant loves it.

title: Psalms 119:141
content: 141 I am lowly and despised, but I do not forget Your precepts.

title: Psalms 119:142
content: 142 Your righteousness is everlasting and Your law is true.

title: Psalms 119:143
content: 143 Trouble and distress have found me, but Your commandments are my delight.

title: Psalms 119:144
content: 144 Your testimonies are righteous forever. Give me understanding, that I may live.

title: Psalms 119:145
content: 145 I call with all my heart; answer me, O LORD! I will obey Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:146
content: 146 I call to You; save me, that I may keep Your testimonies.

title: Psalms 119:147
content: 147 I rise before dawn and cry for help; in Your word I have put my hope.

title: Psalms 119:148
content: 148 My eyes anticipate the watches of night, that I may meditate on Your word.

title: Psalms 119:149
content: 149 Hear my voice, O LORD, according to Your loving devotion; give me life according to Your justice.

title: Psalms 119:150
content: 150 Those who follow after wickedness draw near; they are far from Your law.

title: Psalms 119:151
content: 151 You are near, O LORD, and all Your commandments are true.

title: Psalms 119:152
content: 152 Long ago I learned from Your testimonies that You have established them forever.

title: Psalms 119:153
content: 153 Look upon my affliction and rescue me, for I have not forgotten Your law.

title: Psalms 119:154
content: 154 Defend my cause and redeem me; revive me according to Your word.

title: Psalms 119:155
content: 155 Salvation is far from the wicked because they do not seek Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:156
content: 156 Great are Your mercies, O LORD; revive me according to Your ordinances.

title: Psalms 119:157
content: 157 Though my persecutors and foes are many, I have not turned from Your testimonies.

title: Psalms 119:158
content: 158 I look on the faithless with loathing because they do not keep Your word.

title: Psalms 119:159
content: 159 Consider how I love Your precepts, O LORD; give me life according to Your loving devotion.

title: Psalms 119:160
content: 160 The entirety of Your word is truth, and all Your righteous judgments endure forever.

title: Psalms 119:161
content: 161 Rulers persecute me without cause, but my heart fears only Your word.

title: Psalms 119:162
content: 162 I rejoice in Your promise like one who finds great spoil.

title: Psalms 119:163
content: 163 I hate and abhor falsehood, but Your law I love.

title: Psalms 119:164
content: 164 Seven times a day I praise You for Your righteous judgments.

title: Psalms 119:165
content: 165 Abundant peace belongs to those who love Your law; nothing can make them stumble.

title: Psalms 119:166
content: 166 I wait for Your salvation, O LORD, and I carry out Your commandments.

title: Psalms 119:167
content: 167 I obey Your testimonies and love them greatly.

title: Psalms 119:168
content: 168 I obey Your precepts and Your testimonies, for all my ways are before You.

title: Psalms 119:169
content: 169 May my cry come before You, O LORD; give me understanding according to Your word.

title: Psalms 119:170
content: 170 May my plea come before You; rescue me according to Your promise.

title: Psalms 119:171
content: 171 My lips pour forth praise, for You teach me Your statutes.

title: Psalms 119:172
content: 172 My tongue sings of Your word, for all Your commandments are righteous.

title: Psalms 119:173
content: 173 May Your hand be ready to help me, for I have chosen Your precepts.

title: Psalms 119:174
content: 174 I long for Your salvation, O LORD, and Your law is my delight.

title: Psalms 119:175
content: 175 Let me live to praise You; may Your judgments sustain me.

title: Psalms 119:176
content: 176 I have strayed like a lost sheep; seek Your servant, for I have not forgotten Your commandments.

title: Psalms 120:0
content: 0 A song of ascents.

title: Psalms 120:1
content: 1 In my distress I cried to the LORD, and He answered me.

title: Psalms 120:2
content: 2 Deliver my soul, O LORD, from lying lips and a deceitful tongue.

title: Psalms 120:3
content: 3 What will He do to you, and what will be added to you, O deceitful tongue?

title: Psalms 120:4
content: 4 Sharp arrows will come from the warrior, with burning coals of the broom tree!

title: Psalms 120:5
content: 5 Woe to me that I dwell in Meshech, that I live among the tents of Kedar!

title: Psalms 120:6
content: 6 Too long have I dwelt among those who hate peace.

title: Psalms 120:7
content: 7 I am in favor of peace; but when I speak, they want war.

title: Psalms 121:0
content: 0 A song of ascents.

title: Psalms 121:1
content: 1 I lift up my eyes to the hills. From where does my help come?

title: Psalms 121:2
content: 2 My help comes from the LORD, the Maker of heaven and earth.

title: Psalms 121:3
content: 3 He will not allow your foot to slip; your Protector will not slumber.

title: Psalms 121:4
content: 4 Behold, the Protector of Israel will neither slumber nor sleep.

title: Psalms 121:5
content: 5 The LORD is your keeper; the LORD is the shade on your right hand.

title: Psalms 121:6
content: 6 The sun will not strike you by day, nor the moon by night.

title: Psalms 121:7
content: 7 The LORD will guard you from all evil; He will preserve your soul.

title: Psalms 121:8
content: 8 The LORD will watch over your coming and going, both now and forevermore.

title: Psalms 122:0
content: 0 A song of ascents. Of David.

title: Psalms 122:1
content: 1 I was glad when they said to me, “Let us go to the house of the LORD.”

title: Psalms 122:2
content: 2 Our feet are standing in your gates, O Jerusalem.

title: Psalms 122:3
content: 3 Jerusalem is built up as a city united together,

title: Psalms 122:4
content: 4 where the tribes go up, the tribes of the LORD, as a testimony for Israel, to give thanks to the name of the LORD.

title: Psalms 122:5
content: 5 For there the thrones of judgment stand, the thrones of the house of David.

title: Psalms 122:6
content: 6 Pray for the peace of Jerusalem: “May those who love you prosper.

title: Psalms 122:7
content: 7 May there be peace within your walls, and prosperity inside your fortresses.”

title: Psalms 122:8
content: 8 For the sake of my brothers and friends, I will say, “Peace be within you.”

title: Psalms 122:9
content: 9 For the sake of the house of the LORD our God, I will seek your prosperity.

title: Psalms 123:0
content: 0 A song of ascents.

title: Psalms 123:1
content: 1 I lift up my eyes to You, the One enthroned in heaven.

title: Psalms 123:2
content: 2 As the eyes of servants look to the hand of their master, as the eyes of a maidservant look to the hand of her mistress, so our eyes are on the LORD our God until He shows us mercy.

title: Psalms 123:3
content: 3 Have mercy on us, O LORD, have mercy, for we have endured much contempt.

title: Psalms 123:4
content: 4 We have endured much scorn from the arrogant, much contempt from the proud.

title: Psalms 124:0
content: 0 A song of ascents. Of David.

title: Psalms 124:1
content: 1 If the LORD had not been on our side—let Israel now declare—

title: Psalms 124:2
content: 2 if the LORD had not been on our side when men attacked us,

title: Psalms 124:3
content: 3 when their anger flared against us, then they would have swallowed us alive,

title: Psalms 124:4
content: 4 then the floods would have engulfed us, then the torrent would have overwhelmed us,

title: Psalms 124:5
content: 5 then the raging waters would have swept us away.

title: Psalms 124:6
content: 6 Blessed be the LORD, who has not given us as prey to their teeth.

title: Psalms 124:7
content: 7 We have escaped like a bird from the snare of the fowler; the net is torn, and we have slipped away.

title: Psalms 124:8
content: 8 Our help is in the name of the LORD, the Maker of heaven and earth.

title: Psalms 125:0
content: 0 A song of ascents.

title: Psalms 125:1
content: 1 Those who trust in the LORD are like Mount Zion. It cannot be moved; it abides forever.

title: Psalms 125:2
content: 2 As the mountains surround Jerusalem, so the LORD surrounds His people, both now and forevermore.

title: Psalms 125:3
content: 3 For the scepter of the wicked will not rest upon the land allotted to the righteous, so that the righteous will not put forth their hands to injustice.

title: Psalms 125:4
content: 4 Do good, O LORD, to those who are good, and to the upright in heart.

title: Psalms 125:5
content: 5 But those who turn to crooked ways the LORD will banish with the evildoers. Peace be upon Israel.

title: Psalms 126:0
content: 0 A song of ascents.

title: Psalms 126:1
content: 1 When the LORD restored the captives of Zion, we were like dreamers.

title: Psalms 126:2
content: 2 Then our mouths were filled with laughter, our tongues with shouts of joy. Then it was said among the nations, “The LORD has done great things for them.”

title: Psalms 126:3
content: 3 The LORD has done great things for us; we are filled with joy.

title: Psalms 126:4
content: 4 Restore our captives, O LORD, like streams in the Negev.

title: Psalms 126:5
content: 5 Those who sow in tears will reap with shouts of joy.

title: Psalms 126:6
content: 6 He who goes out weeping, bearing a trail of seed, will surely return with shouts of joy, carrying sheaves of grain.

title: Psalms 127:0
content: 0 A song of ascents. Of Solomon.

title: Psalms 127:1
content: 1 Unless the LORD builds the house, its builders labor in vain; unless the LORD protects the city, its watchmen stand guard in vain.

title: Psalms 127:2
content: 2 In vain you rise early and stay up late, toiling for bread to eat—for He gives sleep to His beloved.

title: Psalms 127:3
content: 3 Children are indeed a heritage from the LORD, and the fruit of the womb is His reward.

title: Psalms 127:4
content: 4 Like arrows in the hand of a warrior, so are children born in one’s youth.

title: Psalms 127:5
content: 5 Blessed is the man whose quiver is full of them. He will not be put to shame when he confronts the enemies at the gate.

title: Psalms 128:0
content: 0 A song of ascents.

title: Psalms 128:1
content: 1 Blessed are all who fear the LORD, who walk in His ways!

title: Psalms 128:2
content: 2 For when you eat the fruit of your labor, blessings and prosperity will be yours.

title: Psalms 128:3
content: 3 Your wife will be like a fruitful vine flourishing within your house, your sons like olive shoots sitting around your table.

title: Psalms 128:4
content: 4 In this way indeed shall blessing come to the man who fears the LORD.

title: Psalms 128:5
content: 5 May the LORD bless you from Zion, that you may see the prosperity of Jerusalem all the days of your life,

title: Psalms 128:6
content: 6 that you may see your children’s children. Peace be upon Israel!

title: Psalms 129:0
content: 0 A song of ascents.

title: Psalms 129:1
content: 1 Many a time they have persecuted me from my youth—let Israel now declare—

title: Psalms 129:2
content: 2 many a time they have persecuted me from my youth, but they have not prevailed against me.

title: Psalms 129:3
content: 3 The plowmen plowed over my back; they made their furrows long.

title: Psalms 129:4
content: 4 The LORD is righteous; He has cut me from the cords of the wicked.

title: Psalms 129:5
content: 5 May all who hate Zion be turned back in shame.

title: Psalms 129:6
content: 6 May they be like grass on the rooftops, which withers before it can grow,

title: Psalms 129:7
content: 7 unable to fill the hands of the reaper, or the arms of the binder of sheaves.

title: Psalms 129:8
content: 8 May none who pass by say to them, “The blessing of the LORD be on you; we bless you in the name of the LORD.”

title: Psalms 130:0
content: 0 A song of ascents.

title: Psalms 130:1
content: 1 Out of the depths I cry to You, O LORD!

title: Psalms 130:2
content: 2 O Lord, hear my voice; let Your ears be attentive to my plea for mercy.

title: Psalms 130:3
content: 3 If You, O LORD, kept track of iniquities, then who, O Lord, could stand?

title: Psalms 130:4
content: 4 But with You there is forgiveness, so that You may be feared.

title: Psalms 130:5
content: 5 I wait for the LORD; my soul does wait, and in His word I put my hope.

title: Psalms 130:6
content: 6 My soul waits for the Lord more than watchmen wait for the morning—more than watchmen wait for the morning.

title: Psalms 130:7
content: 7 O Israel, put your hope in the LORD, for with the LORD is loving devotion, and with Him is redemption in abundance.

title: Psalms 130:8
content: 8 And He will redeem Israel from all iniquity.

title: Psalms 131:0
content: 0 A song of ascents. Of David.

title: Psalms 131:1
content: 1 My heart is not proud, O LORD, my eyes are not haughty. I do not aspire to great things or matters too lofty for me.

title: Psalms 131:2
content: 2 Surely I have stilled and quieted my soul; like a weaned child with his mother, like a weaned child is my soul within me.

title: Psalms 131:3
content: 3 O Israel, put your hope in the LORD, both now and forevermore.

title: Psalms 132:0
content: 0 A song of ascents.

title: Psalms 132:1
content: 1 O LORD, remember on behalf of David all the hardships he endured,

title: Psalms 132:2
content: 2 how he swore an oath to the LORD, and vowed to the Mighty One of Jacob:

title: Psalms 132:3
content: 3 “I will not enter my house or get into my bed,

title: Psalms 132:4
content: 4 I will not give sleep to my eyes or slumber to my eyelids,

title: Psalms 132:5
content: 5 until I find a place for the LORD, a dwelling for the Mighty One of Jacob.”

title: Psalms 132:6
content: 6 We heard that the ark was in Ephrathah; we found it in the fields of Jaar.

title: Psalms 132:7
content: 7 Let us go to His dwelling place; let us worship at His footstool.

title: Psalms 132:8
content: 8 Arise, O LORD, to Your resting place, You and the ark of Your strength.

title: Psalms 132:9
content: 9 May Your priests be clothed with righteousness, and Your saints shout for joy.

title: Psalms 132:10
content: 10 For the sake of Your servant David, do not reject Your anointed one.

title: Psalms 132:11
content: 11 The LORD swore an oath to David, a promise He will not revoke: “One of your descendants I will place on your throne.

title: Psalms 132:12
content: 12 If your sons keep My covenant and the testimony I will teach them, then their sons will also sit on your throne forever and ever.”

title: Psalms 132:13
content: 13 For the LORD has chosen Zion; He has desired it for His home:

title: Psalms 132:14
content: 14 “This is My resting place forever and ever; here I will dwell, for I have desired this home.

title: Psalms 132:15
content: 15 I will bless her with abundant provisions; I will satisfy her poor with bread.

title: Psalms 132:16
content: 16 I will clothe her priests with salvation, and her saints will sing out in joy.

title: Psalms 132:17
content: 17 There I will make a horn grow for David; I have prepared a lamp for My anointed one.

title: Psalms 132:18
content: 18 I will clothe his enemies with shame, but the crown upon him will gleam.”

title: Psalms 133:0
content: 0 A song of ascents. Of David.

title: Psalms 133:1
content: 1 Behold, how good and pleasant it is when brothers live together in harmony!

title: Psalms 133:2
content: 2 It is like fine oil on the head, running down on the beard, running down Aaron’s beard over the collar of his robes.

title: Psalms 133:3
content: 3 It is like the dew of Hermon falling on the mountains of Zion. For there the LORD has bestowed the blessing of life forevermore.

title: Psalms 134:0
content: 0 A song of ascents.

title: Psalms 134:1
content: 1 Come, bless the LORD, all you servants of the LORD who serve by night in the house of the LORD!

title: Psalms 134:2
content: 2 Lift up your hands to the sanctuary and bless the LORD!

title: Psalms 134:3
content: 3 May the LORD, the Maker of heaven and earth, bless you from Zion.

title: Psalms 135:1
content: 1 Hallelujah! Praise the name of the LORD. Give praise, O servants of the LORD,

title: Psalms 135:2
content: 2 who stand in the house of the LORD, in the courts of the house of our God.

title: Psalms 135:3
content: 3 Hallelujah, for the LORD is good; sing praises to His name, for it is lovely.

title: Psalms 135:4
content: 4 For the LORD has chosen Jacob as His own, Israel as His treasured possession.

title: Psalms 135:5
content: 5 For I know that the LORD is great; our Lord is above all gods.

title: Psalms 135:6
content: 6 The LORD does all that pleases Him in the heavens and on the earth, in the seas and in all their depths.

title: Psalms 135:7
content: 7 He causes the clouds to rise from the ends of the earth. He generates the lightning with the rain and brings forth the wind from His storehouses.

title: Psalms 135:8
content: 8 He struck down the firstborn of Egypt, of both man and beast.

title: Psalms 135:9
content: 9 He sent signs and wonders into your midst, O Egypt, against Pharaoh and all his servants.

title: Psalms 135:10
content: 10 He struck down many nations and slaughtered mighty kings:

title: Psalms 135:11
content: 11 Sihon king of the Amorites, Og king of Bashan, and all the kings of Canaan.

title: Psalms 135:12
content: 12 He gave their land as an inheritance, as a heritage to His people Israel.

title: Psalms 135:13
content: 13 Your name, O LORD, endures forever, Your renown, O LORD, through all generations.

title: Psalms 135:14
content: 14 For the LORD will vindicate His people and will have compassion on His servants.

title: Psalms 135:15
content: 15 The idols of the nations are silver and gold, made by the hands of men.

title: Psalms 135:16
content: 16 They have mouths, but cannot speak; they have eyes, but cannot see;

title: Psalms 135:17
content: 17 they have ears, but cannot hear; nor is there breath in their mouths.

title: Psalms 135:18
content: 18 Those who make them become like them, as do all who trust in them.

title: Psalms 135:19
content: 19 O house of Israel, bless the LORD; O house of Aaron, bless the LORD;

title: Psalms 135:20
content: 20 O house of Levi, bless the LORD; you who fear the LORD, bless the LORD!

title: Psalms 135:21
content: 21 Blessed be the LORD from Zion—He who dwells in Jerusalem. Hallelujah!

title: Psalms 136:1
content: 1 Give thanks to the LORD, for He is good. His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:2
content: 2 Give thanks to the God of gods. His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:3
content: 3 Give thanks to the Lord of lords. His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:4
content: 4 He alone does great wonders. His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:5
content: 5 By His insight He made the heavens. His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:6
content: 6 He spread out the earth upon the waters. His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:7
content: 7 He made the great lights—His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:8
content: 8 the sun to rule the day, His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:9
content: 9 the moon and stars to govern the night. His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:10
content: 10 He struck down the firstborn of Egypt His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:11
content: 11 and brought Israel out from among them His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:12
content: 12 with a mighty hand and an outstretched arm. His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:13
content: 13 He divided the Red Sea in two His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:14
content: 14 and led Israel through the midst, His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:15
content: 15 but swept Pharaoh and his army into the Red Sea. His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:16
content: 16 He led His people through the wilderness. His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:17
content: 17 He struck down great kings His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:18
content: 18 and slaughtered mighty kings—His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:19
content: 19 Sihon king of the Amorites His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:20
content: 20 and Og king of Bashan—His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:21
content: 21 and He gave their land as an inheritance, His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:22
content: 22 a heritage to His servant Israel. His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:23
content: 23 He remembered us in our low estate His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:24
content: 24 and freed us from our enemies. His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:25
content: 25 He gives food to every creature. His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 136:26
content: 26 Give thanks to the God of heaven! His loving devotion endures forever.

title: Psalms 137:1
content: 1 By the rivers of Babylon we sat and wept when we remembered Zion.

title: Psalms 137:2
content: 2 There on the willows we hung our harps,

title: Psalms 137:3
content: 3 for there our captors requested a song; our tormentors demanded songs of joy: “Sing us a song of Zion.”

title: Psalms 137:4
content: 4 How can we sing a song of the LORD in a foreign land?

title: Psalms 137:5
content: 5 If I forget you, O Jerusalem, may my right hand cease to function.

title: Psalms 137:6
content: 6 May my tongue cling to the roof of my mouth if I do not remember you, if I do not exalt Jerusalem as my greatest joy!

title: Psalms 137:7
content: 7 Remember, O LORD, the sons of Edom on the day Jerusalem fell: “Destroy it,” they said, “tear it down to its foundations!”

title: Psalms 137:8
content: 8 O Daughter of Babylon, doomed to destruction, blessed is he who repays you as you have done to us.

title: Psalms 137:9
content: 9 Blessed is he who seizes your infants and dashes them against the rocks.

title: Psalms 138:0
content: 0 Of David.

title: Psalms 138:1
content: 1 I give You thanks with all my heart; before the gods I sing Your praises.

title: Psalms 138:2
content: 2 I bow down toward Your holy temple and give thanks to Your name for Your loving devotion and Your faithfulness; You have exalted Your name and Your word above all else.

title: Psalms 138:3
content: 3 On the day I called, You answered me; You emboldened me and strengthened my soul.

title: Psalms 138:4
content: 4 All the kings of the earth will give You thanks, O LORD, when they hear the words of Your mouth.

title: Psalms 138:5
content: 5 They will sing of the ways of the LORD, for the glory of the LORD is great.

title: Psalms 138:6
content: 6 Though the LORD is on high, He attends to the lowly; but the proud He knows from afar.

title: Psalms 138:7
content: 7 If I walk in the midst of trouble, You preserve me from the anger of my foes; You extend Your hand, and Your right hand saves me.

title: Psalms 138:8
content: 8 The LORD will fulfill His purpose for me. O LORD, Your loving devotion endures forever—do not abandon the works of Your hands.

title: Psalms 139:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 139:1
content: 1 O LORD, You have searched me and known me.

title: Psalms 139:2
content: 2 You know when I sit and when I rise; You understand my thoughts from afar.

title: Psalms 139:3
content: 3 You search out my path and my lying down; You are aware of all my ways.

title: Psalms 139:4
content: 4 Even before a word is on my tongue, You know all about it, O LORD.

title: Psalms 139:5
content: 5 You hem me in behind and before; You have laid Your hand upon me.

title: Psalms 139:6
content: 6 Such knowledge is too wonderful for me, too lofty for me to attain.

title: Psalms 139:7
content: 7 Where can I go to escape Your Spirit? Where can I flee from Your presence?

title: Psalms 139:8
content: 8 If I ascend to the heavens, You are there; if I make my bed in Sheol, You are there.

title: Psalms 139:9
content: 9 If I rise on the wings of the dawn, if I settle by the farthest sea,

title: Psalms 139:10
content: 10 even there Your hand will guide me; Your right hand will hold me fast.

title: Psalms 139:11
content: 11 If I say, “Surely the darkness will hide me, and the light become night around me”—

title: Psalms 139:12
content: 12 even the darkness is not dark to You, but the night shines like the day, for darkness is as light to You.

title: Psalms 139:13
content: 13 For You formed my inmost being; You knit me together in my mother’s womb.

title: Psalms 139:14
content: 14 I praise You, for I am fearfully and wonderfully made. Marvelous are Your works, and I know this very well.

title: Psalms 139:15
content: 15 My frame was not hidden from You when I was made in secret, when I was woven together in the depths of the earth.

title: Psalms 139:16
content: 16 Your eyes saw my unformed body; all my days were written in Your book and ordained for me before one of them came to be.

title: Psalms 139:17
content: 17 How precious to me are Your thoughts, O God, how vast is their sum!

title: Psalms 139:18
content: 18 If I were to count them, they would outnumber the grains of sand; and when I awake, I am still with You.

title: Psalms 139:19
content: 19 O God, that You would slay the wicked—away from me, you bloodthirsty men—

title: Psalms 139:20
content: 20 who speak of You deceitfully; Your enemies take Your name in vain.

title: Psalms 139:21
content: 21 Do I not hate those who hate You, O LORD, and detest those who rise against You?

title: Psalms 139:22
content: 22 I hate them with perfect hatred; I count them as my enemies.

title: Psalms 139:23
content: 23 Search me, O God, and know my heart; test me and know my concerns.

title: Psalms 139:24
content: 24 See if there is any offensive way in me; lead me in the way everlasting.

title: Psalms 140:0
content: 0 For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 140:1
content: 1 Rescue me, O LORD, from evil men. Protect me from men of violence,

title: Psalms 140:2
content: 2 who devise evil in their hearts and stir up war all day long.

title: Psalms 140:3
content: 3 They sharpen their tongues like snakes; the venom of vipers is on their lips. Selah

title: Psalms 140:4
content: 4 Guard me, O LORD, from the hands of the wicked. Keep me safe from men of violence who scheme to make me stumble.

title: Psalms 140:5
content: 5 The proud hide a snare for me; the cords of their net are spread along the path, and lures are set out for me. Selah

title: Psalms 140:6
content: 6 I say to the LORD, “You are my God.” Hear, O LORD, my cry for help.

title: Psalms 140:7
content: 7 O GOD the Lord, the strength of my salvation, You shield my head in the day of battle.

title: Psalms 140:8
content: 8 Grant not, O LORD, the desires of the wicked; do not promote their evil plans, lest they be exalted. Selah

title: Psalms 140:9
content: 9 May the heads of those who surround me be covered in the trouble their lips have caused.

title: Psalms 140:10
content: 10 May burning coals fall on them; may they be thrown into the fire, into the miry pits, never to rise again.

title: Psalms 140:11
content: 11 May no slanderer be established in the land; may calamity hunt down the man of violence.

title: Psalms 140:12
content: 12 I know that the LORD upholds justice for the poor and defends the cause of the needy.

title: Psalms 140:13
content: 13 Surely the righteous will praise Your name; the upright will dwell in Your presence.

title: Psalms 141:0
content: 0 A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 141:1
content: 1 I call upon You, O LORD; come quickly to me. Hear my voice when I call to You.

title: Psalms 141:2
content: 2 May my prayer be set before You like incense; my uplifted hands, like the evening offering.

title: Psalms 141:3
content: 3 Set a guard, O LORD, over my mouth; keep watch at the door of my lips.

title: Psalms 141:4
content: 4 Do not let my heart be drawn to any evil thing or take part in works of wickedness with men who do iniquity; let me not feast on their delicacies.

title: Psalms 141:5
content: 5 Let the righteous man strike me; let his rebuke be an act of loving devotion. It is oil for my head; let me not refuse it. For my prayer is ever against the deeds of the wicked.

title: Psalms 141:6
content: 6 When their rulers are thrown down from the cliffs, the people will listen to my words, for they are pleasant.

title: Psalms 141:7
content: 7 As when one plows and breaks up the soil, so our bones have been scattered at the mouth of Sheol.

title: Psalms 141:8
content: 8 But my eyes are fixed on You, O GOD the Lord. In You I seek refuge; do not leave my soul defenseless.

title: Psalms 141:9
content: 9 Keep me from the snares they have laid for me, and from the lures of evildoers.

title: Psalms 141:10
content: 10 Let the wicked fall into their own nets, while I pass by in safety.

title: Psalms 142:0
content: 0 A Maskil of David, when he was in the cave. A prayer.

title: Psalms 142:1
content: 1 I cry aloud to the LORD; I lift my voice to the LORD for mercy.

title: Psalms 142:2
content: 2 I pour out my complaint before Him; I reveal my trouble to Him.

title: Psalms 142:3
content: 3 Although my spirit grows faint within me, You know my way. Along the path I travel they have hidden a snare for me.

title: Psalms 142:4
content: 4 Look to my right and see; no one attends to me. There is no refuge for me; no one cares for my soul.

title: Psalms 142:5
content: 5 I cry to You, O LORD: “You are my refuge, my portion in the land of the living.”

title: Psalms 142:6
content: 6 Listen to my cry, for I am brought quite low. Rescue me from my pursuers, for they are too strong for me.

title: Psalms 142:7
content: 7 Free my soul from prison, that I may praise Your name. The righteous will gather around me because of Your goodness to me.

title: Psalms 143:0
content: 0 A Psalm of David.

title: Psalms 143:1
content: 1 O LORD, hear my prayer. In Your faithfulness, give ear to my plea; in Your righteousness, answer me.

title: Psalms 143:2
content: 2 Do not bring Your servant into judgment, for no one alive is righteous before You.

title: Psalms 143:3
content: 3 For the enemy has pursued my soul, crushing my life to the ground, making me dwell in darkness like those long since dead.

title: Psalms 143:4
content: 4 My spirit grows faint within me; my heart is dismayed inside me.

title: Psalms 143:5
content: 5 I remember the days of old; I meditate on all Your works; I consider the work of Your hands.

title: Psalms 143:6
content: 6 I stretch out my hands to You; my soul thirsts for You like a parched land. Selah

title: Psalms 143:7
content: 7 Answer me quickly, O LORD; my spirit fails. Do not hide Your face from me, or I will be like those who descend to the Pit.

title: Psalms 143:8
content: 8 Let me hear Your loving devotion in the morning, for I have put my trust in You. Teach me the way I should walk, for to You I lift up my soul.

title: Psalms 143:9
content: 9 Deliver me from my enemies, O LORD; I flee to You for refuge.

title: Psalms 143:10
content: 10 Teach me to do Your will, for You are my God. May Your good Spirit lead me on level ground.

title: Psalms 143:11
content: 11 For the sake of Your name, O LORD, revive me. In Your righteousness, bring my soul out of trouble.

title: Psalms 143:12
content: 12 And in Your loving devotion, cut off my enemies. Destroy all who afflict me, for I am Your servant.

title: Psalms 144:0
content: 0 Of David.

title: Psalms 144:1
content: 1 Blessed be the LORD, my Rock, who trains my hands for war, my fingers for battle.

title: Psalms 144:2
content: 2 He is my steadfast love and my fortress, my stronghold and my deliverer. He is my shield, in whom I take refuge, who subdues peoples under me.

title: Psalms 144:3
content: 3 O LORD, what is man, that You regard him, the son of man that You think of him?

title: Psalms 144:4
content: 4 Man is like a breath; his days are like a passing shadow.

title: Psalms 144:5
content: 5 Part Your heavens, O LORD, and come down; touch the mountains, that they may smoke.

title: Psalms 144:6
content: 6 Flash forth Your lightning and scatter them; shoot Your arrows and rout them.

title: Psalms 144:7
content: 7 Reach down from on high; set me free and rescue me from the deep waters, from the grasp of foreigners,

title: Psalms 144:8
content: 8 whose mouths speak falsehood, whose right hands are deceitful.

title: Psalms 144:9
content: 9 I will sing to You a new song, O God; on a harp of ten strings I will make music to You—

title: Psalms 144:10
content: 10 to Him who gives victory to kings, who frees His servant David from the deadly sword.

title: Psalms 144:11
content: 11 Set me free and rescue me from the grasp of foreigners, whose mouths speak falsehood, whose right hands are deceitful.

title: Psalms 144:12
content: 12 Then our sons will be like plants nurtured in their youth, our daughters like corner pillars carved to adorn a palace.

title: Psalms 144:13
content: 13 Our storehouses will be full, supplying all manner of produce; our flocks will bring forth thousands, tens of thousands in our fields.

title: Psalms 144:14
content: 14 Our oxen will bear great loads. There will be no breach in the walls, no going into captivity, and no cry of lament in our streets.

title: Psalms 144:15
content: 15 Blessed are the people of whom this is so; blessed are the people whose God is the LORD.

title: Psalms 145:0
content: 0 A Psalm of praise. Of David.

title: Psalms 145:1
content: 1 I will exalt You, my God and King; I will bless Your name forever and ever.

title: Psalms 145:2
content: 2 Every day I will bless You, and I will praise Your name forever and ever.

title: Psalms 145:3
content: 3 Great is the LORD and greatly to be praised; His greatness is unsearchable.

title: Psalms 145:4
content: 4 One generation will commend Your works to the next, and will proclaim Your mighty acts—

title: Psalms 145:5
content: 5 the glorious splendor of Your majesty. And I will meditate on Your wondrous works.

title: Psalms 145:6
content: 6 They will proclaim the power of Your awesome deeds, and I will declare Your greatness.

title: Psalms 145:7
content: 7 They will extol the fame of Your abundant goodness and sing joyfully of Your righteousness.

title: Psalms 145:8
content: 8 The LORD is gracious and compassionate, slow to anger and abounding in loving devotion.

title: Psalms 145:9
content: 9 The LORD is good to all; His compassion rests on all He has made.

title: Psalms 145:10
content: 10 All You have made will give You thanks, O LORD, and Your saints will bless You.

title: Psalms 145:11
content: 11 They will tell of the glory of Your kingdom and speak of Your might,

title: Psalms 145:12
content: 12 to make known to men Your mighty acts and the glorious splendor of Your kingdom.

title: Psalms 145:13
content: 13 Your kingdom is an everlasting kingdom, and Your dominion endures through all generations. The LORD is faithful in all His words and kind in all His actions.

title: Psalms 145:14
content: 14 The LORD upholds all who fall and lifts up all who are bowed down.

title: Psalms 145:15
content: 15 The eyes of all look to You, and You give them their food in season.

title: Psalms 145:16
content: 16 You open Your hand and satisfy the desire of every living thing.

title: Psalms 145:17
content: 17 The LORD is righteous in all His ways and kind in all His deeds.

title: Psalms 145:18
content: 18 The LORD is near to all who call on Him, to all who call out to Him in truth.

title: Psalms 145:19
content: 19 He fulfills the desires of those who fear Him; He hears their cry and saves them.

title: Psalms 145:20
content: 20 The LORD preserves all who love Him, but all the wicked He will destroy.

title: Psalms 145:21
content: 21 My mouth will declare the praise of the LORD; let every creature bless His holy name forever and ever.

title: Psalms 146:1
content: 1 Hallelujah! Praise the LORD, O my soul.

title: Psalms 146:2
content: 2 I will praise the LORD all my life; I will sing praises to my God while I have my being.

title: Psalms 146:3
content: 3 Put not your trust in princes, in mortal man, who cannot save.

title: Psalms 146:4
content: 4 When his spirit departs, he returns to the ground; on that very day his plans perish.

title: Psalms 146:5
content: 5 Blessed is he whose help is the God of Jacob, whose hope is in the LORD his God,

title: Psalms 146:6
content: 6 the Maker of heaven and earth, the sea, and everything in them. He remains faithful forever.

title: Psalms 146:7
content: 7 He executes justice for the oppressed and gives food to the hungry. The LORD sets the prisoners free,

title: Psalms 146:8
content: 8 the LORD opens the eyes of the blind, the LORD lifts those who are weighed down, the LORD loves the righteous.

title: Psalms 146:9
content: 9 The LORD protects foreigners; He sustains the fatherless and the widow, but the ways of the wicked He frustrates.

title: Psalms 146:10
content: 10 The LORD reigns forever, your God, O Zion, for all generations. Hallelujah!

title: Psalms 147:1
content: 1 Hallelujah! How good it is to sing praises to our God, how pleasant and lovely to praise Him!

title: Psalms 147:2
content: 2 The LORD builds up Jerusalem; He gathers the exiles of Israel.

title: Psalms 147:3
content: 3 He heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds.

title: Psalms 147:4
content: 4 He determines the number of the stars; He calls them each by name.

title: Psalms 147:5
content: 5 Great is our Lord, and mighty in power; His understanding has no limit.

title: Psalms 147:6
content: 6 The LORD sustains the humble, but casts the wicked to the ground.

title: Psalms 147:7
content: 7 Sing to the LORD with thanksgiving; make music on the harp to our God,

title: Psalms 147:8
content: 8 who covers the sky with clouds, who prepares rain for the earth, who makes grass to grow on the hills.

title: Psalms 147:9
content: 9 He provides food for the animals, and for the young ravens when they call.

title: Psalms 147:10
content: 10 He does not delight in the strength of the horse; He takes no pleasure in the legs of a man.

title: Psalms 147:11
content: 11 The LORD is pleased with those who fear Him, who hope in His loving devotion.

title: Psalms 147:12
content: 12 Exalt the LORD, O Jerusalem; praise your God, O Zion!

title: Psalms 147:13
content: 13 For He strengthens the bars of your gates and blesses the children within you.

title: Psalms 147:14
content: 14 He makes peace at your borders; He fills you with the finest wheat.

title: Psalms 147:15
content: 15 He sends forth His command to the earth; His word runs swiftly.

title: Psalms 147:16
content: 16 He spreads the snow like wool; He scatters the frost like ashes;

title: Psalms 147:17
content: 17 He casts forth His hail like pebbles. Who can withstand His icy blast?

title: Psalms 147:18
content: 18 He sends forth His word and melts them; He unleashes His winds, and the waters flow.

title: Psalms 147:19
content: 19 He declares His word to Jacob, His statutes and judgments to Israel.

title: Psalms 147:20
content: 20 He has done this for no other nation; they do not know His judgments. Hallelujah!

title: Psalms 148:1
content: 1 Hallelujah! Praise the LORD from the heavens; praise Him in the highest places.

title: Psalms 148:2
content: 2 Praise Him, all His angels; praise Him, all His heavenly hosts.

title: Psalms 148:3
content: 3 Praise Him, O sun and moon; praise Him, all you shining stars.

title: Psalms 148:4
content: 4 Praise Him, O highest heavens, and you waters above the skies.

title: Psalms 148:5
content: 5 Let them praise the name of the LORD, for He gave the command and they were created.

title: Psalms 148:6
content: 6 He established them forever and ever; He issued a decree that will never pass away.

title: Psalms 148:7
content: 7 Praise the LORD from the earth, all great sea creatures and ocean depths,

title: Psalms 148:8
content: 8 lightning and hail, snow and clouds, powerful wind fulfilling His word,

title: Psalms 148:9
content: 9 mountains and all hills, fruit trees and all cedars,

title: Psalms 148:10
content: 10 wild animals and all cattle, crawling creatures and flying birds,

title: Psalms 148:11
content: 11 kings of the earth and all peoples, princes and all rulers of the earth,

title: Psalms 148:12
content: 12 young men and maidens, old and young together.

title: Psalms 148:13
content: 13 Let them praise the name of the LORD, for His name alone is exalted; His splendor is above the earth and the heavens.

title: Psalms 148:14
content: 14 He has raised up a horn for His people, the praise of all His saints, of Israel, a people near to Him. Hallelujah!

title: Psalms 149:1
content: 1 Hallelujah! Sing to the LORD a new song—His praise in the assembly of the godly.

title: Psalms 149:2
content: 2 Let Israel rejoice in their Maker; let the children of Zion rejoice in their King.

title: Psalms 149:3
content: 3 Let them praise His name with dancing, and make music to Him with tambourine and harp.

title: Psalms 149:4
content: 4 For the LORD takes pleasure in His people; He adorns the afflicted with salvation.

title: Psalms 149:5
content: 5 Let the saints exult in glory; let them shout for joy upon their beds.

title: Psalms 149:6
content: 6 May the high praises of God be in their mouths, and a double-edged sword in their hands,

title: Psalms 149:7
content: 7 to inflict vengeance on the nations and punishment on the peoples,

title: Psalms 149:8
content: 8 to bind their kings with chains and their nobles with shackles of iron,

title: Psalms 149:9
content: 9 to execute the judgment written against them. This honor is for all His saints. Hallelujah!

title: Psalms 150:1
content: 1 Hallelujah! Praise God in His sanctuary. Praise Him in His mighty heavens.

title: Psalms 150:2
content: 2 Praise Him for His mighty acts; praise Him for His excellent greatness.

title: Psalms 150:3
content: 3 Praise Him with the sound of the horn; praise Him with the harp and lyre.

title: Psalms 150:4
content: 4 Praise Him with tambourine and dancing; praise Him with strings and flute.

title: Psalms 150:5
content: 5 Praise Him with clashing cymbals; praise Him with resounding cymbals.

title: Psalms 150:6
content: 6 Let everything that has breath praise the LORD! Hallelujah!
